###Block:Abilities																																
Rage	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can imbue yourself with a primal power called Rage, a force that grants you extraordinary might and resilience. You can enter it as a Bonus Action if you aren't wearing Heavy armor. You can enter your Rage the number of times shown for your Barbarian level in the Rages column of the Barbarian Features table ( %2 ). You regain one expended use when you finish a Short Rest, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. While active, your Rage follows the rules below. &nl; Damage Resistance. You have Resistance to Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing damage. &nl; Rage Damage. When you make an attack using Strength-with either a weapon or an Unarmed Strike-and deal damage to the target, you gain a bonus to the damage that increases as you gain levels as a Barbarian, as shown in the Rage Damage column of the Barbarian Features table. ( +%1 ) &nl; Strength Advantage. You have Advantage on Strength checks and Strength saving throws. No Concentration or Spells. You can't maintain Concentration, and you can't cast spells. &nl; Duration. The Rage lasts until the end of your next turn, and it ends early if you don Heavy armor or have the Incapacitated condition. If your Rage is still active on your next turn, you can extend the Rage for another round by doing one of the following: &nl; Make an attack roll against an enemy. &nl; Force an enemy to make a saving throw. &nl; Take a Bonus Action to extend your Rage. &nl; Each time the Rage is extended, it lasts until the end of your next turn. You can maintain a Rage for up to 10 minutes.|RageDamageBonus|RageTimes	KEY:Barbarian ~ Rage				DEFINE:Raging|0	DEFINE:RageDamageBonus|0	DEFINE:RageTimes|0			BONUS:VAR|MeleeStrBonus|RageDamageBonus|PREVAREQ:Raging,1	BONUS:VAR|RageTimes|2+(BarbarianLVL>2)+(BarbarianLVL>5)+(BarbarianLVL>11)+(BarbarianLVL>16)	BONUS:VAR|RageDamageBonus|2+(BarbarianLVL>8)+(BarbarianLVL>15)														TEMPBONUS:PC|VAR|Raging|1	SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Unarmored Defense	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:While you aren't wearing any armor, your base Armor Class equals 10 plus your Dexterity and Constitution modifiers. You can use a Shield and still gain this benefit.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Unarmored Defense																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Weapon Mastery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your training with weapons allows you to use the mastery properties of two kinds of Simple or Martial Melee weapons of your choice, such as Greataxes and Handaxes. Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can practice weapon drills and change one of those weapon choices. When you reach certain Barbarian levels, you gain the ability to use the mastery properties of more kinds of weapons, as shown in the Weapon Mastery column of the Barbarian Features table.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Weapon Mastery	DESC:%1 weapon mastery.|WeaponMastery			DEFINE:WeaponMastery|0					BONUS:VAR|POOL_Weapon_Mastery|WeaponMastery	BONUS:VAR|WeaponMastery|2+(BarbarianLVL>=4)+(BarbarialLVL>=10)																SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Danger Sense	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain an uncanny sense of when things aren't as they should be, giving you an edge when you dodge perils. You have Advantage on Dexterity saving throws unless you have the Incapacitated condition.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Danger Sense																									ASPECT:SaveBonus|You have Advantage on Dexterity saving throws unless you have the Incapacitated condition.	SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Reckless Attack	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can throw aside all concern for defense to attack with increased ferocity. When you make your first attack roll on your turn, you can decide to attack recklessly. Doing so gives you Advantage on attack rolls using Strength until the start of your next turn, but attack rolls against you have Advantage during that time.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Reckless Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Barbarian Subclass	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a Barbarian subclass of your choice. The Path of the Berserker, Path of the Wild Heart, Path of the World Tree, and Path of the Zealot subclasses are detailed after this class's description. A subclass is a specialization that grants you features at certain Barbarian levels. For the rest of your career, you gain each of your subclass's features that are of your Barbarian level or lower.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Barbarian Subclass									BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Barbarian Subclass|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Primal Knowledge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain proficiency in another skill of your choice from the skill list available to Barbarians at level 1. In addition, while your Rage is active, you can channel primal power when you attempt certain tasks; whenever you make an ability check using one of the following skills, you can make it as a Strength check even if it normally uses a different ability: Acrobatics, Intimidation, Perception, Stealth, or Survival. When you use this ability, your Strength represents primal power coursing through you, honing your agility, bearing, and senses.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Primal Knowledge									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Barbarian_Skill|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01g	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ability Score Improvement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the Ability Score Improvement feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. You gain this feature again at Barbarian levels 8,12, and 16.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Ability Score Improvement									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Feat|1*((BarbarianLVL>=4)+(BarbarianLVL>=8)+(BarbarianLVL>=12)+(BarbarianLVL>=16))																	SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01h	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Extra Attack	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can attack twice instead of once whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Extra Attack																		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Extra Attack ~ 1								SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01i	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Fast Movement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your speed increases by 10 feet while you aren't wearing Heavy armor.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Fast Movement									BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Walk|10|!PREEQUIP:1,TYPE=Armor.Heavy																	SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01j	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Feral Instinct	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your instincts are so honed that you have Advantage on Initiative rolls.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Feral Instinct																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01k	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Instinctive Pounce	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As part of the Bonus Action you take to enter your Rage, you can move up to half your Speed.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Instinctive Pounce																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01l	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Brutal Strike	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If you use Reckless Attack, you can forgo any Advantage on one Strength-based attack roll of your choice on your turn. The chosen attack roll mustn't have Disadvantage. If the chosen attack roll hits, the target takes an extra %1d10 damage of the same type dealt by the weapon or Unarmed Strike, and you can cause one Brutal Strike effect of your choice. You have the following effect options. &nl; Forceful Blow. The target is pushed 15 feet straight away from you. You can then move up to half your Speed straight toward the target without provoking Opportunity Attacks. &nl; Hamstring Blow. The target's Speed is reduced by 15 feet until the start of your next turn. A target can be affected by only one Hamstring Blow at a time- the most recent one.|BrutalStrikeDice	KEY:Barbarian ~ Brutal Strike				DEFINE:BrutalStrikeDice|0					BONUS:VAR|BrutalStrikeDice|1+(BarbarialLVL>=17)																	SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01m	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Relentless Rage	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your Rage can keep you fighting despite grievous wounds. If you drop to 0 Hit Points while your Rage is active and don't die outright, you can make a DC 10 Constitution saving throw. If you succeed, your Hit Points instead change to a number equal to twice your Barbarian level. Each time you use this feature after the first, the DC increases by 5. When you finish a Short or Long Rest, the DC resets to 10.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Relentless Rage																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01n	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Improved Brutal Strike	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have honed new ways to attack furiously. The following effects are now among your Brutal Strike Options. &nl; Staggering Blow. The target has Disadvantage on the next saving throw it makes, and it can't make Opportunity Attacks until the start of your next Turn. &nl; Sundering Blow. Before the start of your next turn, the next attack roll made by another creature against the target gains a +5 bonus to the roll. An attack roll can gain only one Sundering Blow bonus.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Improved Brutal Strike																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01o	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Persistent Rage	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you roll Initiative, you can regain all expended uses of Rage. After you regain uses of Rage in this way, you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest. In addition, your Rage is so fierce that it now lasts for 10 minutes without you needing to do anything to extend it from round to round. Your Rage ends early if you have the Unconscious condition (not just the Incapacitated condition) or don Heavy armor.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Persistent Rage																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01p	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Indomitable Might	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If your total for a Strength check or Strength saving throw is less than your Strength score, you can use that score in place of the total.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Indomitable Might																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01q	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Epic Boon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain an Epic Boon feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. Boon of Irresistible Offense is recommended.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Epic Boon									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Epic_Boon|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01r	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Primal Champion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You embody primal power. Your Strength and Constitution scores increase by 4, to a maximum of 25.	KEY:Barbarian ~ Primal Champion																ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|TYPE=PrimalChampionAbility										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01s	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block:Barbarian Subclass																																
Path of the Berserker	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Barbarian Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Barbarians who walk the Path of the Berserker direct their Rage primarily toward violence. Their path is one of untrammeled fury, and they thrill in the chaos of battle as they allow their Rage to seize and empower them.	KEY:Barbarian Subclass ~ Path of the Berserker																		ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Berserker ~ Frenzy|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,3	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Berserker ~ Mindless Rage|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,6	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Berserker ~ Retaliation|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,10	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Berserker ~ Intimidating Presence|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,14					SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Path of the Wild Heart	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Barbarian Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Barbarians who follow the Path of the Wild Heart view themselves as kin to animals. These Barbarians learn magical means to communicate with animals, and their Rage heightens their connection to animals as it fills them with supernatural might.	KEY:Barbarian Subclass ~ Path of Wild Heart																		ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Wild Heart ~ Animal Speaker|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,3	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Wild Heart ~ Rage of the Wilds|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,3	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Wild Heart ~ Aspect of the Wilds|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,6	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Wild Heart ~ Nature Speaker|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,10	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Wild Heart ~ Power of the Wilds|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,14				SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Path of the World Tree	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Barbarian Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Barbarians who follow the Path of the World Tree connect with the cosmic tree Yggdrasil through their Rage. This tree grows among the Outer Planes, connecting them to each other and the Material Plane. These Barbarians draw on the tree's magic for vitality and as a means of dimensional travel.	KEY:Barbarian Subclass ~ Path of World Tree																		ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the World Tree ~ Vitality of the Tree|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,3	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the World Tree ~ Branches of the Tree|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,6	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the World Tree ~ Battering Roots|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,10	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the World Tree ~ Travel Along the Tree|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,14					SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Pact of the Zealot	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Barbarian Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Barbarians who walk the Path of the Zealot receive boons from a god or pantheon. These Barbarians experience their Rage as an ecstatic episode of divine union that infuses them with power. They are often allies to the priests and other followers of their god or pantheon.	KEY:Barbarian Subclass ~ Path of the Zealot																		ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Zealot ~ Divine Fury|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,3	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Zealot ~ Warrior of the Gods|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,3	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Zealot ~ Fanatical Focus|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,6	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Zealot ~ Zealous Presence|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,10	ABILITY:Barbarian Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Path of the Zealot ~ Rage of the Gods|PREVAREQ:BarbarianLVL,14				SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Frenzy	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Berserker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Starting when you choose this path at 3rd level, you can go into a frenzy when you rage. If you do so, for the duration of your rage you can make a single melee weapon attack as a bonus action on each of your turns after this one. When your rage ends, you suffer one level of exhaustion (as described in appendix A).	KEY:Path of the Berserker ~ Frenzy																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f1a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Mindless Rage	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Berserker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Beginning at 6th level, you can't be charmed or frightened while raging. If you are charmed or frightened when you enter your rage, the effect is suspended for the duration of the rage.	KEY:Path of the Berserker ~ Mindless Rage																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f1b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Retaliation	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Berserker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Starting at 14th level, when you take damage from a creature that is within 5 feet of you. you can use your reaction to make a melee weapon attack against that creature.	KEY:Path of the Berserker ~ Retaliation																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f1c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Intimidating Presence	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Berserker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Beginning at 10th level, you can use your action to frighten someone with your menacing presence. When you do so, choose one creature that you can see within 30 feet of you. If the creature can see or hear you, it must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw (DC equal to %1) or be frightened of you until the end of your next turn. On subsequent turns, you can use your action to extend the duration of this effect on the frightened creature until the end of your next turn. This effect ends if the creature ends its turn out of line of sight or more than 60 feet away from you. If the creature succeeds on its saving throw, you can't use this feature on that creature again for 24 hours.|8+Proficiency_Bonus+CHA	KEY:Path of the Berserker ~ Intimidating Presence																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f1d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Animal Speaker	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Wild Heart.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast the Beast Sense and Speak with Animals spells but only as Rituals. Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for them.	KEY:Path of the Wild Heart ~ Animal Speaker																		SPELLS:Animal Speaker|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=BarbarianLVL|Beast Sense(Ritual)	SPELLS:Animal Speaker|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=BarbarianLVL|Speak with Animals(Ritual)							SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f2a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Rage of the Wilds	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Wild Heart.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your Rage taps into the primal power of animals. Whenever you activate your Rage, you gain one of the following options of your choice. &nl; Bear. While your Rage is active, you have Resistance to every damage type except Force, Necrotic, Psychic, and Radiant. &nl; Eagle. When you activate your Rage, you can take the Disengage and Dash actions as part of that Bonus Action. While your Rage is active, you can take a Bonus Action to take both of those actions. &nl; Wolf. While your Rage is active, your allies have Advantage on attack rolls against any enemy of yours within 5 feet of you.	KEY:Path of the Wild Heart ~ Rage of the Wilds																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f2b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Aspect of the Wilds	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Wild Heart.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain one of the following options of your choice. Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can change your choice. &nl; Owl. You have Darkvision with a range of 60 feet. If you already have Darkvision, its range increases by 60 feet. &nl; Panther. You have a Climb Speed equal to your Speed. &nl; Salmon. You have a Swim Speed equal to your Speed.	KEY:Path of the Wild Heart ~ Aspect of the Wilds																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f2c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Nature Speaker	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Wild Heart.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast the Commune with Nature spell but only as a Ritual. Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for it.	KEY:Path of the Wild Heart ~ Nature Speaker																		SPELLS:Nature Speaker|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=BarbarianLVL|Commune with Nature(Ritual)								SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f2d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Power of the Wilds	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Wild Heart.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever you activate your Rage, you gain one of the following options of your choice. &nl; Falcon. While your Rage is active, you have a Fly Speed equal to your Speed if you aren't wearing any armor. &nl; Lion. While your Rage is active, any of your enemies within 5 feet of you have Disadvantage on attack rolls against targets other than you or another Barbarian who has this option active. &nl; Ram. While your Rage is active, you can cause a Large or smaller creature to have the Prone condition when you hit it with a melee attack.	KEY:Path of the Wild Heart ~ Power of the Wilds																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f2e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Vitality of the Tree	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the World Tree.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your Rage taps into the life force of the World Tree. You gain the following benefits. &nl; Vitality Surge. When you activate your Rage, you gain a number of Temporary Hit Points equal to your Barbarian level. &nl; Life-Giving Force. At the start of each of your turns while your Rage is active, you can choose another creature within 10 feet of yourself to gain Temporary Hit Points. To determine the number of Temporary Hit Points, roll a number of d6s equal to your Rage Damage bonus, and add them together. If any of these Temporary Hit Points remain when your Rage ends, they vanish.	KEY:Path of the World Tree ~ Vitality of the Tree																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f3a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Branches of the Tree	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the World Tree.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever a creature you can see starts its turn within 30 feet of you while your Rage is active, you can take a Reaction to summon spectral branches of the World Tree around it. The target must succeed on a Strength saving throw (DC 8 plus your Strength modifier and Proficiency Bonus) or be teleported to an unoccupied space you can see within 5 feet of yourself or in the nearest unoccupied space you can see. After the target teleports, you can reduce its Speed to 0 until the end of the current turn.	KEY:Path of the World Tree ~ Branches of the Tree																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f3b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Battering Roots	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the World Tree.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:During your turn, your reach is 10 feet greater with any Melee weapon that has the Heavy or Versatile property, as tendrils of the World Tree extend from you. When you hit with such a weapon on your turn, you can activate the Push or Topple mastery property in addition to a different mastery property you're using with that weapon.	KEY:Path of the World Tree ~ Battering Roots																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f3c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Travel Along the Tree	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the World Tree.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you activate your Rage and as a Bonus Action while your Rage is active, you can teleport up to 60 feet to an unoccupied space you can see. In addition, once per Rage, you can increase the range of that teleport to 150 feet. When you do so, you can also bring up to six willing creatures who are within 10 feet of you. Each creature teleports to an unoccupied space of your choice within 10 feet of your destination space.	KEY:Path of the World Tree ~ Travel Along the Tree																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f3d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Divine Fury	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Zealot.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can channel divine power into your strikes. On each of your turns while your Rage is active, the first creature you hit with a weapon or an Unarmed Strike takes extra damage equal to ld6 plus half your Barbarian level (round down). The extra damage is Necrotic or Radiant; you choose the type each time you deal the damage.	KEY:Path of the Zealot ~ Divine Fury																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f4a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Warrior of the Gods	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Zealot.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A divine entity helps ensure you can continue the fight. You have a pool of four dl2s that you can spend to heal yourself. As a Bonus Action, you can expend dice from the pool, roll them, and regain a number of Hit Points equal to the roll's total. Your pool regains all expended dice when you finish a Long Rest. The pool's maximum number of dice increases by one when you reach Barbarian levels 6 (5 dice), 12 (6 dice), and 17 (7 dice).	KEY:Path of the Zealot ~ Warrior of the Gods	DESC:Pool %1d12.|BarbarianWarriorOfTheGods			DEFINE:BarbarianWarriorOfTheGods|0					BONUS:VAR|BarbarianWarriorOfTheGods|4+1*((BarbarianLVL>=6)+(BarbarianLVL>=12)+(BarbarianLVL>=17))																	SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f4b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Fanatical Focus	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Zealot.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Once per active Rage, if you fail a saving throw, you can reroll it with a bonus equal to your Rage Damage bonus, and you must use the new roll.	KEY:Path of the Zealot ~ Fanatical Focus																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f4c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Zealous Presence	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Zealot.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you unleash a battle cry infused with divine energy. Up to ten other creatures of your choice within 60 feet of you gain Advantage on attack rolls and saving throws until the start of your next turn. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest unless you expend a use of your Rage (no action required) to restore your use of it.	KEY:Path of the Zealot ~ Zealous Presence																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f4d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Rage of the Gods	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Barbarian Class Feature.Class Feature.Path of the Zealot.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you activate your Rage, you can assume the form of a divine warrior. This form lasts for 1 minute or until you drop to 0 Hit Points. Once you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest. While in this form, you gain the benefits below. &nl; Flight. You have a Fly Speed equal to your Speed and can hover. &nl; Resistance. You have Resistance to Necrotic, Psychic, and Radiant damage. &nl; Revivification. When a creature within 30 feet of you would drop to 0 Hit Points, you can take a Reaction to expend a use of your Rage to instead change the target's Hit Points to a number equal to your Barbarian level.	KEY:Path of the Zealot ~ Rage of the Gods																										SORTKEY:Class_Barbarian_01f4e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block:Abilities																																
Bardic Inspiration	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can supernaturally inspire others through words, music, or dance. This inspiration is represented by your Bardic Inspiration die, which is a d%1. &nl; Using Bardic Inspiration. As a Bonus Action, you can inspire another creature within 60 feet of yourself who can see or hear you. That creature gains one of your Bardic Inspiration dice. A creature can have only one Bardic Inspiration die at a time. Once within the next hour when the creature fails a D20 Test, the creature can roll the Bardic Inspiration die and add the number rolled to the d20, potentially turning the failure into a success. A Bardic Inspiration die is expended when it's rolled. &nl; Number of Uses. You can confer a Bardic Inspiration die a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of once, %2), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; At Higher Levels. Your Bardic Inspiration die changes when you reach certain Bard levels, as shown in the Bardic Die column of the Bard Features table. The die becomes a d8 at level 5, a dlO at level 10, and a dl2 at level 15.|BardInspirationDice|max(1,CHA)	KEY:Bard ~ Bardic Inspiration				DEFINE:BardInspirationDice|0					BONUS:VAR|BardInspirationDice|6+(BardLVL>=5)*2+(BardLVL>=10)*2+(BardLVL>=15)*2																	SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Spellcasting	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have learned to cast spells through your bardic arts. See chapter 7 for the rules on spellcasting. The information below details how you use those rules with Bard spells, which appear in the Bard spell list later in the class's description. &nl; Cantrips. You know two cantrips of your choice from the Bard spell list. Dancing Lights and Vicious Mockery are recommended. Whenever you gain a Bard level, you can replace one of your cantrips with another cantrip of your choice from the Bard spell list. When you reach Bard levels 4 and 10, you learn another cantrip of your choice from the Bard spell list, as shown in the Cantrips column of the Bard Features table. &nl; Spell Slots. The Bard Features table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your level 1+ spells. You regain all expended slots when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; Prepared Spells of Level 1+. You prepare the list of level 1+ spells that are available for you to cast with this feature. To start, choose four level 1 spells from the Bard spell list. Charm Person, Color Spray, Dissonant Whispers, and Healing Word are recommended. Spell save DC %1; Spell attack modifier +%2. &nl; The number of spells on your list increases as you gain Bard levels, as shown in the Prepared Spells column of the Bard Features table. Whenever that number increases, choose additional spells from the Bard spell list until the number of spells on your list matches the number on the table. The chosen spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots. For example, if you're a level 3 Bard, your list of prepared spells can include six spells of levels 1 and 2 in any combination. If another Bard feature gives you spells that you always have prepared, those spells don't count against the number of spells you can prepare with this feature, but those spells otherwise count as Bard spells for you. &nl; Changing Your Prepared Spells. Whenever you gain a Bard level, you can replace one spell on your list with another Bard spell for which you have spell slots. &nl; Spellcasting Ability. Charisma is your spellcasting ability for your Bard spells. &nl; Spellcasting Focus. You can use a Musical Instrument as a Spellcasting Focus for your Bard spells.|BardSpellDC|Proficiency_Bonus+CHA	KEY:Bard ~ Spellcasting				DEFINE:BardSpellDC|0					BONUS:VAR|BardSpellDC|SpellDC_CHA	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Bard_Cantrip|2+(BardLVL>=4)+(BardLVL>=10)																SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Expertise	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain Expertise (see the rules glossary) in two of your skill proficiencies of your choice. Performance and Persuasion are recommended if you have proficiency in them. At Bard level 9, you gain Expertise in two more of your skill proficiencies of your choice.	KEY:Bard ~ Expertise									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Expertise|2*((BardLVL>=2)+(BardLVL>=9))																	SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Jack of All Trades	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:DESC:You can add half your Proficiency Bonus (round down) to any ability check you make that uses a skill proficiency you lack and that doesn't otherwise use your Proficiency Bonus. For example, if you make a Strength (Athletics) check and lack Athletics proficiency, you can add half your Proficiency Bonus to the check.	KEY:Bard ~ Jack of All Trades																										SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Bard Subclass	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a Bard subclass of your choice. The College of Dance, College of Glamour, College of Lore, and College of Valor subclasses are detailed after this class's description. A subclass is a specialization that grants you features at certain Bard levels. For the rest of your career, you gain each of your subclass's features that are of your Bard level or lower.	KEY:Bard ~ Bard Subclass									BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Bard Subclass|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ability Score Improvement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the Ability Score Improvement feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. You gain this feature again at Bard levels 8,12, and 16.	KEY:Bard ~ Ability Score Improvement									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Feat|1*((BardLVL>=4)+(BardLVL>=8)+(BardLVL>=12)+(BardLVL>=16))																	SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Font of Inspiration	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You now regain all your expended uses of Bardic Inspiration when you finish a Short or Long Rest. In addition, you can expend a spell slot (no action required) to regain one expended use of Bardic Inspiration.	KEY:Bard ~ Font of Inspiration																										SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01g	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Countercharm	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can use musical notes or words of power to disrupt mind-influencing effects. If you or a creature within 30 feet of you fails a saving throw against an effect that applies the Charmed or Frightened condition, you can take a Reaction to cause the save to be rerolled, and the new roll has Advantage.	KEY:Bard ~ Countercharm																										SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01h	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Magical Secrets	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You've learned secrets from various magical traditions. Whenever you reach a Bard level (including this level) and the Prepared Spells number in the Bard Features table increases, you can choose any of your new prepared spells from the Bard, Cleric, Druid, and Wizard spell lists, and the chosen spells count as Bard spells for you (see a class's section for its spell list). In addition, whenever you replace a spell prepared for this class, you can replace it with a spell from those lists.	KEY:Bard ~ Magical Secrets									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Bard_Magical_Secrets|1*((BardLVL>=11)+(BardLVL>=13)+(BardLVL>=15)+(BardLVL>=17)+(BardLVL>=18)+(BardLVL>=19)+(BardLVL>=20))																	SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01i	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Superior Inspiration	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you roll Initiative, you regain expended uses of Bardic Inspiration until you have two if you have fewer than that.	KEY:Bard ~ Superior Inspiration																										SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01j	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Epic Boon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain an Epic Boon feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. Boon of Spell Recall is recommended.	KEY:Bard ~ Epic Boon									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Epic_Boon|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01k	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Words of Creation	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have mastered two of the Words of Creation: the words of life and death. You therefore always have the Power Word Heal and Power Word Kill spells prepared. When you cast either spell, you can target a second creature with it if that creature is within 10 feet of the first target.	KEY:Bard ~ Words of Creation																		SPELLS:Words of Creation|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=BardLVL|Power Word Heal,BardSpellDC|Power Word Kill,SpellDC_CHA								SORTKEY:Class_Bard_01l	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
