CATEGORY=Special Ability|Druid ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:DruidPreparedSlots|0	BONUS:SPELLCAST|CLASS=Druid;LEVEL=10|DruidPreparedSlots	BONUS:VAR|DruidPreparedSlots|DruidPreparedBase																													
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Druid ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:DruidPreparedBase|0	BONUS:VAR|DruidPreparedBase|3+DruidLVL+(DruidLVL>=6)+(DruidLVL>=9)-(DruidLVL>=12)-(DruidLVL>=14)-(DruidLVL>=16)																														
																																
### Druid Cantrips																																
Druidcraft	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip		DESC:Whispering to the spirits of nature, you create one of the following effects within range:&nl;- You create a tiny, harmless sensory effect that predicts what the weather will be at your location for the next 24 hours. The effect might manifest as a golden orb for clear skies, a cloud for rain, falling snowflakes for snow, and so on. This effect persists for 1 round.&nl;- You instantly make a flower blossom, a seed pod open, or a leaf bud bloom.&nl;- You create an instantaneous, harmless sensor effect, such as falling leaves, a puff of wind, the sound of a small animal, or the faint odor of skunk. The effect must fit in a 5-foot cube.&nl;- You instantly light or snuff out a candle, a torch, or a small campfire.	KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Druidcraft																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Druidcraft,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Druidcraft								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Elementalism	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip			KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Elementalism																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Elementalism,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Elementalism								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Guidance	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip		DESC:You touch one willing creature. Once before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one ability check of its choice. It can roll the die before or after making the ability check. The spell then ends.	KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Guidance																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Guidance,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Guidance								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Mending	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip		DESC:This spell repairs a single break or tear in an object you touch, such as a broken chain link, two halves of a broken key, a torn cloak, or a leaking wineskin. As long as the break or tear is no larger than 1 foot in any dimension, you mend it. leaving no trace of the former damage. This spell can physically repair a magic item or construct, but the spell can't restore magic to such an object.	KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Mending																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mending,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Mending								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Message	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip		DESC:You point your finger toward a creature within range and whisper a message. The target (and only the target) hears the message and can reply in a whisper that only you can hear. You can cast this spell through solid objects if you are familiar with the target and know it is beyond the barrier. Magical silence. 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood blocks the spell. The spell doesn't have to follow a straight line and can travel freely around corners or through openings.	KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Message																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Message,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Message								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Poison Spray	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip		DESC:You extend your hand toward a creature you can see within range and project a puff of noxious gas from your palm. The creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take 1d12 poison damage. This spell's damage increases by 1d12 when you reach 5th level (2d12), 11th level (3d12), and 17th level (4d12).	KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Poison Spray																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Poison Spray,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Poison Spray								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Produce Flame	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip		DESC:A flicking flame appears in our hand. The flame remains there for the duration and harms neither you nor your equipment. The flame sheds bright light in a 10-foot radius and dim light for an additional 10 feet. The spell ends if you dismiss it as an action or if you cast it again.&nl;You can also attack with the flame, although doing so ends the spell. When you cast this spell, or as an action on a later turn, you can hurl the flame at a creature within 30 feet of you. Make a ranged spell attack. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 fire damage.&nl;This spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).	KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Produce Flame																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Produce Flame,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Produce Flame								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Resistance	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip		DESC:You touch one willing creature. Once before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one saving throw of its choice. It can roll the die before or after making the saving throw. The spell then ends.	KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Resistance																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Resistance,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Resistance								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Shillelagh	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip		DESC:The wood of a club or quarterstaff you are holding is imbued with nature's power. For the duration, you can use your spellcasting ability instead of Streangth for the attack and damage rolls of melee attacks using that weapon, and the weapon's damage die becomes a d8. The weapon also becomes magical, if it isn't already. The spell ends if you cast it again or if you let go of the weapon.	KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Shillelagh																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Shillelagh,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Shillelagh								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Spare the Dying	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip		DESC:You touch a living creature that has 0 hit points. The creature becomes stable. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.	KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Spare the Dying																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Spare the Dying,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Spare the Dying								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Starry Wisp	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip			KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Starry Wisp																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Starry Wisp,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Starry Wisp								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Thunderclap	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip			KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Thunderclap																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Thunderclap,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Thunderclap								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Thorn Whip	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Druid Cantrip		DESC:You create a long, vine-like whip covered in thorns that lashes out at your command toward a creature in range. Make a melee spell attack against the target. If the attack hits, the creature takes 1d6 piercing damage, and if the creature is Large or smaller, you pull the creature up to 10 feet closer to you.&nl;This spell's damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th elvel (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).	KEY:Druid Cantrip ~ Thorn Whip																		SPELLS:Druid Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Thorn Whip,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Thorn Whip								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block:Druid Subclass																																
Circle of the Land	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Druid Subclass.SpecialQuality.Nature Domain	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The Circle of the Land comprises mystics and sages who safeguard ancient knowledge and rites. These Druids meet within sacred circles of trees or standing stones to whisper primal secrets in Druidic. The circle's wisest members preside as the chief priests of their communities.	KEY:Druid Subclass ~ Circle of the Land																		ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Land ~ Circle of the Land Spells|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,3	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Land ~ Land's Aid|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,3	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Land ~ Natural Recovery|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,6	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Land ~ Nature's Ward|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,10	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Land ~ Nature's Sanctuary|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,14				SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Circle of the Moon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Druid Subclass.SpecialQuality.Nature Domain	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Druids of the Circle of the Moon draw on lunar magic to transform themselves. Their order gathers under the moon to share news and perform rituals. Changeable as the moon, a Druid of this circle might prowl as a great cat one night, soar over the treetops as an eagle the next day, and then crash through undergrowth as a bear to drive off a trespassing monster. The wild is in the Druid's blood.	KEY:Druid Subclass ~ Circle of the Moon																		ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Moon ~ Circle Forms|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,3	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Moon ~ Circle of the Moon Spells|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,3	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Moon ~ Improved Circle Forms|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,6	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Moon ~ Moonlight Step|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,10	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Moon ~ Lunar Form|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,14				SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Circle of the Sea	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Druid Subclass.SpecialQuality.Nature Domain	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Druids of the Circle of the Sea draw on the tempestuous forces of oceans and storms. Some view themselves as embodiments of nature's wrath, seeking vengeance against those who despoil nature. Others seek mystical unity with nature by attuning themselves to the ebb and flow of the tides, following the rush of currents and waves and listening to the inscrutable whispers and roars of the winds.	KEY:Druid Subclass ~ Circle of the Sea																		ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Sea ~ Circle of the Sea Spells|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,3	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Sea ~ Wrath of the Sea|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,3	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Sea ~ Aquatic Affinity|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,6	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Sea ~ Stormborn|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,10	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Sea ~ Oceanic Gift|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,14				SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Circle of the Stars	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Druid Subclass.SpecialQuality.Nature Domain	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The Circle of the Stars has tracked heavenly patterns since time immemorial, discovering secrets hidden amid the constellations. By understanding these secrets, the Druids of this circle seek to harness the powers of the cosmos.	KEY:Druid Subclass ~ Circle of the Stars																		ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Stars ~ Star Map|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,3	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Stars ~ Starry Form|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,3	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Stars ~ Cosmic Omen|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,6	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Stars ~ Twinkling Constellations|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,10	ABILITY:Druid Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Circle of the Stars ~ Full of Stars|PREVAREQ:DruidLVL,14				SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Circle of the Land Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever you finish a Long Rest, choose one type of land: arid, polar, temperate, or tropical. Consult the table below that corresponds to the chosen type; you have the spells listed for your Druid level and lower prepared.	KEY:Circle of the Land ~ Circle of the Land Spells									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Circle_Of_The_Land_Spell|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f1a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Land's Aid	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Magic action, you can expend a use of your Wild Shape and choose a point within 60 feet of yourself. Vitality-giving flowers and life-draining thorns appear for a moment in a 10-foot-radius Sphere centered on that point. Each creature of your choice in the Sphere must make a Constitution saving throw against your spell save DC, taking 2d6 Necrotic damage on a failed save or half as much damage on a successful one. One creature of your choice in that area regains 2d6 Hit Points. The damage and healing increase by 1d6 when you reach Druid levels 10 (3d6) and 14 (4d6).	KEY:Circle of the Land ~ Land's Aid																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f1b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Natural Recovery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast one of the level 1+ spells that you have prepared from your Circle Spells feature without expending a spell slot, and you must finish a Long Rest before you do so again. In addition, when you finish a Short Rest, you can choose expended spell slots to recover. The spell slots can have a combined level that is equal to or less than half your Druid level (round up), and none of them can be level 6+. For example, if you're a level 6 Druid, you can recover up to three levels' worth of spell slots. You can recover a level 3 spell slot, a level 2 and a level 1 spell slot, or three level 1 spell slots. Once you recover spell slots with this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Circle of the Land ~ Natural Recovery																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f1c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Nature's Ward	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You are immune to the Poisoned condition, and you have Resistance to a damage type associated with your current land choice in the Circle Spells feature, as shown in the Nature's Ward table.	KEY:Circle of the Land ~ Nature's Ward																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f1d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Nature's Sanctuary	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Magic action, you can expend a use of your Wild Shape and cause spectral trees and vines to appear in a 15-foot Cube on the ground within 120 feet of yourself. They last there for 1 minute or until you have the Incapacitated condition or die. You and your allies have Half Cover while in that area, and your allies gain the current Resistance of your Nature's Ward while there. As a Bonus Action, you can move the Cube up to 60 feet to ground within 120 feet of yourself.	KEY:Circle of the Land ~ Nature's Sanctuary																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f1e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Arid Land	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Circle of the Land Spells	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Arid lands.	KEY:Circle of the Land ~ Circle of the Land Spells ~ Arid Land														SPELLS:Arid Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Blur|Burning Hands|Fire Bolt|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,3	SPELLS:Arid Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Fireball,SpellDC_WIS|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,5	SPELLS:Arid Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Blight|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,7	SPELLS:Arid Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Wall of Stone|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,9									SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f1a1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Polar Land	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Circle of the Land Spells	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Polar lands.	KEY:Circle of the Land ~ Circle of the Land Spells ~ Polar Land														SPELLS:Polar Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Fog Cloud|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,3	SPELLS:Polar Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Daylight|Sleet Storm|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,5	SPELLS:Polar Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Ice Storm|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,7	SPELLS:Polar Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Cone of Cold|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,9									SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f1a2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Temperate Land	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Circle of the Land Spells	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Temperate lands.	KEY:Circle of the Land ~ Circle of the Land Spells ~ Temperate Land														SPELLS:Temperate Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Misty Step|Shocking Grasp|Sleep|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,3	SPELLS:Temperate Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Lightning Bolt|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,5	SPELLS:Temperate Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Freedom of Movement|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,7	SPELLS:Temperate Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Tree Stride|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,9									SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f1a3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Tropical Land	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Circle of the Land Spells	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Tropical lands.	KEY:Circle of the Land ~ Circle of the Land Spells ~ Tropical Land														SPELLS:Tropical Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Acid Splash|Ray of Sickness|Web|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,3	SPELLS:Tropical Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Stinking Cloud|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,5	SPELLS:Tropical Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Polymorph|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,7	SPELLS:Tropical Land Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Insect Plague|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,9									SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f1a4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Circle Forms	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Moon.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can channel lunar magic when you assume a Wild Shape form, granting you the benefits below. Challenge Rating. The maximum Challenge Rating for the form equals your Druid level divided by 3 (round down). &nl; Armor Class. Until you leave the form, your AC equals 13 plus your Wisdom modifier if that total is higher than the Beast's AC. &nl; Temporary Hit Points. You gain a number of Temporary Hit Points equal to three times your Druid level.	KEY:Circle of the Moon ~ Circle Forms																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f2a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Circle of the Moon Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you reach a Druid level specified in the Circle of the Moon Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared. In addition, you can cast the spells from this feature while you're in a Wild Shape form.	KEY:Circle of the Moon ~ Circle of the Moon Spells														SPELLS:Circle of the Moon Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Cure Wounds|Moonbeam|Starry Wisp|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,3	SPELLS:Circle of the Moon Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Conjure Animals|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,5	SPELLS:Circle of the Moon Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Fount of Moonlight|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,7	SPELLS:Circle of the Moon Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Mass Cure Wounds|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,9									SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f2b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Improved Circle Forms	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:While in a Wild Shape form, you gain the following benefits. &nl; Lunar Radiance. Each of your attacks in a Wild Shape form can deal its normal damage type or Radiant damage. You make this choice each time you hit with those attacks. &nl; Increased Toughness. You can add your Wisdom modifier to your Constitution saving throws.	KEY:Circle of the Moon ~ Improved Circle Forms																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f2c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Moonlight Step	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You magically transport yourself, reappearing amid a burst of moonlight. As a Bonus Action, you teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see, and you have Advantage on the next attack roll you make before the end of this turn. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. You can also regain uses by expending a level 2+ spell slot for each use you want to restore (no action required).	KEY:Circle of the Moon ~ Moonlight Step	DESC:%1 times.|MoonlightStepTimes			DEFINE:MoonlightStepTimes|0					BONUS:VAR|MoonlightStepTimes|max(1,WIS)																	SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f2d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Lunar Form	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The power of the moon suffuses you, granting you the following benefits. &nl; Improved Lunar Radiance. Once per turn, you can deal an extra 2dl0 Radiant damage to a target you hit with a Wild Shape form's attack. &nl; Shared Moonlight. Whenever you use Moonlight Step, you can also teleport one willing creature. That creature must be within 10 feet of you, and you teleport it to an unoccupied space you can see within 10 feet of your destination space.	KEY:Circle of the Moon ~ Lunar Form																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f2e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Circle of the Sea Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you reach a Druid level specified in the Circle of the Sea Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Circle of the Sea ~ Circle of the Sea Spells														SPELLS:Circle of the Sea Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Fog Cloud|Gust of Wind|Ray of Frost|Shatter|Thunderwave|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,3	SPELLS:Circle of the Sea Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Lightning Bolt|Water Breathing|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,5	SPELLS:Circle of the Sea Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Control Water|Ice Storm|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,7	SPELLS:Circle of the Sea Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=DruidLVL|Conjure Elemental|Hold Monster|PREVARGTEQ:DruidLVL,9									SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f3a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Wrath of the Sea	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can expend a use of your Wild Shape to manifest a 5-foot Emanation that takes the form of ocean spray that surrounds you for 10 minutes. It ends early if you dismiss it (no action required), manifest it again, or have the Incapacitated Condition. When you manifest the Emanation and as a Bonus Action on your subsequent turns, you can choose another creature you can see in the Emanation. The target must succeed on a Constitution saving throw against your spell save DC or take Cold damage and, if the creature is Large or smaller, be pushed up to 15 feet away from you. To determine this damage, roll a number of d6s equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of one die).	KEY:Circle of the Sea ~ Wrath of the Sea																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f3b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Aqatic Affinity	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The size of the Emanation created by your Wrath of the Sea increases to 10 feet. In addition, you gain a Swim Speed equal to your Speed.	KEY:Circle of the Sea ~ Aquatic Affinity																		MOVECLONE:Walk,Swim,*1								SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f3c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Stormborn	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your Wrath of the Sea confers two more benefits while active, as detailed below. &nl; Flight. You gain a Fly Speed equal to your Speed. &nl; Resistance. You have Resistance to Cold, Lightning, and Thunder damage.	KEY:Circle of the Sea ~ Stormborn																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f3d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Oceanic Gift	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Land.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Instead of manifesting the Emanation of Wrath of the Sea around yourself, you can manifest it around one willing creature within 60 feet of yourself. That creature gains all the benefits of the Emanation and uses your spell save DC and Wisdom modifier for it. In addition, you can manifest the Emanation around both the other creature and yourself if you expend two uses of your Wild Shape instead of one when manifesting it.	KEY:Circle of the Sea ~ Oceanic Gift																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f3e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Star Map	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Star.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You've created a star chart as part of your heavenly studies. It is a Tiny object, and you can use it as a Spellcasting Focus for your Druid spells. You determine its form by rolling on the Star Map table or by choosing one. While holding the map, you have the Guidance and Guiding Bolt spells prepared, and you can cast Guiding Bolt without expending a spell slot. You can cast it in that way a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. If you lose the map, you can perform a 1-hour ceremony to magically create a replacement. This ceremony can be performed during a Short or Long Rest, and it destroys the previous map.	KEY:Circle of the Stars ~ Star Map																		SPELLS:Star Map|TIMES=max(1,WIS)|CASTERLEVEL=BardLVL|Guidance|Guiding Bolt	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Druid=0|Guidance,Guiding Bolt							SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f4a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Starry Form	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Star.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can expend a use of your Wild Shape feature to take on a starry form rather than shape-shifting. While in your starry form, you retain your game statistics, but your body becomes luminous, your joints glimmer like stars, and glowing lines connect them as on a star chart. This form sheds Bright Light in a 10-foot radius and Dim Light for an additional 10 feet. The form lasts for 10 minutes. It ends early if you dismiss it (no action required), have the Incapacitated condition, or use this feature again. Whenever you assume your starry form, choose which of the following constellations glimmers on your body; your choice gives you certain benefits while in the form. &nl; Archer. A constellation of an archer appears on you. When you activate this form and as a Bonus Action on your subsequent turns while it lasts, you can make a ranged spell attack, hurling a luminous arrow that targets one creature within 60 feet of yourself. On a hit, the attack deals Radiant damage equal to ld8 plus your Wisdom modifier. &nl; Chalice. A constellation of a life-giving goblet appears on you. Whenever you cast a spell using a spell slot that restores Hit Points to a creature, you or another creature within 30 feet of you can regain Hit Points equal to ld8 plus your Wisdom Modifier. &nl; Dragon. A constellation of a wise dragon appears on you. When you make an Intelligence or a Wisdom check or a Constitution saving throw to maintain Concentration, you can treat a roll of 9 or lower on the d20 as a 10.	KEY:Circle of the Stars ~ Starry Form																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f4b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Cosmic Omen	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Star.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can consult your Star Map for omens and roll a die. Until you finish your next Long Rest, you gain access to a special Reaction based on whether you rolled an even or an odd number on the die: &nl; Weal (Even). Whenever a creature you can see within 30 feet of you is about to make a D20 Test, you can take a Reaction to roll ld6 and add the number rolled to the total. &nl; Woe (Odd). Whenever a creature you can see within 30 feet of you is about to make a D20 Test, you can take a Reaction to roll ld6 and subtract the number rolled from the total. &nl; You can use this Reaction a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Circle of the Stars ~ Cosmic Omen																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f4c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Twinkling Constellations	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Star.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The constellations of your Starry Form improve. The ld8 of the Archer and the Chalice becomes 2d8, and while the Dragon is active, you have a Fly Speed of 20 feet and can hover. Moreover, at the start of each of your turns while in your Starry Form, you can change which constellation glimmers on your body.	KEY:Circle of the Stars ~ Twinkling Constellations																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f4d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Full of Stars	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Druid Class Feature.Class Feature.Circle of the Star.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:While in your Starry Form, you become partially incorporeal, giving you Resistance to Bludgeoning, Piercing, and Slashing damage.	KEY:Circle of the Stars ~ Full of Stars																										SORTKEY:Class_Druid_01f4e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block:Abilities																																
Fighting Style	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have honed your martial prowess and gain a Fighting Style feat of your choice (see chapter 5). Defense is recommended. Whenever you gain a Fighter level, you can replace the feat you chose with a different Fighting Style feat.	KEY:Fighter ~ Fighting Style									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Fighting_Style|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Second Wind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have a limited well of physical and mental stamina that you can draw on. As a Bonus Action, you can use it to regain Hit Points equal to 1d10 plus your Fighter level. You can use this feature twice. You regain one expended use when you finish a Short Rest, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. When you reach certain Fighter levels, you gain more uses of this feature, as shown in the Second Wind column of the Fighter Features table.	KEY:Fighter ~ Second Wind	DESC:%1 uses.|SecondWindTimes			DEFINE:SecondWindTimes|0					BONUS:VAR|SecondWindTimes|2	BONUS:VAR|SecondWindTimes|1|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,4	BONUS:VAR|SecondWindTimes|1|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,10															SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Weapon Mastery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your training with weapons allows you to use the mastery properties of three kinds of Simple or Martial weapons of your choice. Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can practice weapon drills and change one of those weapon choices. When you reach certain Fighter levels, you gain the ability to use the mastery properties of more kinds of weapons, as shown in the Weapon Mastery column of the Fighter Features table.	KEY:Fighter ~ Weapon Mastery	DESC:%1 weapon mastery.|WeaponMastery			DEFINE:WeaponMastery|0					BONUS:VAR|POOL_Weapon_Mastery|WeaponMastery	BONUS:VAR|WeaponMastery|3+(FighterLVL>=4)+(FighterLVL>=10)+(FighterLVL>=16)																SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Action Surge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can push yourself beyond your normal limits for a moment. On your turn, you can take one additional action, except the Magic action. Once you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Short or Long Rest. Starting at level 17, you can use it twice before a rest but only once on a turn.	KEY:Fighter ~ Action Surge	DESC:%1 uses.|ActionSurgeTimes			DEFINE:ActionSurgeTimes|0					BONUS:VAR|ActionSurgeTimes|1	BONUS:VAR|ActionSurgeTimes|1|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,17																SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Tactical Mind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have a mind for tactics on and off the battlefield. When you fail an ability check, you can expend a use of your Second Wind to push yourself toward success. Rather than regaining Hit Points, you roll ldlO and add the number rolled to the ability check, potentially turning it into a success. If the check still fails, this use of Second Wind isn't expended.	KEY:Fighter ~ Tactical Mind																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Fighter Subclass	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a Fighter subclass of your choice. The Battle Master, Champion, Eldritch Knight, and Psi Warrior subclasses are detailed after this class's description. A subclass is a specialization that grants you features at certain Fighter levels. For the rest of your career, you gain each of your subclass's features that are of your Fighter level or lower.	KEY:Fighter ~ Fighter Subclass									BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Fighter Subclass|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ability Score Improvement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the Ability Score Improvement feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. You gain this feature again at Fighter levels 6, 8,12,14, and 16.	KEY:Fighter ~ Ability Score Improvement									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Feat|1*((FighterLVL>=4)+(FighterLVL>=8)+(FighterLVL>=12)+(FighterLVL>=16))																	SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01g	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Extra Attack	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can attack twice instead of once whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.	KEY:Fighter ~ Extra Attack																		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Extra Attack ~ 1								SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01h	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Tactical Shift	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever you activate your Second Wind with a Bonus Action, you can move up to half your Speed without provoking Opportunity Attacks.	KEY:Fighter ~ Tactical Shift																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01i	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Indomitable	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If you fail a saving throw, you can reroll it with a bonus equal to your Fighter level. You must use the new roll, and you can't use this feature again until you finish a Long Rest. You can use this feature twice before a Long Rest starting at level 13 and three times before a Long Rest starting at level 17.	KEY:Fighter ~ Indomitable	DESC:%1 uses.|IndomitableTimes			DEFINE:IndomitableTimes|0					BONUS:VAR|IndomitableTimes|1	BONUS:VAR|IndomitableTimes|1|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,13	BONUS:VAR|IndomitableTimes|1|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,17															SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01j	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Tactcal Master	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you attack with a weapon whose mastery property you can use, you can replace that property with the Push, Sap, or Slow property for that attack.	KEY:Fighter ~ Tactical Master																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01k	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Two Extra Attack	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can attack three times instead of once whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.	KEY:Fighter ~ Two Extra Attack																		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Extra Attack ~ 2								SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01l	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Studied Attack	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You study your opponents and learn from each attack you make. If you make an attack roll against a creature and miss, you have Advantage on your next attack roll against that creature before the end of your next turn.	KEY:Fighter ~ Studied Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01m	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Epic Boon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain an Epic Boon feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. Boon of Combat Prowess is recommended.	KEY:Fighter ~ Epic Boon									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Epic_Boon|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01n	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Three Extra Attack	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can attack four times instead of once whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.	KEY:Fighter ~ Three Extra Attack																		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Extra Attack ~ 3								SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01o	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																																																
###Block:Fighter Subclass																																
Battle Master	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Fighter Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Battle Masters are students of the art of battle, learning martial techniques passed down through generations. The most accomplished Battle Masters are well-rounded figures who combine their carefully honed combat skills with academic study in the fields of history, theory, and the arts.	KEY:Fighter Subclass ~ Battlemaster																		ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Battle Master ~ Combat Superiority|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,3	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Battle Master ~ Student of War|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,3	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Battle Master ~ Know Your Enemy|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,7	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Battle Master ~ Improved Combat Superiority|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,10	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Battle Master ~ Relentless|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,15	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Battle Master ~ Ultimate Combat Superiority|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,18			SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Champion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Fighter Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A Champion focuses on the development of martial prowess in a relentless pursuit of victory. Champions combine rigorous training with physical excellence to deal devastating blows, withstand peril, and garner glory. Whether in athletic contests or bloody battle, Champions strive for the crown of the victor.	KEY:Fighter Subclass ~ Champion																		ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Champion ~ Improved Critical|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,3	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Champion ~ Remarkable Athlete|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,3	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Champion ~ Additional Fighting Style|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,7	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Champion ~ Heroic Warrior|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,10	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Champion ~ Superior Critical|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,15	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Champion ~ Survivor|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,18			SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Eldritch Knight	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Fighter Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Eldritch Knights combine the martial mastery common to all Fighters with a careful study of magic. Their spells both complement and extend their combat skills, providing additional protection to shore up their armor and also allowing them to engage many foes at once with explosive magic.	KEY:Fighter Subclass ~ Eldritch Knight																		ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Eldritch Knight ~ Spellcasting|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,3	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Eldritch Knight ~ War Bond|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,3	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Eldritch Knight ~ War Magic|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,7	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Eldritch Knight ~ Eldritch Strike|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,10	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Eldritch Knight ~ Arcane Charge|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,15	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Eldritch Knight ~ Improved War Magic|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,18			SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Psi Warrior	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Fighter Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Psi Warriors awaken the power of their minds to augment their physical might. They harness this psionic power to infuse their weapon strikes, lash out with telekinetic energy, and create barriers of mental force.	KEY:Fighter Subclass ~ Psi Warrior																		ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Psi Warrior ~ Psionic Power|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,3		ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Psi Warrior ~ Telekinetic Adept|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,7	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Psi Warrior ~ Guarded Mind|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,10	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Psi Warrior ~ Bulwark of Force|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,15	ABILITY:Fighter Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Psi Warrior ~ Telekinetic Master|PREVAREQ:FighterLVL,18			SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Combat Superiority	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Battle Master.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your experience on the battlefield has refined your fighting techniques. You learn maneuvers that are fueled by special dice called Superiority Dice. &nl; Maneuvers. You learn three maneuvers of your choice from the "Maneuver Options" section later in this subclass's description. Many maneuvers enhance an attack in some way. You can use only one maneuver per attack. You learn two additional maneuvers of your choice when you reach Fighter levels 7,10, and 15. Each time you learn new maneuvers, you can also replace one maneuver you know with a different One. &nl; Superiority Dice. You have four Superiority Dice, which are d8s. A Superiority Die is expended when you use it. You regain all expended Superiority Dice when you finish a Short or Long Rest. You gain an additional Superiority Die when you reach Fighter levels 7 (five dice total) and 15 (six dice total). &nl; Saving Throws. If a maneuver requires a saving throw, the DC equals 8 plus your Strength or Dexterity modifier (your choice) and Proficiency Bonus.	KEY:Battle Master ~ Combat Superiority	DESC: Superiority Dice: %1.|SuperiorityDice			DEFINE:ManeuversDC|0	DEFINE:SuperiorityDice|0				BONUS:VAR|ManeuversDC|8+max(STR,DEX)+ProficiencyBonus	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Maneuvers|3+2*(FighterLVL>=7+FighterLVL>=10+FighterLVL>=15)	BONUS:VAR|SuperiorityDice|4+1*(FighterLVL>=7+FighterLVL>=15)															SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Student of War	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Battle Master.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain proficiency with one type of Artisan's Tools of your choice, and you gain proficiency in one skill of your choice from the skills available to Fighters at level 1.	KEY:Battle Master ~ Student of War									BONUS:VAR|Tool Proficiency|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Fighter_Skill|1																SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Know Your Enemy	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Battle Master.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can discern certain strengths and weaknesses of a creature you can see within 30 feet of yourself; you know whether that creature has any Immunities, Resistances, or Vulnerabilities, and if the creature has any, you know what they are. Once you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also restore a use of the feature by expending one Superiority Die (no action required).	KEY:Battle Master ~ Know your Enemy																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Improved Combat Superiority	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Battle Master.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your Superiority Die becomes a d10.	KEY:Battle Master ~ Improved Combat Superiority																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Relentless	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Battle Master.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Once per turn, when you use a maneuver, you can roll 1d8 and use the number rolled instead of expending a Superiority Die.	KEY:Battle Master ~ Relentless																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ultimate Combat Superiority	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Battle Master.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your Superiority Die becomes a d12.	KEY:Battle Master ~ Ultimate Combat Superiority																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Improved Critical	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Champion.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your attack rolls with weapons and Unarmed Strikes can score a Critical Hit on a roll of 19 or 20 on the d20.	KEY:Champion ~ Improved Critical									BONUS:WEAPONPROF=TYPE.Weapon|CRITRANGEADD|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f2a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Remarkable Athlete	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Champion.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Thanks to your athleticism, you have Advantage on Initiative rolls and Strength (Athletics) checks. In addition, immediately after you score a Critical Hit, you can move up to half your Speed without provoking Opportunity Attacks.	KEY:Champion ~ Remarkable Athlete																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f2b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Additional Fighting Style	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Champion.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain another Fighting Style feat of your choice.	KEY:Champion ~ Additional fighting Style																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f2c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Heroic Warrior	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Champion.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The thrill of battle drives you toward victory. During combat, you can give yourself Heroic Inspiration whenever you start your turn without it.	KEY:Champion ~ Heroic Warrior																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f2d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Superior Critical	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Champion.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your attack rolls with weapons and Unarmed Strikes can now score a Critical Hit on a roll of 18-20 on the d20.	KEY:Champion ~ Superior Critical									BONUS:WEAPONPROF=TYPE.Weapon|CRITRANGEADD|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f2e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Survivor	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Champion.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You attain the pinnacle of resilience in battle, giving you these benefits. &nl; Defy Death. You have Advantage on Death Saving Throws. Moreover, when you roll 18-20 on a Death Saving Throw, you gain the benefit of rolling a 20 on it. &bl; Heroic Rally. At the start of each of your turns, you regain Hit Points equal to 5 plus your Constitution modifier if you are Bloodied and have at least 1 Hit Point.	KEY:Champion ~ Survivor																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f2f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Spellcasting	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Eldritch Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have learned to cast spells. See chapter 7 for the rules on spellcasting. The information below details how you use those rules as an Eldritch Knight. &nl; Cantrips. You know two cantrips of your choice from the Wizard spell list (see that class0's section for its list). Ray of Frost and Shocking Grasp are recommended. Whenever you gain a Fighter level, you can replace one of these cantrips with another cantrip of your choice from the Wizard spell list. When you reach Fighter level 10, you learn another Wizard cantrip of your choice. &nl; Spell Slots. The Eldritch Knight Spellcasting table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your level 1+ spells. You regain all expended slots when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; Prepared Spells of Level 1+. You prepare the list of level 1+ spells that are available for you to cast with this feature. To start, choose three level 1 spells from the Wizard spell list. Burning Hands, Jump, and Shield are recommended. The number of spells on your list increases as you gain Fighter levels, as shown in the Prepared Spells column of the Eldritch Knight Spellcasting table. Whenever that number increases, choose additional spells from the Wizard spell list until the number of spells on your list matches the number on the table. The chosen spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots. For example, if you're a level 7 Fighter, your list of prepared spells can include five Wizard spells of levels 1 and 2 in any combination. &nl; Changing Your Prepared Spells. Whenever you gain a Fighter level, you can replace one spell on your list with another Wizard spell for which you have spell slots. &nl; Spellcasting Ability. Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for your Wizard spells. &nl; Spellcasting Focus. You can use an Arcane Focus as a Spellcasting Focus for your Wizard spells. Spell save DC %1; Spell attack modifier +%2|8+Proficiency_Bonus+INT|Proficiency_Bonus+INT	KEY:Eldritch Knight ~ Spellcasting				DEFINE:POOL_Eldritch_Knight_Cantrip|0					BONUS:VAR|POOL_Eldritch_Knight_Cantrip|2+(FighterLVL>=10)																	SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f3a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
War Bond	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Eldritch Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You learn a ritual that creates a magical bond between yourself and one weapon. You perform the ritual over the course of 1 hour, which can be done during a Short Rest. The weapon must be within your reach throughout the ritual, at the conclusion of which you touch the weapon and forge the bond. The bond fails if another Fighter is bonded to the weapon or if the weapon is a magic item to which someone else is attuned. Once you have bonded a weapon to yourself, you can't be disarmed of that weapon unless you have the Incapacitated condition. If it is on the same plane of existence, you can summon that weapon as a Bonus Action, causing it to teleport instantly to your hand. You can have up to two bonded weapons, but you can summon only one at a time with a Bonus Action. If you attempt to bond with a third weapon, you must break the bond with one of the other two.	KEY:Eldritch Knight ~ War Bond																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f3b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
War Magic	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Eldritch Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you take the Attack action on your turn, you can replace one of the attacks with a casting of one of your Wizard cantrips that has a casting time of an action.	KEY:Eldritch Knight ~ War Magic																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f3c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Eldritch Strike	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Eldritch Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You learn how to make your weapon strikes undercut a creature's ability to withstand your spells. When you hit a creature with an attack using a weapon, that creature has Disadvantage on the next saving throw it makes against a spell you cast before the end of your next turn.	KEY:Eldritch Knight ~ Eldritch Strike																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f3d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Arcane Charge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Eldritch Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you use your Action Surge, you can teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see. You can teleport before or after the additional action.	KEY:Eldritch Knight ~ Arcane Charge																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f3e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Improved War Magic	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Eldritch Knight.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you take the Attack action on your turn, you can replace two of the attacks with a casting of one of your level 1 or level 2 Wizard spells that has a casting time of an action.	KEY:Eldritch Knight ~ Improved War Magic																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f3f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Psionic Power	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Psi Warrior.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You harbor a wellspring of psionic energy within yourself. It is represented by your Psionic Energy Dice, which fuel powers you have from this subclass. The Psi Warrior Energy Dice table shows the die size and number of these dice you have when you reach certain Fighter levels. Any features in this subclass that use a Psionic Energy Die use only the dice from this subclass. Some of your powers expend the Psionic Energy Die, as specified in a power's description, and you can't use a power if it requires you to use a die when all your Psionic Energy Dice are expended. You regain one of your expended Psionic Energy Dice when you finish a Short Rest, and you regain all of them when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; Protective Field. When you or another creature you can see within 30 feet of you takes damage, you can take a Reaction to expend one Psionic Energy Die, roll the die, and reduce the damage taken by the number rolled plus your Intelligence modifier (minimum reduction of 1), as you create a momentary shield of telekinetic force. &nl; Psionic Strike. You can propel your weapons with psionic force. Once on each of your turns, immediately after you hit a target within 30 feet of yourself with an attack and deal damage to it with a weapon, you can expend one Psionic Energy Die, rolling it and dealing Force damage to the target equal to the number rolled plus your Intelligence modifier. &nl; Telekinetic Movement. You can move an object or a creature with your mind. As a Magic action, choose one target you can see within 30 feet of yourself; the target must be a loose object that is Large or smaller or one willing creature other than you. You transport the target up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see. Alternatively, if the target is a Tiny object, you can transport it to or from your hand. Once you take this action, you can't do so again until you finish a Short or Long Rest unless you expend a Psionic Energy Die (no action required) to restore your use of it.	KEY:Psi Warrior ~ Psionic Power	DESC: Energy Dice: %1d%2.|EnergyDice|EnergyDiceDie			DEFINE:EnergyDice|0	DEFINE:EnergyDiceDie|0				BONUS:VAR|EnergyDice|4|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,3	BONUS:VAR|EnergyDice|2|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,5	BONUS:VAR|EnergyDice|2|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,9	BONUS:VAR|EnergyDice|2|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,13	BONUS:VAR|EnergyDice|2|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,17	BONUS:VAR|EnergyDiceDie|6|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,3	BONUS:VAR|EnergyDiceDie|2|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,5	BONUS:VAR|EnergyDiceDie|2|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,11	BONUS:VAR|EnergyDiceDie|12|PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,17									SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f4a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Telekinetic Adept	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Psi Warrior.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have mastered new ways to use your telekinetic abilities, detailed below. &nl; Psi-Powered Leap. As a Bonus Action, you gain a Fly Speed equal to twice your Speed until the end of the current turn. Once you take this Bonus Action, you can't do so again until you finish a Short or Long Rest unless you expend a Psionic Energy Die (no action required) to restore your use of it. &nl; Telekinetic Thrust. When you deal damage to a target with your Psionic Strike, you can force the target to make a Strength saving throw (DC 8 plus your Intelligence modifier and Proficiency Bonus). On a failed save, you can give the target the Prone condition or transport it up to 10 feet horizontally.	KEY:Psi Warrior ~ Telekinetic Adept	DESC: Telekinetic Trust DC %1|8+INT+ProficiencyBonus																									SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f4b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Guarded Mind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Psi Warrior.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have Resistance to Psychic damage. Moreover, if you start your turn with the Charmed or Frightened condition, you can expend a Psionic Energy Die (no action required) and end every effect on yourself giving you those conditions.	KEY:Psi Warrior ~ Guarded Mind																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f4c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Bulwark of Force	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Psi Warrior.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can shield yourself and others with telekinetic force. As a Bonus Action, you can choose creatures, including yourself, within 30 feet of yourself, up to a number of creatures equal to your Intelligence modifier (minimum of one creature). Each of the chosen creatures has Half Cover for 1 minute or until you have the Incapacitated condition. Once you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest unless you expend a Psionic Energy Die (no action required) to restore your use of it.	KEY:Psi Warrior ~ Bulwark of Force																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f4d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Telekinetic Master	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Fighter Class Feature.Class Feature.Psi Warrior.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You always have the Telekinesis spell prepared. With this feature, you can cast it without a spell slot or components, and your spellcasting ability for it is Intelligence. On each of your turns while you maintain Concentration on it, including the turn when you cast it, you can make one attack with a weapon as a Bonus Action. Once you cast the spell with this feature, you can't do so in this way again until you finish a Long Rest unless you expend a Psionic Energy Die (no action required) to restore your use of it.	KEY:Psi Warrior ~ Telekinetic Master																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f4e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Eldritch Knight ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:FighterCast1|0	DEFINE:FighterKnown1|0	BONUS:VAR|FighterCast1|SpellSlotsLVL1																													
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Eldritch Knight ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:FighterCast2|0	DEFINE:FighterKnown2|0	BONUS:VAR|FighterCast2|SpellSlotsLVL2																													
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Eldritch Knight ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:FighterCast3|0	DEFINE:FighterKnown3|0	BONUS:VAR|FighterCast3|SpellSlotsLVL3																													
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Eldritch Knight ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:FighterCast4|0	DEFINE:FighterKnown4|0	BONUS:VAR|FighterCast4|SpellSlotsLVL4																													
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Eldritch Knight ~ Spellcasting.MOD	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Fighter Known Progression Selection|1																															
																																
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Eldritch Knight ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:FighterPreparedSlots|0	BONUS:SPELLCAST|CLASS=Fighter;LEVEL=10|FighterPreparedSlots	BONUS:VAR|FighterPreparedSlots|FighterPreparedBase																													
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Eldritch Knight ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:FighterPreparedBase|0	BONUS:VAR|FighterPreparedBase|2+FighterLVL-(FighterLVL>=5)-(FighterLVL>=6)-(FighterLVL>=9)-(FighterLVL>=12)-(FighterLVL>=15)-(FighterLVL>=17)-(FighterLVL>=18)																														
																																
###Block: Choose Fighter Known Progression																																
Grant Highest Known only	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Known Progression	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:This will manipulate your spells known to increase to the max highest allowed by the rules.	KEY:Fighter Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only																											
Follow Standard Progression	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Known Progression	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:This will follow the progression chart in the Player's Handbook.	KEY:Fighter Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression																											
Choose Own Progression	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Known Progression	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:This will force the user to select spells each level.	KEY:Fighter Known Progression ~ Choose Own Progression				BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Fighter Known|if(FighterLVL>=3,3,0)+(FighterLVL>=4)+(FighterLVL>=7)+(FighterLVL>=8)+(FighterLVL>=10)+(FighterLVL>=11)+(FighterLVL>=13)+(FighterLVL>=14)+(FighterLVL>=16)+(FighterLVL>=19)+(FighterLVL>=20)																							
#																																
# Grant Highest Known																																
CATEGORY=Internal|Fighter Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|FighterKnown1|if(FighterLVL>=3,2,0)+(FighterLVL>=4)-3*(FighterLVL>=7)																															
CATEGORY=Internal|Fighter Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|FighterKnown2|if(FighterLVL>=7,6,0)+(FighterLVL>=10)-3*(FighterLVL>=13)																															
CATEGORY=Internal|Fighter Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|FighterKnown3|if(FighterLVL>=13,9,0)+(FighterLVL>=16)-10*(FighterLVL>=19)																															
CATEGORY=Internal|Fighter Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|FighterKnown4|if(FighterLVL>=19,11,0)																															
#																																
# Follow Standard Progression																																
CATEGORY=Internal|Fighter Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|FighterKnown1|if(FighterLVL>=3,2,0)+(FighterLVL>=4)+(FighterLVL>=7)																															
CATEGORY=Internal|Fighter Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|FighterKnown2|if(FighterLVL>=7,2,0)+(FighterLVL>=10)																															
CATEGORY=Internal|Fighter Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|FighterKnown3|if(FighterLVL>=13,2,0)+(FighterLVL>=16)																															
CATEGORY=Internal|Fighter Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|FighterKnown4|(FighterLVL>=19)																															
#																																
# Choose Own Progression																																
Fighter Known Level 1	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Known	PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,3	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|FighterKnown1|1																									
Fighter Known Level 2	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Known	PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,7	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|FighterKnown2|1																									
Fighter Known Level 3	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Known	PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,13	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|FighterKnown3|1																									
Fighter Known Level 4	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Known	PREVARGTEQ:FighterLVL,19	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|FighterKnown4|1																									
																																
###Block: Maneuvers																																
Ambush	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you make a Dexterity (Stealth) check or an Initiative roll, you can expend one Superiority Die and add the die to the roll, unless you have the Incapacitated condition.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Ambush																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Bait and Switch	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you're within 5 feet of a creature on your turn, you can expend one Superiority Die and switch places with that creature, provided you spend at least 5 feet of movement and the creature is willing and doesn't have the Incapacitated condition. This movement doesn't provoke Opportunity Attacks. Roll the Superiority Die. Until the start of your next turn, you or the other creature (your choice) gains a bonus to AC equal to the number rolled.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Bait and Switch																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Commander Strike	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you take the Attack action on your turn, you can replace one of your attacks to direct one of your companions to strike. When you do so, choose a willing creature who can see or hear you and expend one Superiority Die. That creature can immediately use its Reaction to make one attack with a weapon or an Unarmed Strike, adding the Superiority Die to the attack's damage roll on a hit.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Commander Strike																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Commanding Presence	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you make a Charisma (Intimidation, Performance, or Persuasion) check, you can expend one Superiority Die and add that die to the roll.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Commanding Presence																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Disarming Attack	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you hit a creature with an attack roll, you can expend one Superiority Die to attempt to disarm the target. Add the Superiority Die roll to the attack's damage roll. The target must succeed on a Strength saving throw or drop one object of your choice that it's holding, with the object landing in its space.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Disarming Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a5	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Distracting Strike	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you hit a creature with an attack roll, you can expend one Superiority Die to distract the target. Add the Superiority Die roll to the attack's damage roll. The next attack roll against the target by an attacker other than you has Advantage if the attack is made before the start of your next turn.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Distracting Strike																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a6	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Evasive Footwork	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can expend one Superiority Die and take the Disengage action. You also roll the die and add the number rolled to your AC until the start of your next turn.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Evasive Footwork																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a7	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Feinting Attack	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can expend one Superiority Die to feint, choosing one creature within 5 feet of yourself as your target. You have Advantage on your next attack roll against that target this turn. If that attack hits, add the Superiority Die to the attack's damage roll.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Feinting Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a8	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Goading Attack	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you hit a creature with an attack roll, you can expend one Superiority Die to attempt to goad the target into attacking you. Add the Superiority Die to the attack's damage roll. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or have Disadvantage on attack rolls against targets other than you until the end of your next turn.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Goading Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a9	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Lunging Attack	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can expend one Superiority Die and take the Dash action. If you move at least 5 feet in a straight line immediately before hitting with a melee attack as part of the Attack action on this turn, you can add the Superiority Die to the attack's damage roll.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Lunging Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a10	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Maneuvering Attack	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you hit a creature with an attack roll, you can expend one Superiority Die to maneuver one of your comrades into another position. Add the Superiority Die roll to the attack's damage roll, and choose a willing creature who can see or hear you. That creature can use its Reaction to move up to half its Speed without provoking an Opportunity Attack from the target of your attack.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Maneuvering Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a11	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Menacing Attack	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you hit a creature with an attack roll, you can expend one Superiority Die to attempt to frighten the target. Add the Superiority Die to the attack's damage roll. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or have the Frightened condition until the end of your next turn.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Menacing Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a12	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Parry	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When another creature damages you with a melee attack roll, you can take a Reaction and expend one Superiority Die to reduce the damage by the number you roll on your Superiority Die plus your Strength or Dexterity modifier (your choice).	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Parry																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a13	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Precision Attack	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you miss with an attack roll, you can expend one Superiority Die, roll that die, and add it to the attack roll, potentially causing the attack to hit.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Precision Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a14	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Pushing Attack	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you hit a creature with an attack roll using a weapon or an Unarmed Strike, you can expend one Superiority Die to attempt to drive the target back. Add the Superiority Die to the attack's damage roll. If the target is Large or smaller, it must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be pushed up to 15 feet directly away from you.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Pushing Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a15	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Rally	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can expend one Superiority Die to bolster the resolve of a companion. Choose an ally of yours within 30 feet of yourself who can see or hear you. That creature gains Temporary Hit Points equal to the Superiority Die roll plus half your Fighter level (round down).	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Rally																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a16	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Riposte	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When a creature misses you with a melee attack roll, you can take a Reaction and expend one Superiority Die to make a melee attack roll with a weapon or an Unarmed Strike against the creature. If you hit, add the Superiority Die to the attack's damage.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Riposte																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a17	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Sweeping Attack	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you hit a creature with a melee attack roll using a weapon or an Unarmed Strike, you can expend one Superiority Die to attempt to damage another creature. Choose another creature within 5 feet of the original target and within your reach. If the original attack roll would hit the second creature, it takes damage equal to the number you roll on your Superiority Die. The damage is of the same type dealt by the original attack.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Sweeping Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a18	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Tactical Assessment	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you make an Intelligence (History or Investigation) check or a Wisdom (Insight) check, you can expend one Superiority Die and add that die to the ability check.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Tactical Assessment																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a19	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Trip Attack	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fighter Maneuvers	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you hit a creature with an attack roll using a weapon or an Unarmed Strike, you can expend one Superiority Die and add the die to the attack's damage roll. If the target is Large or smaller, it must succeed on a Strength saving throw or have the Prone condition.	KEY:Fighter Maneuvers ~ Trip Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Fighter_01f1a20	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block:Abilities																																
Martial Art	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your practice of martial arts gives you mastery of combat styles that use your Unarmed Strike and Monk weapons, which are the following: &nl;- Simple Melee weapons &nl - Martial Melee weapons that have the Light property &nl; You gain the following benefits while you are unarmed or wielding only Monk weapons and you aren't wearing armor or wielding a Shield. &nl; Bonus Unarmed Strike. You can make an Unarmed Strike as a Bonus Action. &nl; Martial Arts Die. You can roll ld6 in place of the normal damage of your Unarmed Strike or Monk weapons. This die changes as you gain Monk levels, as shown in the Martial Arts column of the Monk Features table. &nl; Dexterous Attacks. You can use your Dexterity modifier instead of your Strength modifier for the attack and damage rolls of your Unarmed Strikes and Monk weapons. In addition, when you use the Grapple or Shove option of your Unarmed Strike, you can use your Dexterity modifier instead of your Strength modifier to determine the save DC.	KEY:Monk ~ Martial Art	DESC:Martial Die 1d%1.|MartialArtDie			DEFINE:MartialArtDie|0					BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT.Unarmed|max(DEX,STR)-STR	BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT.Simple|max(DEX,STR)-STR	BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT.LightMartial|max(DEX,STR)-STR	BONUS:VAR|MartialArtDie|6	BONUS:VAR|MartialArtDie|2|PREVARGTEQ:MonkLVL,5	BONUS:VAR|MartialArtDie|2|PREVARGTEQ:MonkLVL,11	BONUS:VAR|MartialArtDie|2|PREVARGTEQ:MonkLVL,17											SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Unarmored Defense	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:While you aren't wearing armor or wielding a Shield, your base Armor Class equals 10 plus your Dexterity and Wisdom modifiers.	KEY:Monk ~ Unarmored Defense																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Monk's Focus	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your focus and martial training allow you to harness a well of extraordinary energy within yourself. This energy is represented by Focus Points. Your Monk level determines the number of points you have, as shown in the Focus Points column of the Monk Features table. You can expend these points to enhance or fuel certain Monk features. You start knowing three such features: Flurry of Blows, Patient Defense, and Step of the Wind, each of which is detailed below. When you expend a Focus Point, it is unavailable until you finish a Short or Long Rest, at the end of which you regain all your expended points. Some features that use Focus Points require your target to make a saving throw. The save DC equals 8 plus your Wisdom modifier and Proficiency Bonus. &nl; Flurry of Blows. You can expend 1 Focus Point to make two Unarmed Strikes as a Bonus Action. &nl; Patient Defense. You can take the Disengage action as a Bonus Action. Alternatively, you can expend 1 Focus Point to take both the Disengage and the Dodge actions as a Bonus Action. &nl; Step of the Wind. You can take the Dash action as a Bonus Action. Alternatively, you can expend 1 Focus Point to take both the Disengage and Dash actions as a Bonus Action, and your jump distance is doubled for the turn.	KEY:Monk ~ Monk's Focus	DESC: Focus Points: %1.|FocusPoints			DEFINE:FocusPoints|0					BONUS:VAR|FocusPoints|MonkLVL																	SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Unarmored Movement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your speed increases by 10 feet while you aren't wearing armor or wielding a Shield. This bonus increases when you reach certain Monk levels, as shown on the Monk Features table.	KEY:Monk ~ Unarmored Movement									BONUS:MOVEADD|TYPE.Walk|10+(5*(MonkLVL>=6))+(5*(MonkLVL>=10))+(5*(MonkLVL>=14))+(5*(MonkLVL>=18))|!PREEQUIP:1,TYPE=Armor,TYPE=Shield																	SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Uncanny Metabolism	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you roll Initiative, you can regain all expended Focus Points. When you do so, roll your Martial Arts die, and regain a number of Hit Points equal to your Monk level plus the number rolled. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Monk ~ Uncanny Metabolism																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Deflect Attack	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When an attack roll hits you and its damage includes Bludgeoning, Piercing, or Slashing damage, you can take a Reaction to reduce the attack's total damage against you. The reduction equals ldlO plus your Dexterity modifier and Monk level. If you reduce the damage to 0, you can expend 1 Focus Point to redirect some of the attack's force. If you do so, choose a creature you can see within 5 feet of yourself if the attack was a melee attack or a creature you can see within 60 feet of yourself that isn't behind Total Cover if the attack was a ranged attack. That creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take damage equal to t wo rolls of your Martial Arts die plus your Dex terity modifier. The damage is the same type dealt by the attack.	KEY:Monk ~ Deflect Attack																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Monk Subclass	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a Monk subclass of your choice. The Warrior of Mercy, Warrior of Shadow, Warrior of the Elements, and Warrior of the Open Hand subclasses are detailed after this class's description. A subclass is a specialization that grants you features at certain Monk levels. For the rest of your career, you gain each of your subclass's features that are of your Monk level or lower.	KEY:Monk ~ Monk Subclass									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Monk_Subclass|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ability Score Improvement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the Ability Score Improvement feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. You gain this feature again at Monk levels 8,12, and 16.	KEY:Monk ~ Ability Score Improvement									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Feat|1*((MonkLVL>=4)+(MonkLVL>=8)+(MonkLVL>=12)+(MonkLVL>=16))																	SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01h	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Slow Fall	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can take a Reaction when you fall to reduce any damage you take from the fall by an amount equal to five times your Monk level.	KEY:Monk ~ Slow Fall																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01i	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Extra Attack	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can attack twice instead of once whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.	KEY:Monk ~ Extra Attack																		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Extra Attack ~ 1								SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01j	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Stunning Strike	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Once per turn when you hit a creature with a Monk weapon or an Unarmed Strike, you can expend 1 Focus Point to attempt a stunning strike. The target must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the target has the Stunned condition until the start of your next turn. On a successful save, the target's Speed is halved until the start of your next turn, and the next attack roll made against the target before then has Advantage.	KEY:Monk ~ Stunning Strike																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01k	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Empowered Strike	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever you deal damage with your Unarmed Strike, it can deal your choice of Force damage or its normal damage type.	KEY:Monk ~ Empowered Strike																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01l	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Evasion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Evasion	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you're subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, you instead take no damage if you succeed on the saving throw and only half damage if you fail. You don't benefit from this feature if you have the Incapacitated condition.	KEY:Monk ~ Evasion																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01m	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Acrobatic Movement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:While you aren't wearing armor or wielding a Shield, you gain the ability to move along vertical surfaces and across liquids on your turn without falling during the movement.	KEY:Monk ~ Acrobatic Movement																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01n	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Heightened Focus	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your Flurry of Blows, Patient Defense, and Step of the Wind gain the following benefits. &nl; Flurry of Blows. You can expend 1 Focus Point to use Flurry of Blows and make three Unarmed Strikes with it instead of two. &nl; Patient Defense. When you expend a Focus Point to use Patient Defense, you gain a number of Temporary Hit Points equal to two rolls of your Martial Arts die. &nl; Step of the Wind. When you expend a Focus Point to use Step of the Wind, you can choose a willing creature within 5 feet of yourself that is Large or smaller. You move the creature with you until the end of your turn. The creature's movement doesn't provoke Opportunity Attacks.	KEY:Monk ~ Heightened Focus																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01o	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Self Restoration	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Through sheer force of will, you can remove one of the following conditions from yourself at the end of each of your turns: Charmed, Frightened, or Poisoned. In addition, forgoing food and drink doesn't give you levels of Exhaustion.	KEY:Monk ~ Self Restoration																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01i	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Deflect Energy	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can now use your Deflect Attacks feature against attacks that deal any damage type, not just Bludgeoning, Piercing, or Slashing.	KEY:Monk ~ Deflect Energy																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01j	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Disciplined Survivor	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your physical and mental discipline grant you proficiency in all saving throws. Additionally, whenever you make a saving throw and fail, you can expend 1 Focus Point to reroll it, and you must use the new roll.	KEY:Monk ~ Disciplined Survivor																		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Saving Throw ~ Con|Saving Throw ~ Int|Saving Throw ~ Wis|Saving Throw ~ Cha								SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01k	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Perfect Focus	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you roll Initiative and don't use Uncanny Metabolism, you regain expended Focus Points until you have 4 if you have 3 or fewer.	KEY:Monk ~ Perfect Focus																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01l	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Superior Defense	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At the start of your turn, you can expend 3 Focus Points to bolster yourself against harm for 1 minute or until you have the Incapacitated condition. During that time, you have Resistance to all damage except Force damage.	KEY:Monk ~ Superior Defense																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01m	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Epic Boon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain an Epic Boon feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. Boon of Irresistible Offense is recommended.	KEY:Monk ~ Epic Boon									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Epic_Boon|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01n	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Body and Mind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have developed your body and mind to new heights. Your Dexterity and Wisdom scores increase by 4, to a maximum of 25.	KEY:Monk ~ Body and Mind									BONUS:STAT|DEX,WIS|4	BONUS:VAR|MaxStatDex|5	BONUS:VAR|MaxStatWis|5															SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01o	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block:Monk Subclass																																
Warrior of Mercy	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Monk Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Warriors of Mercy manipulate the life force of others. These Monks are wandering physicians, but they bring a swift end to their enemies. They often wear masks, presenting themselves as faceless bringers of life and death.	KEY:Monk Subclass ~ Warrior of Mercy																		ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of Mercy ~ Hand of Harm|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,3	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of Mercy ~ Hand of Healing|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,3	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of Mercy ~ Implements of Mercy|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,3	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of Mercy ~ Physician's Touch|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,6	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of Mercy ~ Flurry of Healing and Harm|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,11	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of Mercy ~ Hand of Ultimate Mercy|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,17			SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Warrior of Shadow	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Monk Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Warriors of Shadow practice stealth and subterfuge, harnessing the power of the Shadowfell. They are at home in darkness, able to draw gloom around themselves to hide, leap from shadow to shadow, and take on a wraithlike form.	KEY:Monk Subclass ~ Warrior of Shadow																		ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of Shadow ~ Shadow Arts|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,3	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of Shadow ~ Shadow Step|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,6	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of Shadow ~ Improved Shadow Step|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,11	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of Shadow ~ Cloak of Shadows|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,17					SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Warrior of the Elements	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Monk Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Warriors of the Elements tap into the power of the Elemental Planes. Harnessing their supernatural focus, these Monks momentarily tame the energy of the Elemental Chaos to empower themselves in and out of battle.	KEY:Monk Subclass ~ Warrior of the Elements																		ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of the Elements ~ Elemental Attunement|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,3	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of the Elements ~ Manipulate Elements|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,3	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of the Elements ~ Elemental Burst|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,6	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of the Elements ~ Stride of the Elements|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,11	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of the Elements ~ Elemental Epitome|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,17				SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Warrior of the Open Hand	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Monk Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Warriors of the Open Hand are masters of unarmed combat. They learn techniques to push and trip their opponents and manipulate their own energy to protect themselves from harm.	KEY:Monk Subclass ~ Warrior of the Open Hand																		ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of the Open Hand ~ Open Hand Technique|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,3	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of the Open Hand ~ Wholeness of Body|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,6	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of the Open Hand ~ Fleet Step|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,11	ABILITY:Monk Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Warrior of the Open Hand ~ Quivering Palm|PREVAREQ:MonkLVL,17					SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g4a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Hand of Harm	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of Mercy.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Once per turn when you hit a creature with an Unarmed Strike and deal damage, you can expend 1 Focus Point to deal extra Necrotic damage equal to one roll of your Martial Arts die plus your Wisdom modifier.	KEY:Warrior of Mercy ~ Hand of Harm	DESC:damage +1d%1 + %2|MartialArtDie|WIS																									SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g1a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Hand of Healing	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of Mercy.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Magic action, you can expend 1 Focus Point to touch a creature and restore a number of Hit Points equal to a roll of your Martial Arts die plus your Wisdom modifier. When you use your Flurry of Blows, you can replace one of the Unarmed Strikes with a use of this feature without expending a Focus Point for the healing.	KEY:Warrior of Mercy ~ Hand of Healing	DESC:heal +1d%1 + %2|MartialArtDie|WIS																									SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g1b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Implements of Mercy	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of Mercy.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain proficiency in the Insight and Medicine skills and proficiency with the Herbalism Kit.	KEY:Warrior of Mercy ~ Implements of Mercy																		ABILITY:Skill|AUTOMATIC|Insight|Medicine	ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Tool Proficiency ~ Herbalism Kit							SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g1c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Physician's Touch	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of Mercy.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your Hand of Harm and Hand of Healing improve, as detailed below. &nl; Hand of Harm. When you use Hand of Harm on a creature, you can also give that creature the Poisoned condition until the end of your next turn. &nl; Hand of Healing. When you use Hand of Healing, you can also end one of the following conditions on the creature you heal: Blinded, Deafened, Paralyzed, Poisoned, or Stunned.	KEY:Warrior of Mercy ~ Physician's Touch																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g1d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Flurry of Healing and Harm	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of Mercy.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you use Flurry of Blows, you can replace each of the Unarmed Strikes with a use of Hand of Healing without expending Focus Points for the Healing. In addition, when you make an Unarmed Strike with Flurry of Blows and deal damage, you can use Hand of Harm with that strike without expending a Focus Point for Hand of Harm. You can still use Hand of Harm only once per turn. You can use these benefits a total number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of once). You regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Warrior of Mercy ~ Flurry of Healing and Harm																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g1e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Hand of Ultimate Mercy	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of Mercy.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your mastery of life energy opens the door to the ultimate mercy. As a Magic action, you can touch the corpse of a creature that died within the past 24 hours and expend 5 Focus Points. The creature then returns to life with a number of Hit Points equal to 4d10 plus your Wisdom modifier. If the creature died with any of the following conditions, the creature revives with the conditions removed: Blinded, Deafened, Paralyzed, Poisoned, and Stunned. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Warrior of Mercy ~ Hand of Ultimate Mercy																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g1f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Shadow Arts	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of Shadow.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have learned to draw on the power of the Shadowfell, gaining the following benefits. Darkness. You can expend 1 Focus Point to cast the Darkness spell without spell components. You can see within the spell's area when you cast it with this feature. While the spell persists, you can move its area of Darkness to a space within 60 feet of yourself at the start of each of your turns. &nl; Darkvision. You gain Darkvision with a range of 60 feet. If you already have Darkvision, its range increases by 60 feet. &nl; Shadowy Figments. You know the Minor Illusion spell. Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for it.	KEY:Warrior of Shadow ~ Shadow Arts									BONUS:VAR|DarkvisionRange|60									SPELLS:Shadow Arts|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=MonkLVL|Minor Illusion,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLS:Shadow Arts|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=MonkLVL|Darkness							SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g2a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Shadow Step	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of Shadow.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:While entirely within Dim Light or Darkness, you can use a Bonus Action to teleport up to 60 feet to an unoccupied space you can see that is also in Dim Light or Darkness. You then have Advantage on the next melee attack you make before the end of the current turn.	KEY:Warrior of Shadow ~ Shadow Step																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g2b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Improved Shadow Step	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of Shadow.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can draw on your Shadowfell connection to empower your teleportation. When you use your Shadow Step, you can expend 1 Focus Point to remove the requirement that you must start and end in Dim Light or Darkness for that use of the feature. As part of this Bonus Action, you can make an Unarmed Strike immediately after you teleport.	KEY:Warrior of Shadow ~ Improved Shadow Step																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g2c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Cloak of Shadows	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of Shadow.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Magic action while entirely within Dim Light or Darkness, you can expend 3 Focus Points to shroud yourself with shadows for 1 minute, until you have the Incapacitated condition, or until you end your turn in Bright Light. While shrouded by these shadows, you gain the following benefits. &nl; Invisibility. You have the Invisible condition. &nl; Partially Incorporeal. You can move through occupied spaces as if they were Difficult Terrain. If you end your turn in such a space, you are shunted to the last unoccupied space you were in. &nl; Shadow Flurry. You can use your Flurry of Blows without expending any Focus Points.	KEY:Warrior of Shadow ~ Cloak of Shadows																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g2d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Elemental Attunement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of the Element.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:At the start of your turn, you can expend 1 Focus Point to imbue yourself with elemental energy. The energy lasts for 10 minutes or until you have the Incapacitated condition. You gain the following benefits while this feature is active. &nl; Reach. When you make an Unarmed Strike, your reach is 10 feet greater than normal, as elemental energy extends from you. &nl; Elemental Strikes. Whenever you hit with your Unarmed Strike, you can cause it to deal your choice of Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, or Thunder damage rather than its normal damage type. When you deal one of these types with it, you can also force the target to make a Strength saving throw. On a failed save, you can move the target up to 10 feet toward or away from you, as elemental energy swirls around it.	KEY:Warrior of the Elements ~ Elemental Attunement																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g3a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Manipulate Elements	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of the Element.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You know the Elementalism spell. Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for it.	KEY:Warrior of the Elements ~ Manipulate Elements																		SPELLS:Manipulate Elements|TIMES=ATWILL|Elementalism,SpellDC_WIS								SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g3b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Elemental Burst	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of the Element.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Magic action, you can expend 2 Focus Points to cause elemental energy to burst in a 20-foot-radius Sphere centered on a point within 120 feet of yourself. Choose a damage type: Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, or Thunder. Each creature in the Sphere must make a Dexterity saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes damage of the chosen type equal to three rolls of your Martial Arts die. On a successful save, a creature takes half as much damage.	KEY:Warrior of the Elements ~ Elemental Burst																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g3c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Stride of the Elements	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of the Element.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:While your Elemental Attunement is active, you also have a Fly Speed and a Swim Speed equal to your Speed.	KEY:Warrior of the Elements ~ Stride of the Elements																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g3d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Elemental Epitome	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of the Element.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:While your Elemental Attunement is active, you also gain the following benefits. &nl; Damage Resistance. You gain Resistance to one of the following damage types of your choice: Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, or Thunder. At the start of each of your turns, you can change this choice. &nl; Destructive Stride. When you use your Step of the Wind, your Speed increases by 20 feet until the end of lite turn. For that duration, any creature of your choice takes damage equal to one roll of your Martial Arts die when you enter a space within 5 feet of it. The damage type is your choice of Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, or Thunder. A creature can take this damage only once per turn. &nl; Empowered Strikes. Once on each of your turns, you can deal extra damage to a target equal to one roll of your Martial Arts die when you hit it with an Unarmed Strike. The extra damage is the same type dealt by that strike.	KEY:Warrior of the Elements ~ Elemental Epitome									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Elemental_Epitome|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g3e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Acid	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Warrior of the Elements.Elemental Epitome	VISIBLE:DISPLAY	DESC:Resistance to Acid	KEY:Warrior of the Elements ~ Elemental Epitome ~ Acid																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g3e1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Cold	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Warrior of the Elements.Elemental Epitome	VISIBLE:DISPLAY	DESC:Resistance to Cold	KEY:Warrior of the Elements ~ Elemental Epitome ~ Cold																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g3e1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Fire	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Warrior of the Elements.Elemental Epitome	VISIBLE:DISPLAY	DESC:Resistance to Fire	KEY:Warrior of the Elements ~ Elemental Epitome ~ Fire																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g3e1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Lightning	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Warrior of the Elements.Elemental Epitome	VISIBLE:DISPLAY	DESC:Resistance to Lightning	KEY:Warrior of the Elements ~ Elemental Epitome ~ Lightning																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g3e1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Thunder	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Warrior of the Elements.Elemental Epitome	VISIBLE:DISPLAY	DESC:Resistance to Thunder	KEY:Warrior of the Elements ~ Elemental Epitome ~ Thunder																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g3e1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Open Hand Technique	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of the Open Hand.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever you hit a creature with an attack granted by your Flurry of Blows, you can impose one of the following effect on that target. &nl; Addle. The target can't make Opportunity Attacks until the start of its next turn. &nl; Push. The target must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be pushed up to 15 feet away from you. &nl; Topple. The target must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or have the Prone condition.	KEY:Warrior of the Open Hand ~ Open Hand Technique																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g4a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Wholeness of Body	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of the Open Hand.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the ability to heal yourself. As a Bonus Action, you can roll your Martial Arts die. You regain a number of Hit Points equal to the number rolled plus your Wisdom modifier (minimum of 1 Hit Point Regained). You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Warrior of the Open Hand ~ Wholeness of Body	DESC:heal +1d%1 + %2|MartialArtDie|WIS																									SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g4b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Fleet Step	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of the Open Hand.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you take a Bonus Action other than Step of the Wind, you can also use Step of the Wind immediately after that Bonus Action.	KEY:Warrior of the Open Hand ~ Fleet Step																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g4c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Quivering Palm	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Monk Class Feature.Class Feature.Warrior of the Open Hand.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the ability to set up lethal vibrations in someone's body. When you hit a creature with an Unarmed Strike, you can expend 4 Focus Points to start these imperceptible vibrations, which last for a number of days equal to your Monk level. The vibrations are harmless unless you take an action to end them. Alternatively, when you take the Attack action on your turn, you can forgo one of the attacks to end the vibrations. To end them, you and the target must be on the same plane of existence.	KEY:Warrior of the Open Hand ~ Quivering Palm																										SORTKEY:Class_Monk_01g4d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block:Abilities																																
Lay on Hands	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your blessed touch can heal wounds. You have a pool of healing power that replenishes when you finish a Long Rest. With that pool, you can restore a total number of Hit Points equal to five times your Paladin level. As a Bonus Action, you can touch a creature (which could be yourself) and draw power from the pool of healing to restore a number of Hit Points to that creature, up to the maximum amount remaining in the pool. You can also expend 5 Hit Points from the pool of healing power to remove the Poisoned condition from the creature; those points don't also restore Hit Points to the creature.	KEY:Paladin ~ Lay on Hands									BONUS:VAR|LayOnHands|5*PaladinLVL									ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Lay on Hands								SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Spellcasting	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have learned to cast spells through prayer and meditation. See chapter 7 for the rules on spellcasting. The information below details how you use those rules with Paladin spells, which appear in the Paladin spell list later in the class's description. &nl; Spell Slots. The Paladin Features table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your level 1+ spells. You regain all expended slots when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; Prepared Spells of Level 1+. You prepare the list of level 1+ spells that are available for you to cast with this feature. To start, choose two level 1 Paladin spells. Heroism and Searing Smite are recommended. The number of spells on your list increases as you gain Paladin levels, as shown in the Prepared Spells column of the Paladin Features table. Whenever that number increases, choose additional Paladin spells until the number of spells on your list matches the number in the Paladin Features table. The chosen spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots. For example, if you're a level 5 Paladin, your list of prepared spells can include six Paladin spells of level 1 or 2 in any combination. If another Paladin feature gives you spells that you always have prepared, those spells don't count against the number of spells you can prepare with this feature, but those spells otherwise count as Paladin spells for you. &nl; Changing Your Prepared Spells. Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can replace one spell on your list with another Paladin spell for which you have spell slots. &nl; Spellcasting Ability. Charisma is your spellcasting ability for your Paladin spells. &nl; Spellcasting Focus. You can use a Holy Symbol as a Spellcasting Focus for your Paladin spells. Spell save DC %1; Spell attack modifier +%2|PaladinSpellDC|Proficiency_Bonus+CHA	KEY:Paladin ~ Spellcasting				DEFINE:PaladinSpellDC|0					BONUS:VAR|PaladinSpellDC|SpellDC_CHA																	SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Weapon Mastery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your training with weapons allows you to use the mastery properties of two kinds of weapons of your choice with which you have proficiency, such as Longswords and Javelins. Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can change the kinds of weapons you chose. For example, you could switch to using the mastery properties of Halberds and Flails.	KEY:Paladin ~ Weapon Mastery	DESC:%1 weapon mastery.|WeaponMastery			DEFINE:WeaponMastery|0					BONUS:VAR|POOL_Weapon_Mastery|WeaponMastery	BONUS:VAR|WeaponMastery|2																SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Fighting Style	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a Fighting Style feat of your choice (see chapter 5 for feats). Instead of choosing one of those feats, you can choose the option below. &nl; Blessed Warrior. You learn two Cleric cantrips of your choice (see the Cleric class's section for a list of Cleric spells). Guidance and Sacred Flame are recommended. The chosen cantrips count as Paladin spells for you, and Charisma is your spellcasting ability for them. Whenever you gain a Paladin level, you can replace one of these cantrips with another Cleric cantrip.	KEY:Paladin ~ Fighting Style									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Fighting_Style|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Paladin's Smite	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You always have the Divine Smite spell prepared. In addition, you can cast it without expending a spell slot, but you must finish a Long Rest before you can cast it in this way again.	KEY:Paladin ~ Paladin's Smite																		SPELLS:Paladin's Smite|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Divine Smite,SpellDC_CHA								SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Channel Divinity	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can channel divine energy directly from the Outer Planes, using it to fuel magical effects. You start with one such effect: Divine Sense, which is described below. Other Paladin features give additional Channel Divinity effect options. Each time you use this class's Channel Divinity, you choose which effect from this class to create. You can use this class's Channel Divinity twice. You regain one of its expended uses when you finish a Short Rest, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. You gain an additional use when you reach Paladin level 11. if a Channel Divinity effect requires a saving throw, the DC equals the spell save DC from this class's Spellcasting feature. &nl; Divine Sense. As a Bonus Action, you can open your awareness to detect Celestials, Fiends, and Undead. For the next 10 minutes or until you have the Incapacitated condition, you know the location of any creature of those types within 60 feet of yourself, and you know its creature type. Within the same radius, you also detect the presence of any place or object that has been consecrated or desecrated, as with the Hallow spell	KEY:Paladin ~ Channel Divinity	DESC: %1/day.|PaladinChannelDivinity			DEFINE:PaladinChannelDivinity|0					BONUS:VAR|PaladinChannelDivinity|2+(PaladinLVL>=11)									ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Channel Divinity ~ Divine Sense								SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Paladin Subclass	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a Paladin subclass of your choice. The Oath of Devotion, Oath of Glory, Oath of the Ancients, and Oath of Vengeance subclasses are detailed after this class's description. A subclass is a specialization that grants you features at certain Paladin levels. For the rest of your career, you gain each of your subclass's features that are of your Paladin level or lower.	KEY:Paladin ~ Paladin Subclass									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Paladin_Subclass|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ability Score Improvement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the Ability Score Improvement feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. You gain this feature again at Paladin levels 8,12, and 16.	KEY:Paladin ~ Ability Score Improvement									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Feat|1*((PaladinLVL>=4)+(PaladinLVL>=8)+(PaladinLVL>=12)+(PaladinLVL>=16))																	SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01h	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Extra Attack	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can attack twice instead of once whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.	KEY:Paladin ~ Extra Attack																		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Extra Attack ~ 1								SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01i	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Faithful Steed	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can call on the aid of an otherworldly steed. You always have the Find Steed spell prepared. You can also cast the spell once without expending a spell slot, and you regain the ability to do so when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Paladin ~ Faithful Steed																		SPELLS:Faithful Steed|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Find Steed								SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01j	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Aura of Protection	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You radiate a protective, unseeable aura in a 10-foot Emanation that originates from you. The aura is inactive while you have the Incapacitated condition. You and your allies in the aura gain a bonus to saving throws equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum bonus of +1). If another Paladin is present, a creature can benefit from only one Aura of Protection at a time; the creature chooses which aura while in them.	KEY:Paladin ~ Aura of Protection	DESC:bonus +%1.|AuraOfProtectionBonus			DEFINE:AuraOfProtectionBonus|0					BONUS:VAR|AuraOfProtectionBonus|max(1,CHA)	BONUS:SAVE|ALL|AuraOfProtectionBonus																SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01k	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Abjure Foes	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Magic action, you can expend one use of this class's Channel Divinity to overwhelm foes with awe. As you present your Holy Symbol or weapon, you can target a number of creatures equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of one creature) that you can see within 60 feet of yourself. Each target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or have the Frightened condition for 1 minute or until it takes any damage. While Frightened in this way, a target can do only one of the following on its turns: move, take an action, or take a Bonus Action.	KEY:Paladin ~ Abjure Foes																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01l	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Aura of Courage	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You and your allies have Immunity to the Frightened condition while in your Aura of Protection. If a Frightened ally enters the aura, that condition has no effect on that ally while there.	KEY:Paladin ~ Aura of Courage																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01m	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Radiant Strikes	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your strikes now carry supernatural power. When you hit a target with an attack roll using a Melee weapon or an Unarmed Strike, the target takes an extra 1d8 Radiant damage.	KEY:Paladin ~ Radiant Strikes																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01n	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Restoring Touch	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you use Lay On Hands on a creature, you can also remove one or more of the following conditions from the creature: Blinded, Charmed, Deafened, Frightened, Paralyzed, or Stunned. You must expend 5 Hit Points from the healing pool of Lay On Hands for each of these conditions you remove; those points don't also restore Hit Points to the creature.	KEY:Paladin ~ Restoring Touch																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01o	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Aura Expansion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your Aura of Protection is now a 30-foot Emanation.	KEY:Paladin ~ Aura Expansion																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01p	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Epic Boon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain an Epic Boon feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. Boon of Truesight is recommended.	KEY:Paladin ~ Epic Boon									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Epic_Boon|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01q	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
# Paladin Cantrip																																
Guidance	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Paladin Cantrip		DESC:You touch one willing creature. Once before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one ability check of its choice. It can roll the die before or after making the ability check. The spell then ends.	KEY:Paladin Cantrip ~ Guidance																		SPELLS:Paladin Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Guidance,SpellDC_CHA	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=0|Guidance								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Light	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Paladin Cantrip		DESC:You touch one object that is no larger than 10 feet in any dimension. Until the spell ends, the object sheds bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light for an additional 20 feet. The light can be colored as you like. Completely covering the object with something opaque blocks the light. The spell ends if you cast it again or dismiss it as an action. If you target an object held or worn by a hostile creature, that creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw to avoid the spell.	KEY:Paladin Cantrip ~ Light																		SPELLS:Paladin Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Light,SpellDC_CHA	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=0|Light								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Mending	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Paladin Cantrip		DESC:This spell repairs a single break or tear in an object you touch, such as a broken chain link, two halves of a broken key, a torn cloak, or a leaking wineskin. As long as the break or tear is no larger than 1 foot in any dimension, you mend it. leaving no trace of the former damage. This spell can physically repair a magic item or construct, but the spell can't restore magic to such an object.	KEY:Paladin Cantrip ~ Mending																		SPELLS:Paladin Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mending,SpellDC_CHA	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=0|Mending								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Resistance	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Paladin Cantrip		DESC:You touch one willing creature. Once before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one saving throw of its choice. It can roll the die before or after making the saving throw. The spell then ends.	KEY:Paladin Cantrip ~ Resistance																		SPELLS:Paladin Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Resistance,SpellDC_CHA	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=0|Resistance								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Sacred Flame	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Paladin Cantrip		DESC:Flame-like radiance descends on a creature that you can see within range. The target must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take 1d8 radiant damage. The target gains no benefit from cover for this saving throw. The spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).	KEY:Paladin Cantrip ~ Sacred Flame																		SPELLS:Paladin Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Sacred Flame,SpellDC_CHA	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=0|Sacred Flame								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Spare the Dying	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Paladin Cantrip		DESC:You touch a living creature that has 0 hit points. The creature becomes stable. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.	KEY:Paladin Cantrip ~ Spare the Dying																		SPELLS:Paladin Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Spare the Dying,SpellDC_CHA	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=0|Spare the Dying								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Thaumaturgy	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Paladin Cantrip		DESC:You manifest a minor wonder, a sign of supernatural power, within range. You create one of the following magical effects within range: * Your voice booms up to three times as loud as normal for 1 minute. * You cause flames to flicker, brighten, dim, or change color for 1 minute. * You cause harmless tremors in the ground for 1 minute. * You create an instantaneous sound that originates from a point of your choice within range, such as a rumble of thunder, the cry of a raven, or ominous whispers. * You instantaneously cause an unlocked door or window to fly open or slam shut. * You alter the appearance of your eyes for 1 minute. If you cast this spell multiple times, you can have up to three of its 1-minute effects active at a time, and you can dismiss such an effect as an action.	KEY:Paladin Cantrip ~ Thaumaturgy																		SPELLS:Paladin Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Thaumaturgy,SpellDC_CHA	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=0|Thaumaturgy								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Toll the Dead	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Paladin Cantrip			KEY:Paladin Cantrip ~ Toll the Dead																		SPELLS:Paladin Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Toll the Dead,SpellDC_CHA	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=0|Toll the Dead								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Word of Radiance	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Paladin Cantrip			KEY:Paladin Cantrip ~ Word of Radiance																		SPELLS:Paladin Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Word of Radiance,SpellDC_CHA	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Paladin=0|Word of Radiance								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block:Channel Divinity																																
Channel Divinity: Divine Sense	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Channel Divinity.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can open your awareness to detect Celestials, Fiends, and Undead. For the next 10 minutes or until you have the Incapacitated condition, you know the location of any creature of those types within 60 feet of yourself, and you know its creature type. Within the same radius, you also detect the presence of any place or object that has been consecrated or desecrated, as with the Hallow spell.	KEY:Channel Divinity ~ Divine Sense																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01f1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block																																
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Paladin ~ Spellcasting.MOD									DEFINE:PaladinCast1|0	DEFINE:BardKnown1|0				BONUS:VAR|PaladinCast1|SpellSlotsLVL1																		
