###Block																																
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Paladin ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:PaladinPreparedSlots|0	BONUS:SPELLCAST|CLASS=Paladin;LEVEL=10|PaladinPreparedSlots	BONUS:VAR|PaladinPreparedSlots|PaladinPreparedBase																													
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Paladin ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:PaladinPreparedBase|0	BONUS:VAR|PaladinPreparedBase|CHA+floor(PaladinLVL/2)	BONUS:VAR|PaladinPreparedBase|3+PaladinLVL+(PaladinLVL>=6)+(PaladinLVL>=9)-(PaladinLVL>=12)-(PaladinLVL>=14)-(PaladinLVL>=16)																													
																																
###Block:Paladin Subclass																																
Oath of Devotion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Paladin Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The Oath of Devotion binds Paladins to the ideals of justice and order. These Paladins meet the archetype of the knight in shining armor. They hold themselves to the highest standards of conduct, and some-for better or worse-hold the rest of the world to the same standards. Many who swear this oath are devoted to gods of law and good and use their gods' tenets as the measure of personal devotion. Others hold angels as their ideals and incorporate images of angelic wings into their helmets or coats of arms. These paladins share the following tenets: &nl; - Let your word be your promise. &nl; - Protect the weak and never fear to act. &nl; - Let your honorable deeds be an example.	KEY:Paladin Subclass ~ Oath of Devotion																		ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Devotion ~ Spells|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Devotion ~ Sacred Weapon|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Devotion ~ Aura of Devotion|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,7	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Devotion ~ Smite of Protection|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,15	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Devotion ~ Holy Nimbus|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,20				SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Oath of Glory	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Paladin Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Paladins who take the Oath of Glory believe they and their companions are destined to achieve glory through deeds of heroism. They train diligently and encourage their companions, so they're all ready when destiny calls. These paladins share the following tenets: &nl; - Endeavor to be known by your deeds. &nl; - Face hardships with courage. &nl; - Inspire others to strive for glory.	KEY:Paladin Subclass ~ Oath of Glory																		ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Glory ~ Spells|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Glory ~ Inspiring Smite|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Glory ~ Peerless Athlete|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Glory ~ Aura of Alacrity|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,7	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Glory ~ Glorious Defense|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,15	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Glory ~ Living Legend|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,20			SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Oath of the Ancients	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Paladin Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Paladins who take the Oath of Glory believe they and their companions are destined to achieve glory through deeds of heroism. They train diligently and encourage their companions, so they're all ready when destiny calls. These paladins share the following tenets: &nl; - Endeavor to be known by your deeds. &nl; - Face hardships with courage. &nl; - Inspire others to strive for glory.	KEY:Paladin Subclass ~ Oath of the Ancients																		ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of the Ancients ~ Spells|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of the Ancients ~ Nature's Wrath|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of the Ancients ~ Aura of Warding|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,7	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of the Ancients ~ Undying Sentinel|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,15	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of the Ancients ~ Elder Champion|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,20				SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Oath of Vengeance	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Paladin Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The Oath of Vengeance is a solemn commitment to punish those who have committed grievously evil acts. When evil armies slaughter helpless villagers, when a tyrant defies the will of the gods, when a thieves' guild grows too violent, when a dragon rampages through the countryside-at times like these, paladins arise and swear an Oath of Vengeance to set right what has gone wrong. These paladins share the following tenets: &nl; - Show the wicked no mercy. &nl; - Fight injustice and its causes. &nl; - Aid those harmed by injustice.	KEY:Paladin Subclass ~ Oath of Vengeance																		ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Vengeance ~ Spells|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Vengeance ~ Vow of Enmity|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,3	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Vengeance ~ Relentless Avenger|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,7	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Vengeance ~ Soul of Vengeance|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,15	ABILITY:Paladin Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Oath of Vengeance ~ Avenging Angel|PREVAREQ:PaladinLVL,20				SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Devotion.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The magic of your oath ensures you always have certain spells ready; when you reach a Paladin level specified in the Oath of Devotion Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Oath of Devotion ~ Spells																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g1a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Sacred Weapon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Devotion.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you take the Attack action, you can expend one use of your Channel Divinity to imbue one Melee weapon that you are holding with positive energy. For 10 minutes or until you use this feature again, you add your Charisma modifier to attack rolls you make with that weapon (minimum bonus of+1), and each time you hit with it, you cause it to deal its normal damage type or Radiant damage. The weapon also emits Bright Light in a 20-foot radius and Dim Light 20 feet beyond that. You can end this effect early (no action required). This effect also ends if you aren't carrying the weapon.	KEY:Oath of Devotion ~ Sacred Weapon	DESC: +%1 attack|SacredWeaponBonus			DEFINE:SacredWeaponBonus|0					BONUS:VAR|SacredWeaponBonus|max(1,CHA)																	SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g1b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Aura of Devotion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Devotion.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You and your allies have Immunity to the Charmed condition while in your Aura of Protection. If a Charmed ally enters the aura, that condition has no effect on that ally while there.	KEY:Oath of Devotion ~ Aura of Devotion																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g1c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Smite of Protection	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Devotion.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your magical smite now radiates protective energy. Whenever you cast Divine Smite, you and your allies have Half Cover while in your Aura of Protection. The aura has this benefit until the start of your next turn.	KEY:Oath of Devotion ~ Smite of Protection																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g1d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Holy Nimbus	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Devotion.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can imbue your Aura of Protection with holy power, granting the benefits below for 10 minutes or until you end them (no action required). Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also restore your use of it by expending a level 5 spell slot (no action required). &nl; Holy Ward. You have Advantage on any saving throw you are forced to make by a Fiend or an Undead. &nl; Radiant Damage. Whenever an enemy starts its turn in the aura, that creature takes Radiant damage equal to your Charisma modifier plus your Proficiency Bonus. &nl; Sunlight. The aura is filled with Bright Light that is sunlight.	KEY:Oath of Devotion ~ Holy Nimbus																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g1e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Glory.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The magic of your oath ensures you always have certain spells ready; when you reach a Paladin level specified in the Oath of Glory Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Oath of Glory ~ Spells																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g2a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Inspiring Smite	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Glory.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Immediately after you cast Divine Smile, you can expend one use of your Channel Divinity and distribute Temporary Hit Points to creatures of your choice within 30 feet of yourself, which can include you. The total number of Temporary Hit Points equals 2d8 plus your Paladin level, divided among the chosen creatures however you like.	KEY:Oath of Glory ~ Inspiring Smite	DESC:Temporary HP 2d8+%1|InspiringSmiteHP			DEFINE:InspiringSmiteHP|0					BONUS:VAR|InspiringSmiteHP|PaladinLVL																	SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g2b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Peerless Athlete	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Glory.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can expend one use of your Channel Divinity to augment your athleticism. For 1 hour, you have Advantage on Strength (Athletics) and Dexterity (Acrobatics) checks, and the distance of your Long and High Jumps increases by 10 feet (this extra distance costs movement as normal).	KEY:Oath of Glory ~ Peerless Athlete																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g2c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Aura of Alacrity	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Glory.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your Speed increases by 10 feet. In addition, whenever an ally enters your Aura of Protection for the first time on a turn or starts their turn there, the ally's Speed increases by 10 feet until the end of their next turn.	KEY:Oath of Glory ~ Aura of Alacrity									BONUS:VAR|Move_Walk|10																	SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g2d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Glorious Defense	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Glory.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can turn defense into a sudden strike. When you or another creature you can see within 10 feet of you is hit by an attack roll, you can take a Reaction to grant a bonus to the target's AC against that attack, potentially causing it to miss. The bonus equals your Charisma modifier (minimum of +1). If the attack misses, you can make one attack with a weapon against the attacker as part of this Reaction if the attacker is within your weapon's range. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Oath of Glory ~ Glorious Defense	DESC:Bonus AC +%1 (%2/day)|GloriousDefenseSC|GloriousDefenseTimes			DEFINE:GloriousDEfenseAC|0	DEFINE:GloriousDefenseTimes|0				BONUS:VAR|GloriousDefenseAC|max(1,CHA)	BONUS:VAR|GloriousDefenseTimes|max(1,CHA)																SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g2e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Living Legend	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Glory.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can empower yourself with the legends-whether true or exaggerated-of your great deeds. As a Bonus Action, you gain the benefits below for 10 minutes. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also restore your use of it by expending a level 5 spell slot (no action required). &nl; Charismatic. You are blessed with an otherworldly presence and have Advantage on all Charisma checks. &nl; Saving Throw Reroll. If you fail a saving throw, you can take a Reaction to reroll it. You must use this new roll. &nl; Unerring Strike. Once on each of your turns when you make an attack roll with a weapon and miss, you can cause that attack to hit instead.	KEY:Oath of Glory ~ Living Legend																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g2f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of the Ancients.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The magic of your oath ensures you always have certain spells ready; when you reach a Paladin level specified in the Oath of the Ancients Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Oath of the Ancients ~ Spells																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g3a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Nature's Wrath	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of the Ancients.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Magic action, you can expend one use of your Channel Divinity to conjure spectral vines around nearby creatures. Each creature of your choice that you can see within 15 feet of yourself must succeed on a Strength saving throw or have the Restrained condition for 1 minute. A Restrained creature repeats the save at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.	KEY:Oath of the Ancients ~ Nature's Wrath																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g3b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Aura of Warding	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of the Ancients.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Ancient magic lies so heavily upon you that it forms an eldritch ward, blunting energy from beyond the Material Plane; you and your allies have Resistance to Necrotic, Psychic, and Radiant damage while in your Aura of Protection.	KEY:Oath of the Ancients ~ Aura of Warding																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g3c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Undying Sentinel	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of the Ancients.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you are reduced to 0 Hit Points and not killed outright, you can drop to 1 Hit Point instead, and you regain a number of Hit Points equal to three times your Paladin level. Once you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest. Additionally, you can't be aged magically, and you cease visibly aging.	KEY:Oath of the Ancients ~ Undying Sentinel																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g3d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Elder Champion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of the Ancients.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can imbue your Aura of Protection with primal power, granting the benefits below for 1 minute or until you end them (no action required). Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also restore your use of it by expending a level 5 spell slot (no action required). &nl; Diminish Defiance. Enemies in the aura have Disadvantage on saving throws against your spells and Channel Divinity options. &nl; Regeneration. At the start of each of your turns, you regain 10 Hit Points. &nl; Swift Spells. Whenever you cast a spell that has a casting time of an action, you can cast it using a Bonus Action instead.	KEY:Oath of the Ancients ~ Elder Champion																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g3e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Vengeance.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The magic of your oath ensures you always have certain spells ready; when you reach a Paladin level specified in the Oath of Vengeance Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Oath of Vengeance ~ Spells																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g4a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Vow of Enmity	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Vengeance.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you take the Attack action, you can expend one use of your Channel Divinity to utter a vow of enmity against a creature you can see within 30 feet of yourself. You have Advantage on attack rolls against the creature for 1 minute or until you use this feature again. If the creature drops to 0 Hit Points before the vow ends, you can transfer the vow to a different creature within 30 feet of yourself (no action required).	KEY:Oath of Vengeance ~ Vow of Enmity																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g4b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Relentless Avenger	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Vengeance.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your supernatural focus helps you close off a foe's retreat. When you hit a creature with an Opportunity Attack, you can reduce the creature's Speed to 0 until the end of the current turn. You can then move up to half your Speed as part of the same Reaction. This movement doesn't provoke Opportunity Attacks.	KEY:Oath of Vengeance ~ Relentless Avenger																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g4c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Soul of Vengeance	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Vengeance.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Immediately after a creature under the effect of your Vow of Enmity hits or misses with an attack roll, you can take a Reaction to make a melee attack against that creature if it's within range.	KEY:Oath of Vengeance ~ Soul of Vengeance																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g4d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Avenging Angel	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Paladin Class Feature.Class Feature.Oath of Vengeance.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you gain the benefits below for 10 minutes or until you end them (no action required). Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest. You can also restore your use of it by expending a level 5 spell slot (no action required). &nl; Flight. You sprout spectral wings on your back, have a Fly Speed of 60 feet, and can hover. &nl; Frightful Aura. Whenever an enemy starts its turn in your Aura of Protection, that creature must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or have the Frightened condition for 1 minute or until it takes any damage. Attack rolls against the Frightened creature have Advantage.	KEY:Oath of Vengeance ~ Avenging Angel																										SORTKEY:Class_Paladin_01g4e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block:Abilities																																
Spellcasting	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have learned to channel the magical essence of nature to cast spells. See chapter 7 for the rules on spellcasting. The information below details how you use those rules with Ranger spells, which appear in the Ranger spell list later in the class's description. &nl; Spell Slots. The Ranger Features table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your level 1+ spells. You regain all expended slots when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; Prepared Spells of Level 1+. You prepare the list of level 1+ spells that are available for you to cast with this feature. To start, choose two level 1 Ranger spells. Cure Wounds and Ensnaring Strike are Recommended. The number of spells on your list increases as you gain Ranger levels, as shown in the Prepared Spells column of the Ranger Features table. Whenever that number increases, choose additional Ranger spells until the number of spells on your list matches the number in the Ranger Features table. The chosen spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots. For example, if you're a level 5 Ranger, your list of prepared spells can include six Ranger spells of level 1 or 2 in any combination. If another Ranger feature gives you spells that you always have prepared, those spells don't count against the number of spells you can prepare with this feature, but those spells otherwise count as Ranger spells for you. &nl; Changing Your Prepared Spells. Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can replace one spell on your list with another Ranger spell for which you have spell slots. &nl; Spellcasting Ability. Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for your Ranger spells. &nl; Spellcasting Focus. You can use a Druidic Focus as a Spellcasting Focus for your Ranger spells. Spell save DC %1; Spell attack modifier +%2|SpellDC_CHA|Proficiency_Bonus+CHA	KEY:Ranger ~ Spellcasting				DEFINE:RangerSpellDC|0					BONUS:VAR|RangerSpellDC|SpellDC_CHA																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Favored Enemy	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You always have the Hunter's Mark spell prepared. You can cast it twice without expending a spell slot, and you regain all expended uses of this ability when you finish a Long Rest. The number of times you can cast the spell without a spell slot increases when you reach certain Ranger levels, as shown in the Favored Enemy column of the Ranger Features table.	KEY:Ranger ~ Favored Enemy				DEFINE:FavoredEnemyTimes|0					BONUS:VAR|FavoredEnemyTimes|2+(RangerLVL>=5)+(RangerLVL>=9)+(RangerLVL>=13)+(RangerLVL>=17)									SPELLS:Favored Enemy|TIMES=FavoredEnemyTimes|Hunter's Mark								SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Weapon Mastery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your training with weapons allows you to use the mastery properties of two kinds of weapons of your choice with which you have proficiency, such as Longbows and Shortswords. Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can change the kinds of weapons you chose. For example, you could switch to using the mastery properties of Scimitars and Longswords.	KEY:Ranger ~ Weapon Mastery									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Weapon_Mastery|2																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Deft Explorer	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Thanks to your travels, you gain the following Benefits. &nl; Expertise. Choose one of your skill proficiencies with which you lack Expertise. You gain Expertise in that skill. &nl; Languages. You know two languages of your choice from the language tables in chapter 2.	KEY:Ranger ~ Deft Explorer									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Expertise|1	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Language|2																SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Fighting Style	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a Fighting Style feat of your choice (see chapter 5). Instead of choosing one of those feats, you can choose the option below. &nl; Druidic Warrior. You learn two Druid cantrips of your choice (see the Druid class's section for a list of Druid spells). Guidance and Starry Wisp are recommended. The chosen cantrips count as Ranger spells for you, and Wisdom is your spellcasting ability for them. Whenever you gain a Ranger level, you can replace one of these cantrips with another Druid cantrip.	KEY:Ranger ~ Fighting Style									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Fighting_Style|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ranger Subclass	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a Ranger subclass of your choice. The Beast Master, Fey Wanderer, Gloom Stalker, and Hunter subclasses are detailed after this class's description. A subclass is a specialization that grants you features at certain Ranger levels. For the rest of your career, you gain each of your subclass's features that are of your Ranger level or lower.	KEY:Ranger ~ Ranger Subclass									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Ranger_Subclass|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ability Score Improvement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the Ability Score Improvement feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. You gain this feature again at Ranger levels 8,12, and 16.	KEY:Ranger ~ Ability Score Improvement									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Feat|1*((RangerLVL>=4)+(RangerLVL>=8)+(RangerLVL>=12)+(RangerLVL>=16))																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01g	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Extra Attack	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can attack twice instead of once whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.	KEY:Ranger ~ Extra Attack																		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Extra Attack ~ 1								SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01h	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Roving	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your Speed increases by 10 feet while you aren't wearing Heavy armor. You also have a Climb Speed and a Swim Speed equal to your Speed.	KEY:Ranger ~ Roving									BONUS:VAR|Move_Walk|10|PREEQUIP:1,TYPE.HeavyArmor	MOVECLONE:Swim,Walk,*1	MOVECLONE:Climb,Walk,*1															SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01i	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Expertise	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Choose two of your skill proficiencies with which you lack Expertise. You gain Expertise in those skills.	KEY:Ranger ~ Expertise									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Expertise|2																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01l	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Tireless	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Primal forces now help fuel you on your journeys, granting you the following benefits. &nl; Temporary Hit Points. As a Magic action, you can give yourself a number of Temporary Hit Points equal to 1d8 plus your Wisdom modifier (minimum of 1). You can use this action a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; Decrease Exhaustion. Whenever you finish a Short Rest, your Exhaustion level, if any, decreases by 1.	KEY:Ranger ~ Tireless																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01m	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Relentless Hunter	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Taking damage can't break your Concentration on Hunter's Mark.	KEY:Ranger ~ Relentless Hunter																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01n	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Nature's Veil	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You invoke spirits of nature to magically hide yourself. As a Bonus Action, you can give yourself the Invisible condition until the end of your next turn. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Ranger ~ Nature's Veil	DESC:%1/day|NatureSVeilTimes			DEFINE:NatureSVeilTimes|0					BONUS:VAR|NatureSVeilTimes|max(1,WIS)																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01o	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Precise Hunter	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have Advantage on attack rolls against the creature currently marked by your Hunter's Mark.	KEY:Ranger ~ Precise Hunter																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01p	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Feral Senses	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your connection to the forces of nature grants you Blindsight with a range of 30 feet.	KEY:Ranger ~ Feral Senses									BONUS:VAR|BlindsightRange|30																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01q	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Epic Boon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain an Epic Boon feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. Boon of Dimensional Travel is recommended.	KEY:Ranger ~ Epic Boon									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Epic_Boon|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01r	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Foe Slayer	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The damage die of your Hunter's Mark is a d10 rather than a d6.	KEY:Ranger ~ Foe Slayer																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01s	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
### Ranger Cantrips																																
Druidcraft	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip		DESC:Whispering to the spirits of nature, you create one of the following effects within range:&nl;- You create a tiny, harmless sensory effect that predicts what the weather will be at your location for the next 24 hours. The effect might manifest as a golden orb for clear skies, a cloud for rain, falling snowflakes for snow, and so on. This effect persists for 1 round.&nl;- You instantly make a flower blossom, a seed pod open, or a leaf bud bloom.&nl;- You create an instantaneous, harmless sensor effect, such as falling leaves, a puff of wind, the sound of a small animal, or the faint odor of skunk. The effect must fit in a 5-foot cube.&nl;- You instantly light or snuff out a candle, a torch, or a small campfire.	KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Druidcraft																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Druidcraft,RangerSpellDC	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Druidcraft								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Elementalism	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip			KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Elementalism																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Elementalism,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Elementalism								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Guidance	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip		DESC:You touch one willing creature. Once before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one ability check of its choice. It can roll the die before or after making the ability check. The spell then ends.	KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Guidance																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Guidance,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Guidance								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Mending	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip		DESC:This spell repairs a single break or tear in an object you touch, such as a broken chain link, two halves of a broken key, a torn cloak, or a leaking wineskin. As long as the break or tear is no larger than 1 foot in any dimension, you mend it. leaving no trace of the former damage. This spell can physically repair a magic item or construct, but the spell can't restore magic to such an object.	KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Mending																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mending,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Mending								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Message	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip		DESC:You point your finger toward a creature within range and whisper a message. The target (and only the target) hears the message and can reply in a whisper that only you can hear. You can cast this spell through solid objects if you are familiar with the target and know it is beyond the barrier. Magical silence. 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood blocks the spell. The spell doesn't have to follow a straight line and can travel freely around corners or through openings.	KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Message																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Message,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Message								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Poison Spray	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip		DESC:You extend your hand toward a creature you can see within range and project a puff of noxious gas from your palm. The creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take 1d12 poison damage. This spell's damage increases by 1d12 when you reach 5th level (2d12), 11th level (3d12), and 17th level (4d12).	KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Poison Spray																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Poison Spray,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Poison Spray								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Produce Flame	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip		DESC:A flicking flame appears in our hand. The flame remains there for the duration and harms neither you nor your equipment. The flame sheds bright light in a 10-foot radius and dim light for an additional 10 feet. The spell ends if you dismiss it as an action or if you cast it again.&nl;You can also attack with the flame, although doing so ends the spell. When you cast this spell, or as an action on a later turn, you can hurl the flame at a creature within 30 feet of you. Make a ranged spell attack. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 fire damage.&nl;This spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).	KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Produce Flame																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Produce Flame,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Produce Flame								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Resistance	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip		DESC:You touch one willing creature. Once before the spell ends, the target can roll a d4 and add the number rolled to one saving throw of its choice. It can roll the die before or after making the saving throw. The spell then ends.	KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Resistance																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Resistance,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Resistance								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Shillelagh	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip		DESC:The wood of a club or quarterstaff you are holding is imbued with nature's power. For the duration, you can use your spellcasting ability instead of Streangth for the attack and damage rolls of melee attacks using that weapon, and the weapon's damage die becomes a d8. The weapon also becomes magical, if it isn't already. The spell ends if you cast it again or if you let go of the weapon.	KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Shillelagh																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Shillelagh,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Shillelagh								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Spare the Dying	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip		DESC:You touch a living creature that has 0 hit points. The creature becomes stable. This spell has no effect on undead or constructs.	KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Spare the Dying																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Spare the Dying,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Spare the Dying								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Starry Wisp	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip			KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Starry Wisp																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Starry Wisp,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Starry Wisp								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Thunderclap	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip			KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Thunderclap																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Thunderclap,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Thunderclap								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Thorn Whip	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Ranger Cantrip		DESC:You create a long, vine-like whip covered in thorns that lashes out at your command toward a creature in range. Make a melee spell attack against the target. If the attack hits, the creature takes 1d6 piercing damage, and if the creature is Large or smaller, you pull the creature up to 10 feet closer to you.&nl;This spell's damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th elvel (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).	KEY:Ranger Cantrip ~ Thorn Whip																		SPELLS:Ranger Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Thorn Whip,SpellDC_WIS	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Ranger=0|Thorn Whip								SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
