###Block:Ranger Subclass																																
Beastmaster	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Ranger Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A Beast Master forms a mystical bond with a special animal, drawing on primal magic and a deep connection to the natural world.	KEY:Ranger Subclass ~ Beastmaster																		ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Beastmaster ~ Primal Companion|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,3	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Beastmaster ~ Exceptional Training|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,7	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Beastmaster ~ Bestial Fury|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,11	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Beastmaster ~ Share Spell|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,15					SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Fey Wanderer	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Ranger Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A fey mystique surrounds you, thanks to the boon of an archfey or a location in the Fey wild that transformed you. However you gained fey magic, you are now a Fey Wanderer. Your joyful laughter brightens the hearts of the downtrodden, and your martial prowess strikes terror in your foes, for great is the mirth of the fey and dreadful is their fury.	KEY:Ranger Subclass ~ Fey Wanderer																		ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Fey Wanderer ~ Dreadful Strikes|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,3	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Fey Wanderer ~ Spells|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,3	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Fey Wanderer ~ Otherwordly Glamour|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,3	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Fey Wanderer ~ Beguiling Twist|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,7	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Fey Wanderer ~ Fey Reinforcement|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,11	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Fey Wanderer ~ Misty Wanderer|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,15			SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Gloom Stalker	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Ranger Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Gloom Stalkers are at home in the darkest places, wielding magic drawn from the Shadowfell to combat enemies that lurk in darkness.	KEY:Ranger Subclass ~ Gloom Stalker																		ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Gloom Stalker ~ Dread Ambusher|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,3	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Gloom Stalker ~ Spells|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,3	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Gloom Stalker ~ Umbral Sight|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,3	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Gloom Stalker ~ Iron Mind|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,7	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Gloom Stalker ~ Stalker's Flurry|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,11	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Gloom Stalker ~ Shadowy Dodge|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,15			SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Hunter	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Ranger Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You stalk prey in the wilds and elsewhere, using your abilities as a Hunter to protect nature and people everywhere from forces that would destroy them.	KEY:Ranger Subclass ~ Hunter																		ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Hunter ~ Hunter's Lore|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,3	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Hunter ~ Hunter's Prey|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,3	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Hunter ~ Defensive Tactics|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,7	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Hunter ~ Superior Hunter's Prey|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,11	ABILITY:Ranger Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Hunter ~ Superior Hunter's Defense|PREVAREQ:RangerLVL,15				SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Primal Companion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Beastmaster.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You magically summon a primal beast, which draws strength from your bond with nature. Choose its stat block: Beast of the Land, Beast of the Sea, or Beast of the Sky. You also determine the kind of animal it is, choosing a kind appropriate for the stat block. Whatever beast you choose, it bears primal markings indicating its supernatural origin. The beast is Friendly to you and your allies and obeys your commands. It vanishes if you die. &nl; The Beast in Combat. In combat, the beast acts during your turn. It can move and use its Reaction on its own, but the only action it takes is the Dodge action unless you take a Bonus Action to command it to take an action in its stat block or some other action. You can also sacrifice one of your attacks when you take the Attack action to command the beast to take the Beast's Strike action. If you have the Incapacitated condition, the beast acts on its own and isn't limited to the Dodge action. &nl; Restoring or Replacing the Beast. If the beast has died within the last hour, you can take a Magic action to touch it and expend a spell slot. The beast returns to life after 1 minute with all its Hit Points restored. &nl; Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can summon a different primal beast, which appears in an unoccupied space within 5 feet of you. You choose its stat block and appearance. If you already have a beast from this feature, the old one vanishes when the new one appears.	KEY:Beastmaster ~ Primal Companion									BONUS:VAR|PrimalCompanionLVL|RangerLVL									ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Primal Companion								SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f1a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Exceptional Training	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Beastmaster.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Primal Companion beast to take an action, you can also command it to take the Dash, Disengage, Dodge, or Help action using its Bonus Action. In addition, whenever it hits with an attack roll and deals damage, it can deal your choice of Force damage or its normal damage type.	KEY:Beastmaster ~ Exceptional Training																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f1b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Bestial Fury	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Beastmaster.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you command your Primal Companion beast to take the Beast's Strike action, the beast can use it twice. In addition, the first time each turn it hits a creature under the effect of your Hunter's Mark spell, the beast deals extra Force damage equal to the bonus damage of that spell.	KEY:Beastmaster ~ Bestial Fury																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f1c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Share Spell	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Beastmaster.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast a spell targeting yourself, you can also affect your Primal Companion beast with the spell if the beast is within 30 feet of you.	KEY:Beastmaster ~ Share Spell																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f1d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Dreadful Strikes	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Fey Wanderer.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can augment your weapon strikes with mind-scarring magic drawn from the murky hollows of the Fey wild. When you hit a creature with a weapon, you can deal an extra ld4 Psychic damage to the target, which can take this extra damage only once per turn. The extra damage increases to ld6 when you reach Ranger level 11.	KEY:Fey Wanderer ~ Dreadful Strikes	DESC:+1d%1 psychic damage|DreadfulStrikeDie			DEFINE:DreadfulStrikeDie|0					BONUS:VAR|DreadfulStrikeDie|4	BONUS:VAR|DreadfulStrikeDie|2|PREVARGTEQ:RangerLVL,11															ASPECT:CombatBonus|+1d%1 psychic damage once per round.|DreadfulStrikeDie	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Fey Wanderer.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you reach a Ranger level specified in the Fey Wanderer Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared. &nl; You also possess a fey blessing. Choose it from the Feywild Gifts table or determine it randomly.	KEY:Fey Wanderer ~ Spells									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Fey_Gift|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Otherworldy Glamour	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Fey Wanderer.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever you make a Charisma check, you gain a bonus to the check equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of +1). You also gain proficiency in one of these skills of your choice: Deception, Performance, or Persuasion	KEY:Fey Wanderer ~ Otherwordly Glamour	DESC:+%1 Charisma check|OtherwordlyGlamourBonus			DEFINE:OtherworldlyGlamourBonus|0					BONUS:VAR|POOL_Otherwordly_Glamour|1	BONUS:VAR|OtherwordlyGlamourBonus|max(1,CHA)																SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Beguiling Twist	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Fey Wanderer.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The magic of the Fey wild guards your mind. You have Advantage on saving throws to avoid or end the Charmed or Frightened condition. In addition, whenever you or a creature you can see within 120 feet of you succeeds on a saving throw to avoid or end the Charmed or Frightened condition, you can take a Reaction to force a different creature you can see within 120 feet of yourself to make a Wisdom save against your spell save DC. On a failed save, the target is Charmed or Frightened (your choice) for 1 minute. The target repeats the save at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.	KEY:Fey Wanderer ~ Beguiling Twist																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Fey Reinforcement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Fey Wanderer.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast Summon Fey without a Material component. You can also cast it once without a spell slot, and you regain the ability to cast it in this way when you finish a Long Rest. Whenever you start casting the spell, you can modify it so that it doesn't require Concentration. If you do so, the spell's duration becomes 1 minute for that casting.	KEY:Fey Wanderer ~ Fey Reinforcement																		SPELLS:Fey Reinforcement|TIMES=1|Summon Fey								SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Misty Wanderer	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Fey Wanderer.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast Misty Step without expending a spell slot. You can do so a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. In addition, whenever you cast Misty Step, you can bring along one willing creature you can see within 5 feet of yourself. That creature teleports to an unoccupied space of your choice within 5 feet of your destination space.	KEY:Fey Wanderer ~ Misty Wanderer																		SPELLS:Misty Wanderer|TIMES=max(1,WIS)|Misty Step								SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Butterflies	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fey Gift.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Illusory butterflies flutter around you while you take a Short or Long Rest.	KEY:Fey Gift ~ Butterfly																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2b1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Flowers	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fey Gift.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Flowers bloom from your hair each dawn.	KEY:Fey Gift ~ Flower																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2b2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Smell	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fey Gift.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You faintly smell of cinnamon, lavender, nutmeg, or another comforting herb or spice.	KEY:Fey Gift ~ Smell																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2b3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Shadows	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fey Gift.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your shadow dances while no one is looking directly at it.	KEY:Fey Gift ~ Shadow																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2b4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Horns	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fey Gift.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Horns or antlers sprout from your head.	KEY:Fey Gift ~ Horn																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2b5	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Skin	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Fey Gift.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your skin and hair change color each dawn.	KEY:Fey Gift ~ Skin																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f2b6	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Dread Ambusher	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Gloom Stalker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have mastered the art of creating fearsome ambushes, granting you the following benefits. &nl; Ambusher's Leap. At the start of your first turn of each combat, your Speed increases by 10 feet until the end of that turn. &nl; Dreadful Strike. When you attack a creature and hit it with a weapon, you can deal an extra 2d6 Psychic damage. You can use this benefit only once per turn, you can use it a number of times equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; Initiative Bonus. When you roll Initiative, you can add your Wisdom modifier to the roll.	KEY:Gloom Stalker ~ Dread Ambusher				DEFINE:DreadAmbusherDie|0	DEFINE:DreadAmbusherTimes|0				BONUS:VAR|DreadAmbusherTimes|WIS	BONUS:COMBAT|INITIATIVE|WIS	BONUS:VAR|DreadAmbusherDie|6														ASPECT:CombatBonus|+2d%1 psychic damage once per round %2 times before longrest.|DreadAmbusherDie|DreadAmbusherTimes	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f3a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Gloom Stalker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you reach a Ranger level specified in the Gloom Stalker Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Gloom Stalker ~ Spells																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f3b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Umbral Sight	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Gloom Stalker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain Darkvision with a range of 60 feet. If you already have Darkvision when you gain this feature, its range increases by 60 feet. You are also adept at evading creatures that rely on Darkvision. While entirely in Darkness, you have the Invisible condition to any creature that relies on Darkvision to see you in that Darkness.	KEY:Gloom Stalker ~ Umbral Sight									BONUS:VAR|DarkvisionRange|60																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f3c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Iron Mind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Gloom Stalker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have honed your ability to resist mind-altering powers. You gain proficiency in Wisdom saving throws. If you already have this proficiency, you instead gain proficiency in Intelligence or Charisma saving throws (your choice).	KEY:Gloom Stalker ~ Iron Mind									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Iron_Mind|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f3d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Stalker's Flurry	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Gloom Stalker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The Psychic damage of your Dreadful Strike becomes 2d8. In addition, when you use the Dreadful Strike effect of your Dread Ambusher feature, you can cause one of the following additional effects. &nl; Sudden Strike. You can make another attack with the same weapon against a different creature that is within 5 feet of the original target and that is within the weapon's range. &nl; Mass Fear. The target and each creature within 10 feet of it must make a Wisdom saving throw against your spell save DC. On a failed save, a creature has the Frightened condition until the start of your next turn.	KEY:Gloom Stalker ~ Stalker's Flurry									BONUS:VAR|DreadAmbusherDie|2																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f3e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Shadowy Dodge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Gloom Stalker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When a creature makes an attack roll against you, you can take a Reaction to impose Disadvantage on that roll. Whether the attack hits or misses, you can then teleport up to 30 feet to an unoccupied space you can see.	KEY:Gloom Stalker ~ Shadowy Dodge																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f3f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Hunter's Lore	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Hunter.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can call on the forces of nature to reveal certain strengths and weaknesses of your prey. While a creature is marked by your Hunter's Mark, you know whether that creature has any Immunities, Resistances, or Vulnerabilities, and if the creature has any, you know what they are.	KEY:Hunter ~ Hunter's Lore																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f4a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Hunter's Prey	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Hunter.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain one of the following feature options of your choice. Whenever you finish a Short or Long Rest, you can replace the chosen option with the other one. &nl; Colossus Slayer. Your tenacity can wear down even the most resilient foes. When you hit a creature with a weapon, the weapon deals an extra 1d8 damage to the target if it's missing any of its Hit Points. You can deal this extra damage only once per turn. &nl; Horde Breaker. Once on each of your turns when you make an attack with a weapon, you can make another attack with the same weapon against a different creature that is within 5 feet of the original target, that is within the weapon's range, and that you haven't attacked this turn.	KEY:Hunter ~ Hunter's Prey									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Hunter_S_Prey|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f4b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Defensive Tactics	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Hunter.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain one of the following feature options of your choice. Whenever you finish a Short or Long Rest, you can replace the chosen option with the other one. &nl; Escape the Horde. Opportunity Attacks have Disadvantage against you. &nl; Multiattack Defense. When a creature hits you with an attack roll, that creature has Disadvantage on all other attack rolls against you this turn.	KEY:Hunter ~ Defensive Tactics									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Defensive_Tactics|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f4c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Superior Hunter's Prey	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Hunter.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Once per turn when you deal damage to a creature marked by your Hunter's Mark, you can also deal that spell's extra damage to a different creature that you can see within 30 feet of the first creature.	KEY:Hunter ~ Superior Hunter's Prey																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f4d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Superior Hunter's Defense	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Ranger Class Feature.Class Feature.Hunter.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you take damage, you can take a Reaction to give yourself Resistance to that damage and any other damage of the same type until the end of the current turn.	KEY:Hunter ~ Superior Hunter's Defense																										SORTKEY:Class_Ranger_01f4e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block: Hunter's Prey																																
Colossus Slayer	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Hunter's Prey	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your tenacity can wear down even the most resilient foes. When you hit a creature with a weapon, the weapon deals an extra 1d8 damage to the target if it's missing any of its Hit Points. You can deal this extra damage only once per turn.	KEY:Hunter's Prey ~ Colossus Slayer																									ASPECT:CombatBonus|+1d8 damage to the target if it's missing any of its Hit Points		SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Horde Breaker	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Hunter's Prey	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Once on each of your turns when you make an attack with a weapon, you can make another attack with the same weapon against a different creature that is within 5 feet of the original target, that is within the weapon's range, and that you haven't attacked this turn.	KEY:Hunter's Prey ~ Horde Breaker																											SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block: Defensive Tactics																																
Escape the Horde	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Defensive Tactics	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Opportunity Attacks have Disadvantage against you.	KEY:Defensive Tactics ~ Escape the Horde																											SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Multiattack Defense	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Defensive Tactics	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When a creature hits you with an attack roll, that creature has Disadvantage on all other attack rolls against you this turn.	KEY:Defensive Tactics ~ Multiattack Defense																											SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block:Abilities																																
Expertise	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain Expertise in two of your skill proficiencies of your choice. Sleight of Hand and Stealth are recommended if you have proficiency in them. At Rogue level 6, you gain Expertise in two more of your skill proficiencies of your choice.	KEY:Rogue ~ Expertise									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Expertise|2*((RogueLVL>=1)+(RogueLVL>=6))																	SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Sneak Attack	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You know how to strike subtly and exploit a foe's distraction. Once per turn, you can deal an extra 1d6 damage to one creature you hit with an attack roll if you have Advantage on the roll and the attack uses a Finesse or a Ranged weapon. The extra damage's type is the same as the weapon's type. You don't need Advantage on the attack roll if at least one of your allies is within 5 feet of the target, the ally doesn't have the Incapacitated condition, and you don't have Disadvantage on the attack roll. The extra damage increases as you gain Rogue levels, as shown in the Sneak Attack column of the Rogue Features table.	KEY:Rogue ~ Sneak Attack									BONUS:VAR|SneakAttack|(RogueLVL+1)/2									ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Sneak Attack								SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Thieves' Cant	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You picked up various languages in the communities where you plied your roguish talents. You know Thieves' Cant and one other language of your choice, which you choose from the language tables in chapter 2.	KEY:Rogue ~ Thieves' Cant									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Language|1	BONUS:VAR|RogueLanguage|1								ABILITY:Language|AUTOMATIC|Language ~ Thieves' Cant								SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Weapon Mastery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your training with weapons allows you to use the mastery properties of two kinds of weapons of your choice with which you have proficiency, such as Daggers and Shortbows. Whenever you finish a Long Rest, you can change the kinds of weapons you chose. For example, you could switch to using the mastery properties of Scimitars and Shortswords.	KEY:Rogue ~ Weapon Mastery	DESC:%1 weapon mastery.|WeaponMastery			DEFINE:WeaponMastery|0					BONUS:VAR|POOL_Weapon_Mastery|WeaponMastery	BONUS:VAR|WeaponMastery|2																SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Cunning Action	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your quick thinking and agility allow you to move and act quickly. On your turn, you can take one of the following actions as a Bonus Action: Dash, Disengage, or Hide.	KEY:Rogue ~ Cunning Action																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Rogue Subclass	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a Rogue subclass of your choice. The Arcane Trickster, Assassin, Soulknife, and Thief sub-classes are detailed after this class's description. A subclass is a specialization that grants you features at certain Rogue levels. For the rest of your career, you gain each of your subclass's features that are of your Rogue level or lower.	KEY:Rogue ~ Rogue Subclass									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Rogue_Subclass|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Steady Aim	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you give yourself Advantage on your next attack roll on the current turn. You can use this feature only if you haven't moved during this turn, and after you use it, your Speed is O until the end of the current turn.	KEY:Rogue ~ Steady Aim																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01g	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ability Score Improvement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the Ability Score Improvement feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. You gain this feature again at Rogue levels 8, 10, 12, and 16.	KEY:Rogue ~ Ability Score Improvement									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Feat|1*((RogueLVL>=4)+(RogueLVL>=8)+(RogueLVL>=10)+(RogueLVL>=12)+(RogueLVL>=16))																	SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01h	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Cunning Strike	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You've developed cunning ways to use your Sneak Attack. When you deal Sneak Attack damage, you can add one of the following Cunning Strike effects. Each effect has a die cost, which is the number of Sneak Attack damage dice you must forgo to add the effect. You remove the die before rolling, and the effect occurs immediately after the attack's damage is dealt. For example, if you add the Poison effect, remove ld6 from the Sneak Attack's damage before rolling. If a Cunning Strike effect requires a saving throw, the DC equals 8 plus your Dexterity modifier and Proficiency Bonus. &nl; Poison (Cost: 1d6). You add a toxin to your strike, forcing the target to make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, the target has the Poisoned condition for 1 minute. At the end of each of its turns, the Poisoned target repeats the save, ending the effect on itself on a success. To use this effect, you must have a Poisoner's Kit on your person. &nl; Trip (Cost: 1d6). If the target is Large or smaller, it must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or have the Prone condition. &nl; Withdraw (Cost: 1d6). Immediately after the attack, you move up to half your Speed without provoking opportunity Attacks.	KEY:Rogue ~ Cunning Strike																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01i	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Uncanny Dodge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Uncanny Dodge	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When an attacker that you can see hits you with an attack roll , you can take a Reaction to halve the attack's damage against you (round down).	KEY:Rogue ~ Uncanny Dodge																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01j	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Evasion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Evasion	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can nimbly dodge out of the way of certain dangers. When you're subjected to an effect that allows you to make a Dexterity saving throw to take only half damage, you instead take no damage if you succeed on the saving throw and only half damage if you fail. You can't use this feature if you have the Incapacitat ed condition.	KEY:Rogue ~ Evasion																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01k	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Reliable Talent	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever you make an ability check that uses one of your skill or tool proficiencie s, you can treat a d20 roll of 9 or lower as a 10.	KEY:Rogue ~ Reliable Talent																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01l	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Improved Cunning Strike	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can use up to two Cunning Strike effects when you deal Sneak Attack damage, paying the die cost for each effect.	KEY:Rogue ~ Improved Cunning Strike																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01m	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Devious Strike	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You've practiced new ways to use your Sneak At- tack deviously. The following effects are now among your Cunning Strike options. &nl; Daze (Cost: 2d6). The target must succeed on a Constitutio n saving throw, or on its next turn, it can do only one of the following: move or take an action or a Bonus Action. &nl; Knock Out (Cost: 6d6). The target must succeed on a Constitutio n saving throw, or it has the Unconscious condition for 1 minute or until it takes any damage. The Unconsciou s target repeats the save at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. &nl; Obscure (Cost: 3d6). The target must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw, or it has the Blinded condi- tion until the end of its next turn.	KEY:Rogue ~ Devious Strike																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01n	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Slippery Mind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your cunning mind is exceptional ly difficult to control. You gain proficiency in Wisdom and Charisma saving throws.	KEY:Rogue ~ Slippery Mind																		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Saving Throw ~ Wis|Saving Throw ~ Cha								SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01o	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Elusive	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You're so evasive that attackers rarely gain the upper hand against you. No attack roll can have Advantage against you unless you have the Incapacitated condition.	KEY:Rogue ~ Elusive																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01p	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Epic Boon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain an Epic Boon feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. Boon of the Night Spirit is recommended.	KEY:Rogue ~ Epic Boon									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Epic_Boon|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01q	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Stroke of Luck	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have a marvelous knack for succeeding when you need to. If you fail a D20 Test, you can turn the roll into a 20. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Short or Long Rest.	KEY:Rogue ~ Stroke of Luck																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01r	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
###Block:Rogue Subclass																																
Arcane Trickster	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Rogue Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Some Rogues enhance their fine-honed skills of stealth and agility with spells, learning magical tricks to aid them in their trade. Some Arcane Tricksters use their talents as pickpockets and burglars, while others are pranksters.	KEY:Rogue Subclass ~ Arcane Trickster																		ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Arcane Trickster ~ Spellcasting|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,3	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Arcane Trickster ~ Mage Hand Legerdemain|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,3	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Arcane Trickster ~ Magical Ambush|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,9	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Arcane Trickster ~ Versatile Trickster|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,13	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Arcane Trickster ~ Spell Thief|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,17				SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Assassin	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Rogue Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:An Assassin's training focuse s on usi ng stealth, poison, and disguise to eliminate foe s with deadly efficiency. While some Rogues who fol low this path are hired killers, spies , or bounty hunters , the capabilities of this subclass are equally us e ful for adventurers facing a variety of monstrous enemies.	KEY:Rogue Subclass ~ Assassin																		ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Assassin ~ Assassinate|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,3	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Assassin ~ Assassin's Tools|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,3	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Assassin ~ Infiltration Expertise|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,9	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Assassin ~ Envenom Weapon|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,13	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Assassin ~ Death Strike|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,17				SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Soulknife	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Rogue Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A Soulknife strikes with the mind, cutting through barriers both physical and psychic. These Rogues discover psionic power within themselves and channel it to do their roguish work. As a Soulknife your psionic abilities might have haunted you since childhood. revealing their full potential only as you experienced the stress of adventure. Or you might have sought out an order of psychic adepts and spent years learning how to manifest your power.	KEY:Rogue Subclass ~ Soulknife																		ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Soulknife ~ Psionic Power|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,3	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Soulknife ~ Psychic Blade|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,3	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Soulknife ~ Soul Blade|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,9	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Soulknife ~ Psychic Veil|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,13	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Soulknife ~ Rend Mind|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,17				SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Thief	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Rogue Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A mix of burglar, treasure hunter, and explorer, you are the epitome of an adventurer. In addition to improving your agility and stealth, you gain abilities useful for delving into ruins and getting maximum benefit from the magic items you find there.	KEY:Rogue Subclass ~ Thief																		ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Thief ~ Fast Hands|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,3	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Thief ~ Second-Story Work|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,3	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Thief ~ Supreme Sneak|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,9	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Thief ~ Use Magic Device|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,13	ABILITY:Rogue Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Thief ~ Thief's Reflexes|PREVAREQ:RogueLVL,17				SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

Spellcasting	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Arcane Trickster.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have learned to cast spells. See chapter 7 for the rules on spellcasting. The information below details how you use those rules as an Arcane Trickster. &nl; Cantrips. You know three cantrips: Mage Hand and two other can trips of your choice from the Wizard spell list (see that class's section for its list). Mind Sliver and Minor Illusion are recommended. Whenever you gain a Rogue level, you can replace one of your cantrips, except Mage Hand, with another Wizard can trip of your choice. When you reach Rogue level 10, you learn another Wizard cantrip of your choice. &nl; Spell Slots. The Arcane Trickster Spellcasting table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your level 1+ spells. You regain all expended spell slots when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; Prepared Spells of Level 1+. You prepare the list of level 1+ spells that are available for you to cast with this feature. To start, choose three level 1 Wizard spells. Charm Person, Disguise Self, and Fog Cloud are recommended . The number of spells on your list increases as you gain Rogue levels, as shown in the Prepared Spells column of the Arcane Trickster Spellcasting table. Whenever that number increases, choose additional Wizard spells until the number of spells on your list matches the number in the Arcane Trickster Spellcasting table. The chosen spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots. For example, if you're a level 7 Rogue, your list of prepared spells can include five Wizard spells of level 1 or 2 in any combination.&nl; Changing Your Prepared Spells. Whenever you gain a Rogue level, you can replace one spell on your fist with another Wizard spell for which you have spell slots.&nl; Spellcasting Ability. Intelligence is your spellcasting ability for your Wizard spells. &nl; Spellcasting Focus. You can use an Arcane Focus as a Spellcasting Focus for your Wizard spells. Spell save DC %1; Spell attack modifier +%2|8+Proficiency_Bonus+INT|Proficiency_Bonus+INT	KEY:Arcane Trickster ~ Spellcasting				DEFINE:POOL_Arcane_Trickster_Cantrip|0					BONUS:VAR|POOL_Arcane_Trickster_Cantrip|3																	SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f1a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Mage Hand Legerdemain	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Arcane Trickster.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast Mage Hand, you can cast it as a Bonus Action, and you can make the spectral hand Invisible. You can control the hand as a Bonus Action, and through it, you can make Dexterity (Sleight of Hand) checks.	KEY:Arcane Trickster ~ Mage Hand Legerdemain																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f1b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Magical Ambush	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Arcane Trickster.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If you have the Invisible condition when you cast a spell on a creature, it has Disadvantage on any saving throw it makes against the spell on the same turn.	KEY:Arcane Trickster ~ Magical Ambush																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f1c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Versatile Trickster	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Arcane Trickster.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the ability to distract targets with your Mage Hand. When you use the Trip option of your Cunning Strike on a creature, you can also use that option on another creature within 5 feet of the spectral hand.	KEY:Arcane Trickster ~ Versatile Trickster																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f1d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Spell Thief	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Arcane Trickster.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the ability to magically steal the knowledge of how to cast a spell from another spellcaster. Immediately after a creature casts a spell that targets you or includes you in its area of effect, you can take a Reaction to force the creature to make an Intelligence saving throw. The DC equals your spell save DC. On a failed save, you negate the spell's effect against you, and you steal the knowledge of the spell if it is at least level 1 and of a level you can cast (it doesn't need to be a Wizard spell). For the next 8 hours, you have the spell prepared. The creature can't cast it until the 8 hours have passed. Once you steal a spell with this feature, you can't use this feature again until you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Arcane Trickster ~ Spell Thief																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f1e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Arcane Trickster ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:RogueCast1|0	DEFINE:RogueKnown1|0	BONUS:VAR|RogueCast1|SpellSlotsLVL1																													
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Arcane Trickster ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:RogueCast2|0	DEFINE:RogueKnown2|0	BONUS:VAR|RogueCast2|SpellSlotsLVL2																													
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Arcane Trickster ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:RogueCast3|0	DEFINE:RogueKnown3|0	BONUS:VAR|RogueCast3|SpellSlotsLVL3																													
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Arcane Trickster ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:RogueCast4|0	DEFINE:RogueKnown4|0	BONUS:VAR|RogueCast4|SpellSlotsLVL4																													
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Arcane Trickster ~ Spellcasting.MOD	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Rogue Known Progression Selection|1																															
																																
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Arcane Trickster ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:RoguePreparedSlots|0	BONUS:SPELLCAST|CLASS=Rogue;LEVEL=10|RoguePreparedSlots	BONUS:VAR|RoguePreparedSlots|RoguePreparedBase																													
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Arcane Trickster ~ Spellcasting.MOD	DEFINE:RoguePreparedBase|0	BONUS:VAR|RoguePreparedBase|2+RogueLVL-(RogueLVL>=5)-(RogueLVL>=6)-(RogueLVL>=9)-(RogueLVL>=12)-(RogueLVL>=15)-(RogueLVL>=17)-(RogueLVL>=18)																														
																																
###Block: Choose Rogue Known Progression																																
Grant Highest Known only	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Rogue Known Progression	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:This will manipulate your spells known to increase to the max highest allowed by the rules.	KEY:Rogue Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only																											
Follow Standard Progression	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Rogue Known Progression	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:This will follow the progression chart in the Player's Handbook.	KEY:Rogue Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression																											
Choose Own Progression	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Rogue Known Progression	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:This will force the user to select spells each level.	KEY:Rogue Known Progression ~ Choose Own Progression				BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Rogue Known|if(RogueLVL>=3,3,0)+(RogueLVL>=4)+(RogueLVL>=7)+(RogueLVL>=8)+(RogueLVL>=10)+(RogueLVL>=11)+(RogueLVL>=13)+(RogueLVL>=14)+(RogueLVL>=16)+(RogueLVL>=19)+(RogueLVL>=20)																							
#																																
# Grant Highest Known																																
CATEGORY=Internal|Rogue Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|RogueKnown1|if(RogueLVL>=3,2,0)+(RogueLVL>=4)-3*(RogueLVL>=7)																															
CATEGORY=Internal|Rogue Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|RogueKnown2|if(RogueLVL>=7,6,0)+(RogueLVL>=10)-3*(RogueLVL>=13)																															
CATEGORY=Internal|Rogue Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|RogueKnown3|if(RogueLVL>=13,9,0)+(RogueLVL>=16)-10*(RogueLVL>=19)																															
CATEGORY=Internal|Rogue Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|RogueKnown4|if(RogueLVL>=19,11,0)																															
#																																
# Follow Standard Progression																																
CATEGORY=Internal|Rogue Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|RogueKnown1|if(RogueLVL>=3,2,0)+(RogueLVL>=4)+(RogueLVL>=7)																															
CATEGORY=Internal|Rogue Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|RogueKnown2|if(RogueLVL>=7,2,0)+(RogueLVL>=10)																															
CATEGORY=Internal|Rogue Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|RogueKnown3|if(RogueLVL>=13,2,0)+(RogueLVL>=16)																															
CATEGORY=Internal|Rogue Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|RogueKnown4|(RogueLVL>=19)																															
#																																
# Choose Own Progression																																
Rogue Known Level 1	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Rogue Known	PREVARGTEQ:RogueLVL,3	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|RogueKnown1|1																									
Rogue Known Level 2	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Rogue Known	PREVARGTEQ:RogueLVL,7	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|RogueKnown2|1																									
Rogue Known Level 3	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Rogue Known	PREVARGTEQ:RogueLVL,13	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|RogueKnown3|1																									
Rogue Known Level 4	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Rogue Known	PREVARGTEQ:RogueLVL,19	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|RogueKnown4|1																									
																																
Assassinate	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Assassin.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You're adept at ambushing a target, granting you the following benefits. &nl; Initiative. You have Advantage on Initiative rolls. &nl; Surprising Strikes. During the first round of each combat, you have Advantage on attack rolls against any creature that hasn't taken a turn . If your Sneak Attack hits any target during that round, the target takes extra damage of the weapon's type equal to your Rogue level.	KEY:Assassin ~ Assassinate																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f2a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Assassin's Tools	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Assassin.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a Disguise Kit and a Poisoner's Kit, and you have proficiency with them.	KEY:Assassin ~ Assassin's Tools																		ABILITY:Internal|AUTOMATIC|Tool Proficiency ~ Disguise Kit|Tool Proficiency ~ Poisoner's Kit								SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f2b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Infiltration Expertise	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Assassin.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You are expert at the following techniques that aid your infiltrations. &nl; Masterful Mimicry. You can unerringly mimic another person's speech, handwri t ing, or both if you have spent at least 1 hour studying them. &nl; Roving Aim. Your Speed isn't reduc ed to 0 by using Steady Aim.	KEY:Assassin ~ Infiltration Expertise																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f2c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Envenom Weapon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Assassin.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you use the Poison option of your Cunning Strike, the target also takes 2d6 Poison damage whenever it fails the saving throw. This damage ignores Resistance to Poison damage.	KEY:Assassin ~ Envenom Weapon																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f2d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Death Strike	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Assassin.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you hit with your Sneak Attack on the first round of a combat, the target must succeed on a Constitution saving throw (DC 8 plus your Dexterity modifier and Proficiency Bonus), or the attack's damage is doubled against the target.	KEY:Assassin ~ Death Strike	DESC:&nl; DC %1.|DeathStrikeDC			DEFINE:DeathStrikeDC|0					BONUS:VAR|DeathStrikeDC|SpellDC_DEX|TYPE=Base																	SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f2e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
																																
Psionic Power	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Soulknife.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You harbor a wellspring of psionic energy within yourself. It is represented by your Psionic Energy Dice, which fuel certain powers you have from this subclass. The Soulknife Energy Dice table shows the number of these dice you have when you reach certain Rogue levels, and the table shows the die size Any features in this subclass that use a Psionic Energy Die use only the dice from this subclass. Some of you r powers ex pend a Psionic Energy Die, as specified in a power's description, and you can't use a power if it requires you to use a die when your Psion ic Energy Dice are all expended. You regain one of your expended Psionic Energy Dice when you finish a Short Rest, and you regain all of them when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; Psi-Bolstered Knack If you fail an ability check using a skill or tool with which you have proficiency, you can roll one Psionic Energy Die and add the number rolled to the check, potentially turning failure into success. The die is expended only if the roll then succeeds. &nl; Psychic Whispers. You can establish telepathic communication between yourself and others. As a Magic ac t ion, choose one or more creatures you can see, up to a number of creatures equal to your Proficiency Bonus, and then roll one Psionic Energy Die. For a number of hours equal to the number rolled , the chosen creatures can speak telepathically with you . and you can speak telepathically with them. To send or receive a message (no action required), you ,, nd the other creature must be within 1 mile of each other. A creature can end the telepathic connection at any time (no action required). The first time you use this power after each Long Rest, you don't expend the Psionic Energy Die. All other times you use the power, you expend the die.	KEY:Soulknife ~ Psionic Power	DESC:&nl; Soulknife Energy Dice %1d%2.|EnergyDice|EnergyDiceSize			DEFINE:EnergyDice|0	DEFINE:EnergyDiceSize|0				BONUS:VAR|EnergyDice|(((RogueLVL+7)/4)*2)|TYPE=Base	BONUS:VAR|EnergyDiceSize|(((RogueLVL+19)/6)*2)|TYPE=Base																SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f3a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Psychic Blades	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Soulknife.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can manifest shimmering blades of psychic energy. Whenever you take the Attack action or make an Opportunity Attack, you can manifest a Psychic Blade in your free hand and make the attack with that blade. The blade vanishes immediately after it hits or misses its target, and it leaves no mark if it deals damage. After you attack with the blade on your turn, you can make a melee or ranged attack with a second psychic blade as a Bonus Action on the same turn if your other hand is free to create it. The damage die of this bonus attack is ld4 instead of ld6.	KEY:Soulknife ~ Psychic Blade				DEFINE:PsychicBlade|0					BONUS:VAR|PsychicBlade|1|TYPE=Base							AUTO:EQUIP|Psychic Blade										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f3b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Soul Blades	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Soulknife.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can now use the following powers with your Psychic Blades. &nl; Homing Strikes. If you make an attack roll with your Psychic Blade and miss the target, you can roll one Psionic Energy Die and add the number rolled to the attack roll. If this causes the attack to hit, the die is expended. &nl; Psychic Teleportation. As a Bonus Action . you manifest a Psychic Blade, expend on e Psionic Energy Die and roll it, and throw the blade at an unoccupied space you can see up to a number of effect away equal to 10 times the numb e r roll ed . You then teleport to that space, and the bl a de vanishes.	KEY:Soulknife ~ Soul Blade																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f3c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	
Psychic Veil	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Soulknife.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can weave a veil of psychic static to mask yourself. As a Magic action, you gain the Invi sible condition for 1 hour or until you dismiss this effect (no action required). This invisibility ends early immediately after you deal damage to a creature or you force a creature to make a saving throw. Once you use this feature , you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest unless you expend a Psionic Energy Die (no action required) to restore your use of it.	KEY:Soulknife ~ Psychic Veil																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f3d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	
Rend Mind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Soulknife.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can sweep your Psychic Blades through a creature's mind. When you use your Psychic Blades to deal Sneak Attack damage to a creature, you can force that target to make a Wisdom saving throw (DC 8 plus your Dexterity modifier and Proficiency Bonus). If the save fails , the target has the Stunned condition for 1 minute. The Stunned target repeats the save at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. Once you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest unless you expend three Psionic Energy Dice (no action required) to restore your use of it.	KEY:Soulknife ~ Rend Mind																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f3e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	

Fast Hands	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Thief.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can do one of the following. &nl; Sleight of Hand. Make a Dexterity (Sleight of Hand) check to pick a lock or disarm a trap with Thieves' Tools or to pick a pocket. &nl; Use an Object. Take the Utilize action , or take the Magic action to use a magic item that requires that action.	KEY:Thief ~ Fast Hands																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f4a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Second-Story Work	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Thief.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You've trained to get into especially hard-to-reach places, granting you these benefits. &nl; Climber. You gain a Climb Speed equal to your Speed. &nl; Jumper. You can determine your jump distance using your Dexterity rather than your Strength	KEY:Thief ~ Second-Story Work	MOVECLONE:Walk,Climb,*1																									SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f4b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Supreme Sneak	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Thief.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the following Cunning Strike option. &nl; Stealth Attack (Cost: 1d6). If you have the Hide action's Invisible condition, this attack doesn't end that condition on you if you end the turn behind Three-Quarters Cover or Total Cover.	KEY:Thief ~ Supreme Sneak																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f4c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Use Magic Device	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Thief.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You've learned how to maximize use of magic items, granting you the following benefits. &nl; Attunement. You can attune to up to four magic items at once. &nl; Charges. Whenever you use a magic item property that expends charges, roll ld6. On a roll of 6, you use the property without expending the charges. &nl;Scrolls. You can use any Spell Scroll, using Intelligence as your spellcasting ability for the spell. If the spell is a cantrip or a level 1 spell, you can cast it reliably. If the scroll contains a higher-level spell, you must first succeed on an Intelligence (Arcana) check (DC 10 plus the spell's level). On a successful check, you cast the spell from the scroll. On a failed check, the scroll disintegrates.	KEY:Thief ~ Use Magic Device										BONUS:VAR|Attuned_Item_Max|1|TYPE=Class																SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f4d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Thief's Reflexes	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Rogue Class Feature.Class Feature.Thief.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You are adept at laying ambushes and quickly escaping danger. You can take two turns during the first round of any combat. You take your first turn at your normal Initiative and your second turn at your Initiative minus 10 .	KEY:Thief ~ Thief's Reflexes																										SORTKEY:Class_Rogue_01f4e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

###Block:Abilities																																
Spellcasting	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Drawing from your innate magic, you can cast spells. See chapter 7 for the rules on spellcasting. The information below details how you use those rules with Sorcerer spells, which appear in the Sorcerer spell list later in the class's description. Cantrips. You know four Sorcerer cantrips of your choice. Light, Prestidigitation, Shocking Grasp, and Sorcerous Burst are recommended. Whenever you gain a Sorcerer level, you can replace one of your cantrips from this feature with another Sorcerer cant rip of your choice. When you reach Sorcerer levels 4 and 10, you learn another Sorcerer can trip of your choice, as shown in the Cantrips column of the Sorcerer Features table. &nl; Spell Slots. The Sorcerer Features table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your level 1+ spells. You regain all expended slots when you finish a Long Rest. &nl; Prepared Spells of Level 1+. You prepare the list of level 1+ spells that are available for you to cast with this feature. To start, choose two level 1 Sor- cerer spells. Burning Hands and Detect Magic are recommended. The number of spells on your list increases as you gain Sorcerer levels, as shown in the Prepared Spells column of the Sorcerer Features table. Whenever that number increases, choose additional Sorcerer spells until the number of spells on your list matches the number in the Sorcerer Features table. The chosen spells must be of a level for which you have spell slots. For example, if you're a level 3 Sorcerer, your list of prepared spells can include six Sorcerer spells of level 1 or 2 in any combination. If another Sorcerer feature gives you spells that you always have prepared, those spells don't count against the number of spells you can prepare with this feature, but those spells otherwise count as Sorcerer spells for you. &nl; Changing Your Prepared Spells. Whenever you gain a Sorcerer level, you can replace one spell on your list with another Sorcerer spell for which you have spell slots. &nl; Spellcasting Ability. Charisma is your spellcasting ability for your Sorcerer spells. &nl; Spellcasting Focus. You can use an Arcane Focus as a Spellcasting Focus for your Sorcerer spells. Spell save DC %1; Spell attack modifier +%2|SorcererSpellDC|Proficiency_Bonus+CHA	KEY:Sorcerer ~ Spellcasting				DEFINE:SorcererSpellDC|0					BONUS:VAR|SorcererSpellDC|SpellDC_CHA																	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Innate Sorcery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:An event in your past left an indelible mark on you, infusing you with simmering magic. As a Bonus Action, you can unleash that magic for 1 minute, during which you gain the following benefits: &nl; - The spell save DC of your Sorcerer spells increases by 1. &nl; - You have Advantage on t he attack rolls of Sorcerer spells you cast. &nl; You can use this feature twice , and you regain all expended uses of it when you fin ish a Long Rest.	KEY:Sorcerer ~ Innate Sorcery																										SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Font of Magic	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can tap into the wellspring of m agic within yourself. This wellspring is represented by Sorcery Points, which allow you to create a var iety of magical effects. You have 2 Sorcery Points, and you gain more as you reach higher levels, as shown in the Sorcery Points column of the Sorcerer Features table. You can't have more Sorcery Points than the number shown in the table for your level. You regain all expended Sorcery Points when you finish a Long Rest. You can use your Sorcery Points to fuel the options below, along with other features, such as Metamagic, that use those points. &nl; Converting Spell Slots to Sorcery Points. You can expend a spell slot to gain a number of Sorcery Points equal to the slot's level (no action required). &nl; Creating Spell Slots. As a Bonus Action, you can transform unexpended Sorcery Points into one spell slot. The Creating Spell Slots table shows the cost of creating a spell slot of a given level, and it lists the minimum Sorcerer level you must be to create a slot. You can create a spell slot no higher than level 5. &nl; Any spell slot you create with this feature vanishes when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Sorcerer ~ Font of Magic					DEFINE:SorceryPoints|0					BONUS:VAR|SorceryPoints|SorcererLVL																SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Metamagic		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Because your magic flows from within, you can alter your spells to suit your needs; you gain two Metamagic options of your choice from "Metamagic Options" later in this class's description. You use the chosen options to temporarily modify spells you cast. To use an option, you must spend the num- ber of Sorcery Points that it costs. You can use only one Metamagic option on a spell when you cast it unless otherwise noted in one of those options. Whenever you gain a Sorcerer level, you can replace one of your Meta magic options with one you don't know. You gain two more options at Sorcerer level 10 and two more at Sorcerer level 17.	KEY:Sorcerer ~ Metamagic									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Metamagic|2+2*(SorcererLVL>=10)+2*(SorcererLVL>=17)																	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Sorcerer Subclass		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a Sorcerer subclass of your choice. The Aberrant Sorcery, Clockwork Sorcery, Draconic Sorcery, a nd Wild Magic Sorcery subclasses are detailed after this class's description. A subclass is a specialization that grants you features at certain Sorcerer levels. For the rest of your career, you gain each of yo ur subclass's features that are of your Sorcerer level or lower.	KEY:Sorcerer ~ Sorcerer Subclass									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Sorcerer_Subclass|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ability Score Improvement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the Ability Score Improvement feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. You gain this feature again at Sorcerer levels 8,12, and 16.	KEY:Sorcerer ~ Ability Score Improvement									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Feat|1*((SorcererLVL>=4)+(SorcererLVL>=8)+(SorcererLVL>=12)+(SorcererLVL>=16))																	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Sorcerous Restoration	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you finish a Short Rest, you can regain expended Sorcery Points, but no more than a number equal to half your Sorcerer level (round down). Once you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Sorcerer ~ Sorcerous Restoration																										SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01g	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Sorcery Incarnate		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If you have no uses of Innate Sorcery left, you can use it if you spend 2 Sorcery Points when you take the Bonus Action to activate it. In addition, while your Innate Sorcery feature is active, you can use up to two of your Meta magic options on each spell you cast.	KEY:Sorcerer ~ Sorcery Incarnate																										SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01h	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Epic Boon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain an Epic Boon feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. Boon of Dimensional Travel is recommended.	KEY:Sorcerer ~ Epic Boon									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Epic_Boon|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01i	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Arcane Apotheosis		CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:While your Innate Sorcery feature is active, you can use one Meta magic option on each of your turns without spending Sorcery Points on it.	KEY:Sorcerer ~ Arcane Apotheosis																										SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01j	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

