###Block: Sorcerer Cantrips
Acid Splash								KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Acid Splash						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Acid Splash,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Acid Splash		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You hurl a bubble of acid. Choose one creature within range, or choose two creatures within range that are within 5 feet of each other. A target must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take 1d6 acid damage. This spell's damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).
Blade Ward								KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Blade Ward						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Blade Ward,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Blade Ward		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You extend your hand and trace a sigil of warding in the air. Until the end of your next turn, you have resistance against bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage dealt by weapon attacks.
Chill Touch								KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Chill Touch						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Chill Touch,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Chill Touch		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You create a ghostly, skeletal hand in the space of a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the creature to assail it with the chill of the grave. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 necrotic damage, and it can't regain hit points until the start of your next turn. Until then, the hand clings to the target. If you hit an undead target, it also has disadvantage on attack rolls against you until the end of your next turn. This spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).
Dancing Lights							KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Dancing Lights					CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Dancing Lights,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Dancing Lights		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You create up to four torch-sized lights within range, making them appear as torches, lanterns, or glowing orbs that hover in the air for the duration. You can also combine the four lights into one glowing vaguely humanoid form of Medium size. Whichever form you choose, each light sheds dim light in a 10-foot radius. As a bonus action on your turn, you can move the lights up to 60 feet to a new spot within range. A light must be within 20 feet of another light created by this spell, and a light winks out if it exceeds the spell's range.
Elementalism							KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Elementalism						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Elementalism,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Elementalism			SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You exert control over the elements, creating one of the following effects within range.
Fire Bolt								KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Fire Bolt						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Fire Bolt,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Fire Bolt		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You hurl a mote of fire at a creature or object within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, the target takes 1d10 fire damage. A flammable object hit by this spell ignites if it isn't being worn or carried. This spell's damage increases by 1d10 when you reach 5th level (2d10), 11th level (3d10), and 17th level (4d10).
Friends								KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Friends						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Friends,SpellDC_CHA				SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Friends		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:For the duration, you have advantage on all Charisma checks directed at one creature of your choice that isn't hostile toward you. When the spell ends, the creature realizes that you used magic to influence its mood and becomes hostile toward you. A creature prone to violence might attack you. Another creature might seek retribution in other ways (at the DM's discretion), depending on the nature of your interaction with it.
Light									KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Light							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Light,SpellDC_CHA				SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Light		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You touch one object that is no larger than 10 feet in any dimension. Until the spell ends, the object sheds bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light for an additional 20 feet. The light can be colored as you like. Completely covering the object with something opaque blocks the light. The spell ends if you cast it again or dismiss it as an action. If you target an object held or worn by a hostile creature, that creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw to avoid the spell.
Mage Hand								KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Mage Hand						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mage Hand,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Mage Hand		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:A spectral, floating hand appears at a point you choose within range. The hand lasts for the duration or until you dismiss it as an action. The hand vanishes if it is ever more than 30 feet away from you or if you cast this spell again. You can use your action to control the hand. You can use the hand to manipulate an object, open an unlocked door or container, stow or retrieve an item from an open container, or pour the contents out of a vial. You can move the hand up to 30 feet each time you use it. The hand can't attack, activate magic items, or carry more than 10 pounds.
Mending								KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Mending						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mending,SpellDC_CHA				SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Mending		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:This spell repairs a single break or tear in an object you touch, such as a broken chain link, two halves of a broken key, a torn cloak, or a leaking wineskin. As long as the break or tear is no larger than 1 foot in any dimension, you mend it. leaving no trace of the former damage. This spell can physically repair a magic item or construct, but the spell can't restore magic to such an object.
Message								KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Message						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Message,SpellDC_CHA				SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Message		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You point your finger toward a creature within range and whisper a message. The target (and only the target) hears the message and can reply in a whisper that only you can hear. You can cast this spell through solid objects if you are familiar with the target and know it is beyond the barrier. Magical silence. 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood blocks the spell. The spell doesn't have to follow a straight line and can travel freely around corners or through openings.
Mind Silver								KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Mind Sliver					CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mind Sliver,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Mind Sliver		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You drive a disorienting spike of psychic energy into the mind of one creature you can see within range. The target must succeed on an Intelligence saving throw or take 1d6 psychic damage and subtract 1 from the next saving throw it makes before the end of your next turn. This spell's damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).
Minor Illusion							KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Minor Illusion					CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Minor Illusion,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Minor Illusion	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You create a sound or an image of an object within range that lasts for the duration. The illusion also ends if you dismiss it as an action or cast this spell again. If you create a sound, its volume can range from a whisper to a scream. It can be your voice, someone else's voice, a lion's roar, a beating of drums, or any other sound you choose. The sound continues unabated throughout the duration, or you can make discrete sounds at different times before the spell ends. If you create an image of an object-such as a chair, muddy footprints, or a small chest-it must be no larger than a 5-foot cube. The image can't create sound, light, smell, or any other sensory effect. Physical interaction with the image reveals it to be an illusion, because things can pass through it. If a creature uses its action to examine the sound or image, the creature can determine that it is an illusion with a successful Intelligence (Investigation) check against your spell save DC. If a creature discerns the illusion for what it is, the illusion becomes faint to the creature.
Poison Spray							KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Poison Spray						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Poison Spray,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Poison Spray	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You extend your hand toward a creature you can see within range and project a puff of noxious gas from your palm. The creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take 1d12 poison damage. This spell's damage increases by 1d12 when you reach 5th level (2d12), 11th level (3d12), and 17th level (4d12).
Prestidigitation							KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Prestidigitation					CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Prestidigitation,SpellDC_CHA		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Prestidigitation	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:This spell is a minor magical trick that novice spellcasters use for practice. You create one of the following magical effects within range: * You create an instantaneous, harmless sensory effect, such as a shower of sparks, a puff of wind, faint musical notes, or an odd odor. * You instantaneously light or snuff out a candle, a torch, or a small campfire. * You instantaneously clean or soil an object no larger than 1 cubic foot. * You chill, warm, or flavor up to 1 cubic foot of nonliving material for 1 hour. * You make a color, a small mark, or a symbol appear on an object or a surface for 1 hour. * You create a nonmagical trinket or an illusory image that can fit in your hand and that lasts until the end of your next turn. If you cast this spell multiple times, you can have up to three of its non-instantaneous effects active at a time, and you can dismiss such an effect as an action.
Ray of Frost							KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Ray of Frost						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Ray of Frost,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Ray of Frost	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:A frigid beam of blue-white light streaks toward a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, it takes 1d8 cold damage, and its speed is reduced by 10 feet until the start of your next turn. The spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).
Shocking Grasp							KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Shocking Grasp					CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Shocking Grasp,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Shocking Grasp		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:Lightning springs from your hand to deliver a shock to a creature you try to touch. Make a melee spell attack against the target. You have advantage on the attack roll if the target is wearing armor made of metal. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 lightning damage, and it can't take reactions until the start of its next turn. The spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).
Sorcerous Burst							KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Sorcerous Burst					CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Sorcerous Burst,SpellDC_CHA		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Sorcerous Burst	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You cast sorcerous energy at one creature or object within range. Make a ranged attack roll against the target. On a hit, the target takes ld8 damage of a type you choose: Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, Poison, Psychic, or Thunder. If you roll an 8 on a d8 for this spell, you can roll another d8, and add it to the damage. When you cast this spell, the maximum number of these d8s you can add to the spell's damage equals your spellcasting ability modifier. Cantrip Upgrade. The damage increases by 1d8 when you reach levels S (2d8), 11 (3d8), and 17 (4d8).
Thunderclaps							KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ Thunderclaps					CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Thunderclaps,SpellDC_CHA		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|Thunderclaps		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:Each creature in a 5-foot Emanation originating from you must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take ld6 Thunder damage. The spell's thunderous sound can be heard up to 100 feet away. Cantrip Upgrade. The damage increases by ld6 when you reach levels 5 (2d6), 11 (3d6), and 17 (4d6).
True Strike								KEY:Sorcerer Cantrip ~ True Strike						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Sorcerer Cantrip																SPELLS:Sorcerer Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|True Strike,SpellDC_CHA			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Sorcerer=0|True Strike		SOURCEPAGE:PHB	DESC:You extend your hand and point a finger at a target in range. Your magic grants you a brief insight into the target's defenses. On your next turn, you gain advantage on your first attack roll against the target, provided that this spell hasn't ended.

###Block: Metamagic
Careful Spell	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Metamagic.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast a spell that forces other creatures to make a saving throw, you can protect some of those creatures from the spell's full force. To do so, spend 1 Sorcery Point and choose a number of those creatures up to your Charisma modifier (minimum of one creature). A chosen creature automatically succeeds on its saving throw against the spell, and it takes no damage if it would normally take half damage on a successful save.	KEY:Metamagic ~ Careful Spell																									ADDSPELLLEVEL:0	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01d1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Distant Spell	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Metamagic.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast a spell that has a range of at least 5 feet, you can spend 1 Sorcery Point to double the spell's range. Or when you cast a spell that has a range of Touch, you can spend 1 Sorcery Point to make the spell's range 30 feet.	KEY:Metamagic ~ Distant Spell																									ADDSPELLLEVEL:0	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01d2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Empowered Spell	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Metamagic.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you roll damage for a spell, you can spend 1 Sorcery Point to reroll a number of the damage dice up to your Charisma modifier (minimum of one), and you must use the new rolls. You can use Empowered Spell even if you've already used a different Metamagic option during the casting of the spell.	KEY:Metamagic ~ Empowered Spell																									ADDSPELLLEVEL:0	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01d3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Extended Spell	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Metamagic.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast a spell that has a duration of 1 minute or longer, you can spend 1 Sorcery Point to double its duration to a maximum duration of 24 hours. If the affected spell requires Concentration, you have Advantage on any saving throw you make to maintain that Concentration.	KEY:Metamagic ~ Extended Spell																									ADDSPELLLEVEL:0	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01d4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Heightened Spell	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Metamagic.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast a spell that forces a creature to make a saving throw, you ca n spend 2 Sorcery Points to give one target of the spell Disadva ntage on saves against the spell.	KEY:Metamagic ~ Heightened Spell																									ADDSPELLLEVEL:0	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01d5	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Quickened Spell	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Metamagic.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast a spell that has a casting tim e of an action , you can spend 2 Sorcery Points to ch ange the casting time to a Bonus Action for thi s casting. You can't modify a spell in this way if you've already cast a level 1+ spell on the current turn , nor ca n you cast a level 1+ spell on this turn after modifying a spell in this way.	KEY:Metamagic ~ Quickened Spell																									ADDSPELLLEVEL:0	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01d6	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Seeking Spell	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Metamagic.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:If you make an attack roll for a spell and miss, you can spend 1 Sorcery Point to reroll the d20, and you must use the new roll. You can use Seeking Spell even if you've already used a different Metamagic option during the casting of the spell.	KEY:Metamagic ~ Seeking Spell																									ADDSPELLLEVEL:0	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01d7	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Subtle Spell	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Metamagic.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast a spell, you can spend 1 Sorcery Point to cast it without any Verbal, Somatic , or Material components, except Material components that are consumed by the spell or that have a cost specified in the spell.	KEY:Metamagic ~ Subtle Spell																									ADDSPELLLEVEL:0	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01d8	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Transmuted Spell	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Metamagic.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast a spell that deals a type of damage from the following list, you can spend 1 Sorcery Point to change that damage type to one of the other listed types: Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, Poison, Thunder.	KEY:Metamagic ~ Transmuted Spell																									ADDSPELLLEVEL:0	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01d9	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Twinned Spell	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Metamagic.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast a spell, such as Cha rm Person, that can be cast with a higher-level spell slot to target an additional creature, you can spend 1 Sorcery Point to increase the spell's effective level by 1.	KEY:Metamagic ~ Twinned Spell																									ADDSPELLLEVEL:0	SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01d10	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

###Block:Sorcerer Subclass																																
Aberrant Sorcery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Sorcerer Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:An alien influence has wrapped its tendrils around your mind, giving you psionic power. You can now touch other minds with that power and alter the world around you. Will this power shine from you as a hopeful beacon to others? Or will you be a terror to those who feel the stab of your mind? Perhaps a psychic wind from the Astral Plane carried psionic energy to you, or you were exposed to the Far Realm's warping influence. Alternatively, you were implanted with a mind flayer tadpole, but your transformation into a mind flayer never occurred; now the tadpole's psionic power is yours. However you acquired this power, your mind is aflame with it.	KEY:Sorcerer Subclass ~ Aberrant Sorcery																		ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Aberrant Sorcery ~ Psionic Spells|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,3	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Aberrant Sorcery ~ Telepathic Speech|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,3	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Aberrant Sorcery ~ Psionic Sorcery|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,6	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Aberrant Sorcery ~ Psychic Defenses|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,6	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Aberrant Sorcery ~ Revelation in Flesh|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,14	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Aberrant Sorcery ~ Warping Implosion|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,18			SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Clockwork Sorcery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Sorcerer Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The cosmic force of order has suffused you with magic. That power arises from Mechanus or a realm like it - a plane of existence sh aped entirely by clockwork efficiency. You or someone from you r lineage might have become entangled in the m achinations of modrons, the orderly beings who inhabit Mechanus. Perhaps your ancestor even took part in the Great Modron March. Wh atever its origin within you , the power of order can seem strange to others, but for you, it's part of a vast and glorious system.	KEY:Sorcerer Subclass ~ Clockwork Sorcery																		ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Clockwork Sorcery ~ Clockwork Spells|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,3	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Clockwork Sorcery ~ Restore Balance|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,3	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Clockwork Sorcery ~ Bastion of Law|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,6	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Clockwork Sorcery ~ Trance of Order|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,14	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Clockwork Sorcery ~ Clockwork Cavalcade|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,18				SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Draconic Sorcery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Sorcerer Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your innate magic comes from the gift of a dragon. Perhaps an ancient dragon facing death bequeathed some of its magical power to you or your ancestor. You might have absorbed magic from a site infused with dragons' power. Or perhaps you handled a treasure taken from a dragon's hoard that was steeped in draconic power. Or you might have a dragon for an ancestor.	KEY:Sorcerer Subclass ~ Draconic Sorcery																		ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Draconic Sorcery ~ Draconic Spells|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,3	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Draconic Sorcery ~ Draconic Resilience|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,3	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Draconic Sorcery ~ Elemental Affinity|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,6	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Draconic Sorcery ~ Dragon Wings|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,14	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Draconic Sorcery ~ Dragon Companion|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,18				SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Wild Magic Sorcery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Sorcerer Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your innate magic comes from the forces of chaos and unpredictability. Perhaps you were born during a magical storm, or you were exposed to the raw power of the Weave in some other way. Maybe your magic is the result of a curse, or it was bestowed on you by a trickster god. Whatever its origin, your magic is wild and untamed, and it can erupt with unexpected effects.	KEY:Sorcerer Subclass ~ Wild Magic Sorcery																		ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Wild Magic Sorcery ~ Wild Magic Surge|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,3	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Wild Magic Sorcery ~ Tides of Chaos|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,3	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Wild Magic Sorcery ~ Bend Luck|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,6	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Wild Magic Sorcery ~ Controlled Chaos|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,14	ABILITY:Sorcerer Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Wild Magic Sorcery ~ Tamed Surge|PREVAREQ:SorcererLVL,18			SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

Psionic Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Aberrant Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you reach a Sorcerer level specified in the Psionic Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Aberrant Sorcery ~ Psionic Spells														SPELLS:Psionic Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Arms of Hadar,SpellDC_CHA|Calm Emotions,SpellDC_CHA|Detect Thoughts,SpellDC_CHA|Dissonant Whispers,SpellDC_CHA|Mind Sliver,SpellDC_CHA|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,3	SPELLS:Psionic Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Hunger of Hadar,SpellDC_CHA|Sending|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,5	SPELLS:Psionic Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Evard's Black Tentacles,SpellDC_CHA|Summon Aberration|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,7	SPELLS:Psionic Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Rary's Telepathic Bond,SpellDC_CHA|Telekinesis|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,9										SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f1a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Telepathic Speech	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Aberrant Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can form a telepathic connection between your mind and the mind of another. As a Bonus Action, choose one creature you can see within 30 feet of yourself. You and the chosen creature can communicate telepathically with each other while the two of you a r e within a number of miles of each other equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of 1 mile). To understand each other, you each must mentally use a language the other knows. The telepathic connection lasts for a number of minutes equal to your Sorcerer level. It ends early if you use t h is ability to form a connection with a differen t creature.	KEY:Aberrant Sorcery ~ Telepathic Speech																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f1b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Psionic Sorcery	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Aberrant Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast any level 1+ spell from your Psionic Spells feature , you can cast it by expending a spell slot as normal or by spending a number of Sorcery Points equal to the spell's level. If you cast the spell using Sorcery Points, it requires no Verbal or Somatic components, and it requires no Material components unless they are consumed by the spell or have a cost specified in it.	KEY:Aberrant Sorcery ~ Psionic Sorcery																										SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f1c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Psychic Defenses	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Aberrant Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have Resistance to Psychic damage, and you have Advantage on saving throws to avoid or end the Charmed or Frightened condition.	KEY:Aberrant Sorcery ~ Psychic Defenses																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f1d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Revelation in Flesh	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Aberrant Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can unleash the aberrant truth hidden within yourself. As a Bonus Action, you can spend 1 Sorcery Point or more to magically alter your body for 10 minutes. For each Sorcery Point you spend, you gain one of the following benefits of your choice, the effects of which last until the alteration ends. &nl; Aquatic Adaptation. You gain a Swim Speed equal to hvice your Speed, and you can breathe underwater. Gills grow from your neck or flare behind your ears, and your fingers become webbed or you grow wriggling cilia. &nl; Glistening Flight. You gain a Fly Speed equal to your Speed, and you can hover. As you fly, your skin glistens with mucus or otherworldly light. &nl; See the Invisible. You can see any Invisible creature within 60 feet of yourself that isn't behind Total Cover. Your eyes also turn black or become writhing sensory tendrils. &nl; Wormlike Movement. Your body, along with any equipment you are wearing or carrying, becomes slimy and pliable. You can move through any space as narrow as 1 inch, and you can spend 5 feet of movement to escape from nonmagical restraints or the Grappled condition.	KEY:Aberrant Sorcery ~ Revelation in Flesh																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f1e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Warping Implosion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Aberrant Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can unleash the full force of the alien power within you, causing a burst of warping energy to radiate from you. As an Action, you can spend 6 Sorcery Points to create a burst of warping energy that emanates from you in a 30-foot radius and is centered on you. Each creature of your choice in that area must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take 10d6 Psychic damage and be pulled 10 feet toward the center of the burst. A creature that succeeds on its saving throw takes half as much damage and isn't pulled toward the center of the burst.	KEY:Aberrant Sorcery ~ Warping Implosion																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f1f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

Clockwork Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Clockwork Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you reach a Sorcerer level specified in th e Clockwork Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared. In addition, consult the Manifestations of Order table and choose or randomly determine a way your connection to order manifests while you are casting any of your Sorcerer spells. &nl; <b>MANIFESTATIONS OF ORDER</b> &nl; 1d6 - Manifestation &nl; 1 - Spectral cogwheels hover behind you. &nl; 2 - The hands of a clock spin in your eyes. &nl; 3 - Your skin glows with a brassy sheen. &nl; 4 - Floating equations and geometric objects overlay your body. &nl; 5 - Your Spellcasting Focus temporarily takes the form of a Tiny clockwork mechanism. &nl; 6 - The ticking of gears or ringing of a clock can be heard by you and those affecte d by your magic.	KEY:Clockwork Sorcery ~ Clockwork Spells														SPELLS:Clockworks Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Arms of Hadar,SpellDC_CHA|Aid,SpellDC_CHA|Alarm,SpellDC_CHA|Lesser Restoration,SpellDC_CHA|Protection from Evil and Good,SpellDC_CHA|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,3	SPELLS:Clockwork Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Dispel Magic,SpellDC_CHA|Protection from Energy,SpellDC_CHA|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,5	SPELLS:Clockwork Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Freedom of Movement|Summon Construct|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,7	SPELLS:Clockwork Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Greater Restoration,SpellDC_CHA|Wall of Force|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,9										SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f2a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Restore Balance	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Clockwork Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your connection to the plane of absolute order allows you to equalize chaotic moments. When a creature you can see within 60 feet of your self is about to roll a d20 with Advantage or Disadvantage, you can take a Reaction to prevent the roll from being affected by Advantage and Disadvantage. You can use this feature a number of times equal to your Cha risma modifier (minimum of once), and you regain all expended uses when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Clockwork Sorcery ~ Restore Balance																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f2b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Bastion of Law	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Clockwork Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can tap into the grand equation of existence to imbue a creature with a shimmering shield of order. As a Magic action, you can expend 1 to 5 Sorcery Points to create a magical ward around yourself or another creature you can see within 30 feet of yourself. The ward is represented by a number of d8s equal to the number of Sorcery Points spent to create it. When the warded creature takes damage, it can expend a number of those dice, roll them, and reduce the damage taken by the total rolled on those dice. The ward lasts until you finish a Long Rest or until you use this feature again.	KEY:Clockwork Sorcery ~ Bastion of Law																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f2c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Trance of Order	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Clockwork Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the ability to align your consciousness with the endless calculations of Mechanus. As a Bonus Action, you can enter this state for 1 minute. For the duration, attack rolls against you can't benefit from Advantage, and whenever you make a D20 Test, you can treat a roll of 9 or lower on the d20 as a 10. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest unless you spend 5 Sorcery Points (no action required) to restore your use of it.	KEY:Clockwork Sorcery ~ Trance of Order																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f2d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	
Clockwork Cavalcade	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Clockwork Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You momentarily summon spirits of order to expunge disorder around you. As a Magic action, you summon the spirits in a 30-foot Cube originating from you. The spirits look like modrons or other Constructs of your choice. The spirits are intangible and invulnerable, and they create the effects below within the Cube before vanishing. Once you use this action, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest unless you spend 7 Sorcery Points (no action required) to restore your use of it. &nl; Heal. The spirits restore up to 100 Hit Points, divided as you choose among any number of creatures of your choice in the Cube. &nl; Repair. Any damaged objects entirely in the Cube are repaired instantly. &nl; Dispel. Every spell of level 6 and lower ends on creatures a nd objects of your choice in the Cube.	KEY:Clockwork Sorcery ~ Clockwork Cavalcade																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f2e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

Draconic Resilience	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Draconic Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The magic in your body manifests physical traits of your draconic gift. Your Hit Point maximum increases by 3, and it increases by 1 whenever you gain another Sorcerer level. Parts of you are also covered by dragon-like scales. While you aren't wearing armor, your base Armor Class equals 10 plus your Dexterity and Charisma modifiers.	KEY:Draconic Sorcery ~ Draconic Resilience						BONUS:HP|CURRENTMAX|SorcererLVL																			SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f3a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Draconic Spells	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Draconic Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you reach a Sorcerer level specified in the Draconic Spells table, you thereafter always have the listed spells prepared.	KEY:Draconic Sorcery ~ Draconic Spells														SPELLS:Draconic Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Alter Self|Chromatic Orb,SpellDC_CHA|Command,SpellDC_CHA|Dragon's Breath,SpellDC_CHA|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,3	SPELLS:Draconic Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Fear,SpellDC_CHA|Fly|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,5	SPELLS:Draconic Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Arcane Eye|Charm Monster|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,7	SPELLS:Draconic Spells|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Legend Lore|Summon Dragon|PREVARGTEQ:SorcererLVL,9										SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f3a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Elemental Affinity	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Draconic Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your draconic magic has an affinity with a damage type associated with dragons. Choose one of those types: Acid, Cold, Fire, Lightning, or Poison. You have Resistance to that damage type, and when you cast a spell that deals damage of that type, you can add your Charisma modifier to one damage roll of that spell.	KEY:Draconic Sorcery ~ Elemental Affinity						BONUS:VAR|POOL_Elemental_Affinity|1																			SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f3c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Dragon Wings	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Draconic Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action, you can cause draconic wings to appear on your back. The wings last for 1 hour or until you dismiss them (no action required). For the duration, you have a Fly Speed of 60 feet. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Long Rest unless you spend 3 Sorcery Points (no action required) to r estore your use of it.	KEY:Draconic Sorcery ~ Dragon Wings																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f3d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Dragon Companion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Draconic Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast Summon Dragon without a Material component. You can also cast it once without a spell slot, and yo u regain the ability to cast it in this way when you finish a Long Rest. Whenever you start casting the spell, you can modify it so that it doesn't require Concentration. If you do so, the spell's duration becomes 1 minute for that casting.	KEY:Draconic Sorcery ~ Dragon Companion														SPELLS:Dragon Companion|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=SorcererLVL|Summon Dragon											SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f3e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

Acid	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Elemental Affinity.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Resistance to Acid.	KEY:Elemental Affinity ~ Acid																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f3c1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Cold	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Elemental Affinity.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Resistance to Cold.	KEY:Elemental Affinity ~ Cold																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f3c2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Fire	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Elemental Affinity.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Resistance to Fire.	KEY:Elemental Affinity ~ Fire																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f3c3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Lightning	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Elemental Affinity.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Resistance to Lightning.	KEY:Elemental Affinity ~ Lightning																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f3c4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Poison	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Elemental Affinity.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Resistance to Poison.	KEY:Elemental Affinity ~ Poison																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f3c5	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

Wild Magic Surge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Wild Magic Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your spellcasting can unleash surges of untamed magic. Once per turn, you can roll ld20 immediately after you cast a Sorcerer spell with a spell slot. If you roll a 20, roll on the Wild Magic Surge table to create a magical effect. If the magical effect is a spell, it is too wild to be affected by you r Meta magic.	KEY:Wild Magic Sorcery ~ Wild Magic Surge																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f4a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Tides of Chaos	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Wild Magic Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can manipulate chaos itself to give yourself Advantage on one D20 Test before you roll the d20. Once you do so, you must cast a Sorcerer spell with a spell slot or finish a Long Rest before you can use this feature again. If you do cast a Sorcerer spell with a spell slot befor e you finish a Long Rest, you automatically roll on the Wild Magic Surge table.	KEY:Wild Magic Sorcery ~ Tides of Chaos																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f4b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Bend Luck	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Wild Magic Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have the ability to twist fate using your wild magic. Immediately after another creature you can see r olls t he d20 for a D20 Test, you can take a Reaction and spend 1 Sorcery Point to roll ld4 and apply the number rolled as a bonus or penalty (your choice) to the d20 roll.	KEY:Wild Magic Sorcery ~ Bend Luck																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f4c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Controlled Chaos	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Wild Magic Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a modic um of control over the surges of your wild magic. Whenever you roll on the Wild Magic Surge table, you can roll twice and use either number.	KEY:Wild Magic Sorcery ~ Controlled Chaos																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f4d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Tamed Surge	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Sorcerer Class Feature.Class Feature.Wild Magic Sorcery.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Immediately after you cast a Sorcerer spell with a spell slot, you can create an effect of your choice from the Wild Magic Surge table instead of rolling on that table. You can choose any effect in the table except for the final row, and if the chosen effect involves a roll, you must make it. Once you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Wild Magic Sorcery ~ Tamed Surge																									SORTKEY:Class_Sorcerer_01f4e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

###Block:Abilities																																
Eldritch Invocations	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Class Feature.Warlock Abilities.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have unearthed Eldritch Invocations, pieces of forbidden knowledge that imbue you with an abiding magical ability or other lessons. You gain one invocation of your choice, such as Pact of the Tome. Invocations are described in the "Eldritch Invocation Options" section later in this class's description. &nl;Prerequisites. If an invocation has a prerequisite, you must meet it to learn that invocation. For example, if an invocation requires you to be a level 5+ Warlock, you can select the invocation once you reach Warlock level 5. &nl; Replacing and Gaining Invocations. Whenever you gain a Warlock level, you can replace one of your invocations with another one for which you qualify. You can't replace an invocation if it's a prerequisite for another invocation that you have. When you gain certain Warlock levels, you gain more invocations of your choice, as shown in the Invocations column of the Warlock Features table. You can't pick the same invocation more than once unless its description says otherwise.	KEY:Warlock ~ Eldritch Invocations						BONUS:VAR|POOL_Eldritch_Invocation|1+2*(WarlockLVL>=2)+2*(WarlockLVL>=5)+2*(WarlockLVL>=7)+2*(WarlockLVL>=9)+2*(WarlockLVL>=12)+2*(WarlockLVL>=15)+2*(WarlockLVL>=18)																SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Pact Magic	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Class Feature.Warlock Abilities.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Through occult ceremony, you have formed a pact with a mysterious entity to gain magical powers. The entity is a voice in the shadows-its identity unclear-but its boon to you is concrete: the ability to cast spells. See chapter 7 for the rules on spell- casting. The information below details how you use those rules with Warlock spells, which appear in the Warlock spell list later in the class's description. &nl; Cantrips. You know two Warlock cantrips of your choice. Eldritch Blast and Prestidigitation are recommended. Whenever you gain a Warlock level, you can replace one of your cantrips from this feature with another Warlock can trip of your choice. When you reach Warlock levels 4 and 10, you learn another Warlock cantrip of your choice, as shown in the Cantrips column of the Warlock Features table. &nl; Spell Slots. The Warlock Features table shows how many spell slots you have to cast your Warlock spells of levels 1-5. The table also shows the level of those slots, all of which are the same level. You regain all expended Pact Magic spell slots when you finish a Short or Long Rest. For example, when you're a level 5 Warlock, you have two level 3 spell slots. To cast the level 1 spell Witch Bolt, you must spend one of those slots, and you cast it as a level 3 spell. &nl; Prepared Spells of Level 1+. You prepare the list of level 1+ spells that are available for you to cast with this feature. To start, choose two level 1 Warlock spells. Charm Person and Hex are recommended. The number of spells on your list increases as you gain Warlock levels, as shown in the Prepared Spells column of the Warlock Features table. Whenever that number increases, choose additional War- lock spells until the number of spells on your list matches the number in the table. The chosen spells must be of a level no higher than what's shown in the table's Slot Level column for your level. When you reach level 6, for example, you learn a new War- lock spell, which can be of levels 1-3. If another Warlock feature gives you spells that you always have prepared, those spells don't count against the number of spells you can prepare with this feature, but those spells otherwise count as Warlock spells for you. &nl; Changing Your Prepared Spells. Whenever you gain a Warlock level, you can replace one spell on your list with another Warlock spell of an eligible level. &nl; Spellcasting Ability. Charisma is the spellcasting ability for your Warlock spells. &nl; Spellcasting Focus. You can use an Arcane Focus as a Spellcasting Focus for your Warlock spells. Spell save DC %1; Spell attack modifier +%2|WarlockSpellDC|Proficiency_Bonus+CHA	KEY:Warlock ~ Pact Magic				DEFINE:WarlockSpellDC|0					BONUS:VAR|WarlockSpellDC|SpellDC_CHA																	SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Magical Cunning	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Class Feature.Warlock Abilities.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can perform an esoteric rite for 1 minute. At the end of it, you regain expended Pact Magic spell slots but no more than a number equal to half your maximum (round up). Once you use this feature, you can't do so again until you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Warlock ~ Magical Cunning																									SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Warlock Subclass	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Class Feature.Warlock Abilities.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain a Warlock subclass of your choice. The Archfey Patron, Celestial Patron , Fiend Patron, and Great Old One Patron subclasses are detailed after this class's description. A subcla ss is a specialization that grants you features at certain Warlock levels. For the rest of your career, you gain e:1ch of your subclass's features that are of you Warlock level or lower.	KEY:Warlock ~ Warlock Subclass									BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Warlock Subclass|1																SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ability Score Improvement	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the Ability Score Improvement feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. You gain this feature again at Warlock levels 8, 12, and 16.	KEY:Warlock ~ Ability Score Improvement									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Feat|1*((WarlockLVL>=4)+(WarlockLVL>=8)+(WarlockLVL>=12)+(WarlockLVL>=16))																	SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Contact Patron	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:In the past, you usually contacted your patron th rough intermediaries. Now you can communicate directly; you always have the Contact Other Plane spell prepa red. With this feature , you can cast the spell without expending a spell slot to contact your patron, and you automat ically succeed on the spell's saving throw. Once you cast the spell with this feature, you can't do so in this way again until you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Warlock ~ Contact Patron																	SPELLS:Contact Patron|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|Contact Other Plane								SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01f	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	
Mystic Arcanum	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your patron grants you a magical secret called an arcanum. Choose one level 6 Warlock spell as this arcanum. You can cast your arcanum spell once without expending a spell slot, and you must finish a Long Rest before you can cast it in this way again. As shown in the Warlock Features table, you gain anot her Warlock spell of your choice that can be cast in this way when you reach Warlock levels 13 (level 7 spell), 15 (level 8 spell), and 17 (level 9 spell). You regain all uses of your Mystic Arcanum when you finish a Long Rest. Whenever you gain a Warlock level, you can replace one of your arcanum spells with another Warlock spell of the same level.	KEY:Warlock ~ Mystic Arcanum									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Mystic_Arcanum_6|(WarlockLVL>=11)	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Mystic_Arcanum_7|(WarlockLVL>=13)	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Mystic_Arcanum_8|(WarlockLVL>=15)	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Mystic_Arcanum_9|(WarlockLVL>=17)													SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01g	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Epic Boon	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain an Epic Boon feat (see chapter 5) or another feat of your choice for which you qualify. Boon of Fate is recommended.	KEY:Warlock ~ Epic Boon									BONUS:VAR|POOL_Epic_Boon|1																	SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01h	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Eldritch Master	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Class Feature.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you use your Magical Cunning feature, you regain all your expended Pact Magic spell slots.	KEY:Warlock ~ Eldritch Master																									SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01i	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	

# Warlock Cantrips
Blade Ward								KEY:Warlock Cantrip ~ Blade Ward						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Cantrip																SPELLS:Warlock Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Blade Ward,WarlockSpellDC		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Warlock=0|Blade Ward		SOURCEPAGE:p.218	DESC:You extend your hand and trace a sigil of warding in the air. Until the end of your next turn, you have resistance against bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage dealt by weapon attacks.
Chill Touch								KEY:Warlock Cantrip ~ Chill Touch						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Cantrip																SPELLS:Warlock Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Chill Touch,WarlockSpellDC		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Warlock=0|Chill Touch		SOURCEPAGE:p.221	DESC:You create a ghostly, skeletal hand in the space of a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the creature to assail it with the chill of the grave. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 necrotic damage, and it can't regain hit points until the start of your next turn. Until then, the hand clings to the target. If you hit an undead target, it also has disadvantage on attack rolls against you until the end of your next turn. This spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).
Eldritch Blast							KEY:Warlock Cantrip ~ Eldritch Blast					CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Cantrip																SPELLS:Warlock Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Eldritch Blast,WarlockSpellDC		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Warlock=0|Eldritch Blast		SOURCEPAGE:p.237	DESC:A beam of crackling energy streaks toward a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, the target takes 1d10 force damage.&nl;The spell creates more than one beam when you reach high levels: two beams at 5th level, three beams at 11th level, and four beams at 17th level. You can direct the beams at the same target or at different ones. Make a separate attack roll for each beam.
Friends								KEY:Warlock Cantrip ~ Friends							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Cantrip																SPELLS:Warlock Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Friends,WarlockSpellDC			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Warlock=0|Friends		SOURCEPAGE:p.244	DESC:For the duration, you have advantage on all Charisma checks directed at one creature of your choice that isn't hostile toward you. When the spell ends, the creature realizes that you used magic to influence its mood and becomes hostile toward you. A creature prone to violence might attack you. Another creature might seek retribution in other ways (at the DM's discretion), depending on the nature of your interaction with it.
Mage Hand								KEY:Warlock Cantrip ~ Mage Hand						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Cantrip																SPELLS:Warlock Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mage Hand,WarlockSpellDC			SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Warlock=0|Mage Hand		SOURCEPAGE:p.256	DESC:A spectral, floating hand appears at a point you choose within range. The hand lasts for the duration or until you dismiss it as an action. The hand vanishes if it is ever more than 30 feet away from you or if you cast this spell again. You can use your action to control the hand. You can use the hand to manipulate an object, open an unlocked door or container, stow or retrieve an item from an open container, or pour the contents out of a vial. You can move the hand up to 30 feet each time you use it. The hand can't attack, activate magic items, or carry more than 10 pounds.
Mind Silver						KEY:Warlock Cantrip ~ Mind Sliver						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Cantrip																SPELLS:Warlock Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mind Sliver,WarlockSpellDC		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Warlock=0|Mind Sliver	SOURCEPAGE:p.260	DESC:You drive a disorienting spike of psychic energy into the mind of one creature you can see within range. The target must succeed on an Intelligence saving throw or take 1d6 psychic damage and subtract 1d4 from the next saving throw it makes before the end of your next turn. This spell's damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).
Minor Illusion							KEY:Warlock Cantrip ~ Minor Illusion					CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Cantrip																SPELLS:Warlock Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Minor Illusion,WarlockSpellDC		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Warlock=0|Minor Illusion	SOURCEPAGE:p.260	DESC:You create a sound or an image of an object within range that lasts for the duration. The illusion also ends if you dismiss it as an action or cast this spell again. If you create a sound, its volume can range from a whisper to a scream. It can be your voice, someone else's voice, a lion's roar, a beating of drums, or any other sound you choose. The sound continues unabated throughout the duration, or you can make discrete sounds at different times before the spell ends. If you create an image of an object-such as a chair, muddy footprints, or a small chest-it must be no larger than a 5-foot cube. The image can't create sound, light, smell, or any other sensory effect. Physical interaction with the image reveals it to be an illusion, because things can pass through it. If a creature uses its action to examine the sound or image, the creature can determine that it is an illusion with a successful Intelligence (Investigation) check against your spell save DC. If a creature discerns the illusion for what it is, the illusion becomes faint to the creature.
Poison Spray							KEY:Warlock Cantrip ~ Poison Spray						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Cantrip																SPELLS:Warlock Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Poison Spray,WarlockSpellDC		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Warlock=0|Poison Spray	SOURCEPAGE:p.266	DESC:You extend your hand toward a creature you can see within range and project a puff of noxious gas from your palm. The creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take 1d12 poison damage. This spell's damage increases by 1d12 when you reach 5th level (2d12), 11th level (3d12), and 17th level (4d12).
Prestidigitation							KEY:Warlock Cantrip ~ Prestidigitation					CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Cantrip																SPELLS:Warlock Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Prestidigitation,WarlockSpellDC	SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Warlock=0|Prestidigitation	SOURCEPAGE:p.267	DESC:This spell is a minor magical trick that novice spellcasters use for practice. You create one of the following magical effects within range: * You create an instantaneous, harmless sensory effect, such as a shower of sparks, a puff of wind, faint musical notes, or an odd odor. * You instantaneously light or snuff out a candle, a torch, or a small campfire. * You instantaneously clean or soil an object no larger than 1 cubic foot. * You chill, warm, or flavor up to 1 cubic foot of nonliving material for 1 hour. * You make a color, a small mark, or a symbol appear on an object or a surface for 1 hour. * You create a nonmagical trinket or an illusory image that can fit in your hand and that lasts until the end of your next turn. If you cast this spell multiple times, you can have up to three of its non-instantaneous effects active at a time, and you can dismiss such an effect as an action.
Thunderclap							KEY:Warlock Cantrip ~ Thunderclap						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Cantrip																SPELLS:Warlock Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Thunderclap,WarlockSpellDC		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Warlock=0|Thunderclap		SOURCEPAGE:p.283	DESC:You create a burst of thunderous sound that can be heard up to 100 feet away. Each creature other than you within 5 feet of you must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes 1d6 thunder damage. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage. This spell's damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).
Toll the Dead							KEY:Warlock Cantrip ~ Toll the Dead						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Cantrip																SPELLS:Warlock Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Toll the Dead,WarlockSpellDC		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Warlock=0|Toll the Dead		SOURCEPAGE:p.283	DESC:You point at a creature you can see within range, and the sound of a dolorous bell fills the air around it for a moment. The target must succeed on a Wisdom saving throw or take 1d8 necrotic damage. If the target is missing any of its hit points, it instead takes 1d12 necrotic damage. This spell's damage increases by 1d8 (or 1d12) when you reach 5th level (2d8 or 2d12), 11th level (3d8 or 3d12), and 17th level (4d8 or 4d12).
True Strike								KEY:Warlock Cantrip ~ True Strike						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Cantrip																SPELLS:Warlock Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|True Strike,WarlockSpellDC		SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Warlock=0|True Strike		SOURCEPAGE:p.284	DESC:You extend your hand and point a finger at a target in range. Your magic grants you a brief insight into the target's defenses. On your next turn, you gain advantage on your first attack roll against the target, provided that this spell hasn't ended.

CATEGORY=Special Ability|Warlock ~ Pact Magic.MOD		DEFINE:WarlockCast1|0	DEFINE:WarlockKnown1|0
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Warlock ~ Pact Magic.MOD		DEFINE:WarlockCast2|0	DEFINE:WarlockKnown2|0
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Warlock ~ Pact Magic.MOD		DEFINE:WarlockCast3|0	DEFINE:WarlockKnown3|0
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Warlock ~ Pact Magic.MOD		DEFINE:WarlockCast4|0	DEFINE:WarlockKnown4|0
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Warlock ~ Pact Magic.MOD		DEFINE:WarlockCast5|0	DEFINE:WarlockKnown5|0
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Warlock ~ Pact Magic.MOD	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Warlock Known Progression Selection|1

###Block: Choose Warlock Known Progression
Grant Highest Known only	KEY:Warlock Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only		CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Known Progression	DESC:This will manipulate your spells known to increase to the max highest allowed by the rules.
Follow Standard Progression	KEY:Warlock Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression		CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Known Progression	DESC:This will follow the progression chart in the Player's Handbook.
Choose Own Progression		KEY:Warlock Known Progression ~ Choose Own Progression		CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Warlock Known Progression	DESC:This will force the user to select spells each level.	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Warlock Known|2+(WarlockLVL>=2)+(WarlockLVL>=3)+(WarlockLVL>=4)+(WarlockLVL>=5)+(WarlockLVL>=6)+(WarlockLVL>=7)+(WarlockLVL>=8)+(WarlockLVL>=9)+(WarlockLVL>=11)+(WarlockLVL>=13)+(WarlockLVL>=15)+(WarlockLVL>=17)+(WarlockLVL>=19)

# Grant Highest Known
CATEGORY=Internal|Warlock Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown1|if(WarlockLVL>=1,2,0)+(WarlockLVL>=2)-(WarlockLVL>=3)-(WarlockLVL>=4)-(WarlockLVL>=5)
CATEGORY=Internal|Warlock Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown2|if(WarlockLVL>=3,2,0)+if(WarlockLVL>=4,2,0)-(WarlockLVL>=6)-(WarlockLVL>=7)-(WarlockLVL>=8)-(WarlockLVL>=9)
CATEGORY=Internal|Warlock Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown3|if(WarlockLVL>=5,2,0)+if(WarlockLVL>=6,2,0)-(WarlockLVL>=10)-(WarlockLVL>=11)-(WarlockLVL>=12)-(WarlockLVL>=13)
CATEGORY=Internal|Warlock Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown4|if(WarlockLVL>=7,2,0)+if(WarlockLVL>=8,2,0)-(WarlockLVL>=14)-(WarlockLVL>=15)-(WarlockLVL>=16)-(WarlockLVL>=17)
CATEGORY=Internal|Warlock Known Progression ~ Grant Highest Known only.MOD	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown5|if(WarlockLVL>=9,2,0)+(WarlockLVL>=10)+if(WarlockLVL>=11,2,0)+(WarlockLVL>=12)+if(WarlockLVL>=13,2,0)+(WarlockLVL>=14)+if(WarlockLVL>=15,2,0)+(WarlockLVL>=16)+if(WarlockLVL>=17,2,0)+(WarlockLVL>=19)

# Follow Standard Progression
CATEGORY=Internal|Warlock Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown1|if(WarlockLVL>=1,2,0)+(WarlockLVL>=2)
CATEGORY=Internal|Warlock Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown2|(WarlockLVL>=3)+(WarlockLVL>=4)
CATEGORY=Internal|Warlock Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown3|(WarlockLVL>=5)+(WarlockLVL>=6)
CATEGORY=Internal|Warlock Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown4|(WarlockLVL>=7)+(WarlockLVL>=8)
CATEGORY=Internal|Warlock Known Progression ~ Follow Standard Progression.MOD	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown5|(WarlockLVL>=9)+(WarlockLVL>=11)+(WarlockLVL>=13)+(WarlockLVL>=15)+(WarlockLVL>=17)+(WarlockLVL>=19)

# Choose Own Progression
Warlock Known Level 1		CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Warlock Known	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,1		CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown1|1
Warlock Known Level 2		CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Warlock Known	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,3		CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown2|1
Warlock Known Level 3		CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Warlock Known	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,5		CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown3|1
Warlock Known Level 4		CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Warlock Known	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,7		CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown4|1
Warlock Known Level 5		CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Warlock Known	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,9		CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	MULT:YES	STACK:YES	BONUS:VAR|WarlockKnown5|1

6-th level spells	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Mystic Arcanum 6.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast one level 6 Warlock spell once without expending a spell slot, and you must finish a Long Rest before you can cast it in this way again.	KEY:Mystic Arcanum ~ 6-th level spells	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,11											STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SPELLS|CLASSLIST=Warlock[LEVELMIN=6;LEVELMAX=6]	SELECT:1	SPELLS:Mystic Arcanum 6th|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|%LIST									SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01g1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
7-th level spells	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Mystic Arcanum 7.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast one level 7 Warlock spell once without expending a spell slot, and you must finish a Long Rest before you can cast it in this way again.	KEY:Mystic Arcanum ~ 7-th level spells	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,13											STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SPELLS|CLASSLIST=Warlock[LEVELMIN=7;LEVELMAX=7]	SELECT:1	SPELLS:Mystic Arcanum 7th|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|%LIST									SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01g2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
8-th level spells	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Mystic Arcanum 8.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast one level 8 Warlock spell once without expending a spell slot, and you must finish a Long Rest before you can cast it in this way again.	KEY:Mystic Arcanum ~ 8-th level spells	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,15											STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SPELLS|CLASSLIST=Warlock[LEVELMIN=8;LEVELMAX=8]	SELECT:1	SPELLS:Mystic Arcanum 8th|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|%LIST									SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01g3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
9-th level spells	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:Mystic Arcanum 9.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast one level 9 Warlock spell once without expending a spell slot, and you must finish a Long Rest before you can cast it in this way again.	KEY:Mystic Arcanum ~ 9-th level spells	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,17											STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SPELLS|CLASSLIST=Warlock[LEVELMIN=9;LEVELMAX=9]	SELECT:1	SPELLS:Mystic Arcanum 9th|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|%LIST									SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01g4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

Agonizing Blast	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Choose one of your known Warlock cantrips that deals damage. You can add your Charisma modifier to that spell's da mage rolls. &nl; Repeatable. You can gain this invocation more than once . Each time you do so, choose a different eligible cantrip.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Agonizing Blast	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,2										STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SPELLS|CLASSLIST=Warlock[LEVELMAX=0]														SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Armor of Shadows	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast Mage Armor on yourself without expending a spell slot.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Armor of Shadows													SPELLS:Armor of Shadows|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|Mage Armor												SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Ascendant Step	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast Levitate on yourself without expending a spell slot.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Ascendant Step													SPELLS:Ascendant Step|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|Levitate												SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Devil Sight	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can see normally in Dim Light and Darkness - both magical and nonmagical - within 120 feet of yourself.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Devil Sight	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,2				BONUS:VAR|Darkvision|120|TYPE=Base																				SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Devouring Blade	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The Extra Attack of your Thirsting Blade invocation confers two extra attacks rather than one.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Devouring Blade	PREMULT:2,[PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,12],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Eldritch Invocation ~ Thirsting Blade]										STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:ABILITYSELECTION|Special Ability|Eldritch Invocation ~ Pact of the Blade	SELECT:1													SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a5	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Eldritch Mind	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have Advantage on Constitution saving throws that you make to maintain Concentration.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Eldritch Mind																									SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a6	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	
Eldritch Smite	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Once per turn when you hit a creature with your pact weapon, you can expend a Pact Magic spell slot to deal an extra 1d8 Force damage to the target, plus another 1d8 per level of the spell slot, and you can give the target the Prone condition if it is Huge or smaller.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Eldritch Smite	PREMULT:2,[PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,5],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Eldritch Invocation ~ Pact of the Blade]				BONUS:VAR|Eldritch_Smite|1d8|TYPE=Damage|DAMAGE_TYPE=Force																	SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a7	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Eldritch Spear	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Choose one of your known Warlock cantrips that deals damage and has a range of 10+ feet. When you cast that spell, its range increases by a number of feet equal to 30 times your Warlock level. &nl; Repeatable. You can gain this invocation more than once. Each time you do so, choose a different eligible cantrip.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Eldritch Spear	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,2										STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SPELLS|CLASSLIST=Warlock[LEVELMAX=0]														SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a8	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Fiendish Vigor	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast False Life on yourself without expending a spell slot. When you cast the spell with this feature, you don't roll the die for the Temporary Hit Points; you automatically get the highest number on the die.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Fiendish Vigor	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,2												SPELLS:Fiendish Vigor|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|False Life												SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a9	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Gaze of Two Minds	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can use a Bonus Action to touch a willing creature and perceive through its senses until the end of your next turn. As long as the creature is on the same plane of existence as you, you can take a Bonus Action on subsequent turns to maintain this connection, extending the duration until the end of your next turn. The connection ends if you don't maintain it in this way. While perceiving through the other creature's senses, you benefit from any special senses possessed by that creature, and you can cast spells as if you were in your space or the other creature's space if the two of you are within 60 feet of each other.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Gaze of Two Minds	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,5																								SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a10	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Gift of the Depths	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can breathe underwater, and you gain a Swim Speed equal to your Speed. You can also cast Water Breathing once without expending a spell slot. You regain the ability to cast it in this way again when you finish a Long Rest.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Gift of the Depths	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,5												MOVECLONE:Walk,Swim,*1	SPELLS:Gift of the Depths|TIMES=1|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|Water Breathing												SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a11	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Gift of the Protectors	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:A new page appears in your Book of Shadows when you conjure it. With your permission, a creature can take an action to write its name on that page, which can contain a number of names equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum of one name). When any creature whose name is on the page is reduced to O Hit Points but not killed outright, the creature magically drops to 1 Hit Point instead. Once this magic is triggered, no creature can benefit from it until you finish a Long Rest. As a Magic action, you can erase a name on the page by touching it.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Gift of the Protectors	PREMULT:2,[PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,9],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Eldritch Invocation ~ Pact of the Tome]																								SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a12	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Investment of the Chain Master	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When you cast Find Familiar, you infuse the summoned familiar with a measure of your eldritch power, granting the creature the following benefits. &nl; Aerial or Aquatic. The familiar gains either a Fly Speed or a Swim Speed (your choice) of 40 feet. &nl; Quick Attack. As a Bonus Action, you can command the familiar to take the Attack action. &nl; Necrotic or Radiant Damage. Whenever the familiar deals Bludgeoning, Piercing, or Slashing damage, you can make it deal Necrotic or Radiant damage instead. &nl; Your Save DC. If the familiar forces a creature to make a saving throw, it uses your spell save DC. &nl; Resistance. When the familiar takes damage, you can take a Reaction to grant it Resistance against that damage.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Investment of the Chain Master	PREMULT:2,[PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,5],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Eldritch Invocation ~ Pact of the Chain]																								SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a13	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Lessons of the First One	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have received knowledge from an elder entity of the multiverse, allowing you to gain one Origin feat of your choice (see chapter 5). &nl; Repeatable. You can gain this invocation more than once. Each time you do so, choose a different Origin feat.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Lessons of the First One	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,2								BONUS:VAR|POOL_Origin_Feat|1				STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	SELECT:1									SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a14	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Lifedrinker	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Once per turn when you hit a creature with your pact weapon, you can deal an extra 1d6 Necrotic, Psychic, or Radiant damage (your choice) to the creature, and you can expend one of your Hit Point Dice to roll it and regain a number of Hit Points equal to the roll plus your Constitution modifier (minimum of 1 Hit Point).	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Lifedrinker	PREMULT:2,[PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,9],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Eldritch Invocation ~ Pact of the Blade]										STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:ABILITYSELECTION|Special Ability|Eldritch Invocation ~ Pact of the Blade	SELECT:1								SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a15	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Mask of Many Faces	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast Disguise Self without expending a spell slot.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Mask of Many Faces	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,2												SPELLS:Mask of Many Faces|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|Disguise Self												SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a16	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Master of Myriad Forms	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast Alter Self without expending a spell slot.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Master of Myriad Form	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,5												SPELLS:Master of Myriad Forms|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|Alter Self												SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a17	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Misty Visions	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast Silent Image without expending a spell slot.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Misty Visions	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,2												SPELLS:Misty Visions|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|Silent Image												SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a18	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
One with the Shadows	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:While you're in an area of Dim Light or Darkness, you can cast Invisibility on yourself without expending a spell slot.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ One with the Shadows	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,5												SPELLS:One with the Shadows|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|Invisibility												SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a19	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Otherwordly Leap	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast jump on you r self withou t ex pending a spell slot.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Otherwordly Leap	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,2												SPELLS:Otherwordly Leap|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|Jump												SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a20	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Pact of the Blade	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:As a Bonus Action , you can conjure a pact weapon in your hand- a Simple or Martial Melee weapon of your choice with which you bond - or create a bond with a magic weapon you touch; you can't bond with a magic weapon if someone else is attuned to it or another Warlock is bonded with it. Until the bond ends, yo u have proficiency with the weapon, and you can u se it as a Spellcasting Focus. Whenever you attack with the bonded weapon, you can use your Charisma modifier for the attack and damage rolls instead of using Strength or Dexterity; and you can cause the weapon to deal Necrotic, Psychic, or Radiant damage or its normal damage type. Your bond with the weapon ends if you use this feature's Bonus Action again, if the weapon is more than 5 feet away from you for 1 minute or more, or if you die. A conjured weapon disappears when the bond ends.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Pact of the Blade										STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:WEAPONPROFICIENCY|TYPE=Simple|TYPE=Martial	SELECT:1													SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a21	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Pact of the Chain	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You learn the Find Familiar spell and can cast it as a Magic action without expending a spell slot. When you cast the spell, you choose one of the normal forms for your familiar or one of the following special forms: Imp, Pseudodragon, Quasit, Skeleton, Slaad Tadpole, Sphinx of Wonder, Sprite, or Venomous Snake (see appendix B for the familiar's stat block). Additionally, when you take the Attack action, you can forgo one of your own attacks to allow your familiar to make one attack of its own with its Reaction.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Pact of the Chain					BONUS:VAR|FamiliarLVL|WarlockLVL								SPELLS:Pact of the Chain|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|Find Familiar	ABILITY:Special Ability|AUTOMATIC|Find Familiar											SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a22	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Pact of the Tome	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Stitching together strands of shadow, you conjure forth a book in your hand at the end of a Short or Long Rest. This Book of Shadows (you determine its appearance) contains eldritch magic that only you can access, granting you the benefits below. The book disappears if you conjure another book with this feature or if you die. &nl; Cantrips and Rituals. When the book appears, choose three cantrips, and choose two level 1 spells that have the Ritual tag. The spells can be from any class's spell list, and they must be spells you don't already have prepared. While the book is on your person, you have the chosen spells prepared, and they function as Warlock spells for you. &nl; Spellcasting Focus. You can use the book as a Spellcasting Focus.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Pact of the Tome					BONUS:VAR|POOL_Warlock_Pact_Of_The_Tome_Cantrip|3	BONUS:VAR|POOL_Warlock_Pact_Of_The_Tome_1|2																			SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a23	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Repelling Blast	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Choose one of your known Warlock cantrips that requires an attack roll. When you hit a Large or smaller creature with that cantrip, you can push the creature up to 10 feet straight away from you. &nl; Repeatable. You can gain this invocation more than once. Each time you do so, choose a different eligible cantrip.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Repelling Blast	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,2										STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:SPELLS|CLASSLIST=Warlock[LEVELMAX=0]														SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a24	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Thirsting Blade	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You gain the Extra Attack feature for your pact weapon only. With that feature, you can attack twice with the weapon instead of once when you take the Attack action on your turn.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Thirsting Blade	PREMULT:2,[PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,5],[PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Special Ability,Eldritch Invocation ~ Pact of the Blade]										STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:ABILITYSELECTION|Special Ability|Eldritch Invocation ~ Pact of the Blade	SELECT:1													SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a25	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Visions of Distant Realms	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast Arcane Eye without expending a spell slot.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Visions of Distant Realms	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,9												SPELLS:Visions of Distant Realms|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|Arcane Eye												SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a26	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Whispers of the Grave	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast Speak with Dead without expending a spell slot.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Whispers of the Grave	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,7												SPELLS:Whispers of the Grave|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WarlockLVL|Speak with Dead												SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a27	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Whitch Sight	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Warlock Class Feature.Eldritch Invocation.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have Truesight with a range of 30 feet.	KEY:Eldritch Invocation ~ Witch Sight	PREVARGTEQ:WarlockLVL,15						BONUS:VAR|TruesightRange|30|TYPE=Base																		SORTKEY:Class_Warlock_01a28	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

