# Wizard Cantrips
Acid Splash			KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Acid Splash							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Acid Splash,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Acid Splash		SOURCEPAGE:p.211	DESC:DESC:You hurl a bubble of acid. Choose one creature within range, or choose two creatures within range that are within 5 feet of each other. A target must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw or take 1d6 acid damage. This spell's damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).
Blade Ward			KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Blade Ward							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Blade Ward,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Blade Ward		SOURCEPAGE:p.218	DESC:You extend your hand and trace a sigil of warding in the air. Until the end of your next turn, you have resistance against bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage dealt by weapon attacks.
Chill Touch			KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Chill Touch							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Chill Touch,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Chill Touch		SOURCEPAGE:p.221	DESC:You create a ghostly, skeletal hand in the space of a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the creature to assail it with the chill of the grave. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 necrotic damage, and it can't regain hit points until the start of your next turn. Until then, the hand clings to the target. If you hit an undead target, it also has disadvantage on attack rolls against you until the end of your next turn. This spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).
Dancing Lights		KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Dancing Lights							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Dancing Lights,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Dancing Lights		SOURCEPAGE:p.230	DESC:You create up to four torch-sized lights within range, making them appear as torches, lanterns, or glowing orbs that hover in the air for the duration. You can also combine the four lights into one glowing vaguely humanoid form of Medium size. Whichever form you choose, each light sheds dim light in a 10-foot radius. As a bonus action on your turn, you can move the lights up to 60 feet to a new spot within range. A light must be within 20 feet of another light created by this spell, and a light winks out if it exceeds the spell's range.
Elementalism		KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Elementalism							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Elementalism,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Elementalism		SOURCEPAGE:p.231	DESC:.
Fire Bolt			KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Fire Bolt							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Fire Bolt,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Fire Bolt			SOURCEPAGE:p.242	DESC:You hurl a mote of fire at a creature or object within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, the target takes 1d10 fire damage. A flammable object hit by this spell ignites if it isn't being worn or carried. This spell's damage increases by 1d10 when you reach 5th level (2d10), 11th level (3d10), and 17th level (4d10).
Friends			KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Friends								CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Friends,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Friends			SOURCEPAGE:p.244	DESC:For the duration, you have advantage on all Charisma checks directed at one creature of your choice that isn't hostile toward you. When the spell ends, the creature realizes that you used magic to influence its mood and becomes hostile toward you. A creature prone to violence might attack you. Another creature might seek retribution in other ways (at the DM's discretion), depending on the nature of your interaction with it.
Light				KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Light								CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Light,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																														SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Light			SOURCEPAGE:p.255	DESC:You touch one object that is no larger than 10 feet in any dimension. Until the spell ends, the object sheds bright light in a 20-foot radius and dim light for an additional 20 feet. The light can be colored as you like. Completely covering the object with something opaque blocks the light. The spell ends if you cast it again or dismiss it as an action. If you target an object held or worn by a hostile creature, that creature must succeed on a Dexterity saving throw to avoid the spell.
Mage Hand			KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Mage Hand							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mage Hand,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Mage Hand			SOURCEPAGE:p.256	DESC:A spectral, floating hand appears at a point you choose within range. The hand lasts for the duration or until you dismiss it as an action. The hand vanishes if it is ever more than 30 feet away from you or if you cast this spell again. You can use your action to control the hand. You can use the hand to manipulate an object, open an unlocked door or container, stow or retrieve an item from an open container, or pour the contents out of a vial. You can move the hand up to 30 feet each time you use it. The hand can't attack, activate magic items, or carry more than 10 pounds.
Mending			KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Mending								CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mending,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Mending			SOURCEPAGE:p.259	DESC:This spell repairs a single break or tear in an object you touch, such as a broken chain link, two halves of a broken key, a torn cloak, or a leaking wineskin. As long as the break or tear is no larger than 1 foot in any dimension, you mend it. leaving no trace of the former damage. This spell can physically repair a magic item or construct, but the spell can't restore magic to such an object.
Message			KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Message								CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Message,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Message			SOURCEPAGE:p.259	DESC:You point your finger toward a creature within range and whisper a message. The target (and only the target) hears the message and can reply in a whisper that only you can hear. You can cast this spell through solid objects if you are familiar with the target and know it is beyond the barrier. Magical silence. 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood blocks the spell. The spell doesn't have to follow a straight line and can travel freely around corners or through openings.
Mind Sliver		KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Mind Sliver							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Mind Sliver,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																											SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Mind Sliver		SOURCEPAGE:p.260	DESC:You drive a disorienting spike of psychic energy into the mind of one creature you can see within range. The target must succeed on an Intelligence saving throw or take 1d6 psychic damage and subtract 1d4 from the next saving throw it makes before the end of your next turn. This spell's damage increases by 1d6 when you reach 5th level (2d6), 11th level (3d6), and 17th level (4d6).	
Minor Illusion		KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Minor Illusion							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Minor Illusion,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Minor Illusion		SOURCEPAGE:p.260	DESC:You create a sound or an image of an object within range that lasts for the duration. The illusion also ends if you dismiss it as an action or cast this spell again. If you create a sound, its volume can range from a whisper to a scream. It can be your voice, someone else's voice, a lion's roar, a beating of drums, or any other sound you choose. The sound continues unabated throughout the duration, or you can make discrete sounds at different times before the spell ends. If you create an image of an object-such as a chair, muddy footprints, or a small chest-it must be no larger than a 5-foot cube. The image can't create sound, light, smell, or any other sensory effect. Physical interaction with the image reveals it to be an illusion, because things can pass through it. If a creature uses its action to examine the sound or image, the creature can determine that it is an illusion with a successful Intelligence (Investigation) check against your spell save DC. If a creature discerns the illusion for what it is, the illusion becomes faint to the creature.
Poison Spray		KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Poison Spray							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Poison Spray,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Poison Spray		SOURCEPAGE:p.266	DESC:You extend your hand toward a creature you can see within range and project a puff of noxious gas from your palm. The creature must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take 1d12 poison damage. This spell's damage increases by 1d12 when you reach 5th level (2d12), 11th level (3d12), and 17th level (4d12).
Prestidigitation		KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Prestidigitation						CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Prestidigitation,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Prestidigitation	SOURCEPAGE:p.267	DESC:This spell is a minor magical trick that novice spellcasters use for practice. You create one of the following magical effects within range: * You create an instantaneous, harmless sensory effect, such as a shower of sparks, a puff of wind, faint musical notes, or an odd odor. * You instantaneously light or snuff out a candle, a torch, or a small campfire. * You instantaneously clean or soil an object no larger than 1 cubic foot. * You chill, warm, or flavor up to 1 cubic foot of nonliving material for 1 hour. * You make a color, a small mark, or a symbol appear on an object or a surface for 1 hour. * You create a nonmagical trinket or an illusory image that can fit in your hand and that lasts until the end of your next turn. If you cast this spell multiple times, you can have up to three of its non-instantaneous effects active at a time, and you can dismiss such an effect as an action.
Ray of Frost		KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Ray of Frost							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Ray of Frost,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Ray of Frost		SOURCEPAGE:p.271	DESC:A frigid beam of blue-white light streaks toward a creature within range. Make a ranged spell attack against the target. On a hit, it takes 1d8 cold damage, and its speed is reduced by 10 feet until the start of your next turn. The spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).
Shocking Grasp		KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Shocking Grasp							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Shocking Grasp,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Shocking Grasp		SOURCEPAGE:p.275	DESC:Lightning springs from your hand to deliver a shock to a creature you try to touch. Make a melee spell attack against the target. You have advantage on the attack roll if the target is wearing armor made of metal. On a hit, the target takes 1d8 lightning damage, and it can't take reactions until the start of its next turn. The spell's damage increases by 1d8 when you reach 5th level (2d8), 11th level (3d8), and 17th level (4d8).
Thnderclap		KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Thunderclap							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Thunderclap,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Thunderclap		SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Toll the Dead		KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ Toll the Dead					CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|Toll the Dead,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|Toll the Dead		SOURCEPAGE:PHB
True Strike			KEY:Wizard Cantrip ~ True Strike							CATEGORY:Internal			TYPE:Wizard Cantrip									SPELLS:Wizard Cantrip|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=1|True Strike,Spell_DC_Wizard																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													SPELLKNOWN:CLASS|Wizard=0|True Strike		SOURCEPAGE:p.284	DESC:You extend your hand and point a finger at a target in range. Your magic grants you a brief insight into the target's defenses. On your next turn, you gain advantage on your first attack roll against the target, provided that this spell hasn't ended.

###TODO Scholar spells (1st or 2nd, 1 action casting)

###Block:Wizard Subclass																																
Abjurer	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Wizard Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your study of magic is focused on spells that block, banish, or protect- ending harmful effects, banishing evil influences, and protecting the weak. Abjurers are sought when baleful spirits require exorcism, when locations must be guarded against magical spying, and when portals to other planes of existence must be closed. Adventuring parties value Abjurers for the protection they provide against a variety of hostile magic and other attacks.	KEY:Wizard Subclass ~ Abjurer																		ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Abjurer ~ Abjuration Savant|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,3	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Abjurer ~ Arcane Ward|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,3	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Abjurer ~ Projected Ward|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,6	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Abjurer ~ Spell Breaker|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,10	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Abjurer ~ Spell Resistance|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,14				SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Diviner	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Wizard Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The counsel of a Diviner is sought by those who want a clearer understanding of the past, present, and future. As a Diviner, you strive to part the veils of space, time, and consciousness. You work to master spells of discernment, remote viewing, supernatural knowledge, and foresight.	KEY:Wizard Subclass ~ Diviner																		ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Diviner ~ Divination Savant|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,3	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Diviner ~ Portent|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,3	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Diviner ~ Expert Divination|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,6	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Diviner ~ The Third Eye|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,10	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Diviner ~ Greater Portent|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,14			SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Evoker	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Wizard Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your studies focus on magic that creates powerful elemental effects such as bitter cold , searing flame, rolling thunder, crackling lightning, and burning acid. Some Evokers find employment in military forces, serving as artillery to blas t armies from a far. Others use their power to protect others, while some seek their own gain.	KEY:Wizard Subclass ~ Evoker																		ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Evoker ~ Evocation Savant|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,3	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Evoker ~ Potent Cantrip|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,3	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Evoker ~ Sculpt Spell|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,6	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Evoker ~ Empowered Evocation|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,10	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Evoker ~ Overchannel|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,14			SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Illusionist	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Wizard Subclass.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You specialize in magic that dazzles the senses and tricks the mind, and the illusions you craft make the impossible seem real.	KEY:Wizard Subclass ~ Illusionist																		ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Illusionist ~ Illusion Savant|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,3	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Illusionist ~ Improved Illusion|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,3	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Illusionist ~ Phantasmal Creatures|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,6	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Illusionist ~ Illusory Self|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,10	ABILITY:Wizard Class Feature|AUTOMATIC|Illusionist ~ Illusory Reality|PREVAREQ:WizardLVL,14			SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e4	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

Abjuration Savant	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Abjurer.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Choose two Wizard spells from the Abjuration school, each of which must be no higher than level 2, and add them to your spellbook for free. In addition, whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Abjuration school to your spellbook for free. The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots.	KEY:Abjurer ~ Abjuration Savant	DEFINE:AbjurationSavant|0					BONUS:VAR|AbjurationSavant|(WizardLVL-2)	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Wizard Known|AbjurationSavant																				SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e1a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Arcane Ward	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Abjurer.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can weave magic around yourself for protection. When you cast an Abjuration spell with a spell slot, you can simultaneously use a strand of the spell's magic to create a magical ward on yourself that lasts until you finish a Long Rest. The ward has a Hit Point maximum equal to twice your Wizard level plus your Intelligence modifier. Whenever you take damage, the ward takes the damage instead, and if you have any Resistances or Vulnerabilities, apply them before reducing the ward's Hit Points. If the damage reduces the ward to O Hit Points, you take any remaining damage. While the ward has 0 Hit Points, it can't absorb damage, but its magic remains. Whenever you cast an Abjurat ion spell with a spell slot, the ward regains a number of Hit Points equal to twice the level of the spell slot. Alternatively, as a Bonus Action, you can expend a spell slot, and the ward regains a number of Hit Points equal to twice the level of the spell slot expended. Once you create the wa rd, you can't cr eate it again until you fini sh a Long Rest.	KEY:Abjurer ~ Arcane Ward	DESC:&nl; max HP %1.|ArcaneWard	DEFINE:ArcaneWard|0					BONUS:VAR|ArcaneWard|2*(WizardLVL+INT)																					SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e1b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Projected Ward	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Abjurer.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When a creature that you can see with in 30 feet of yourself takes dam age, you can take a reaction to cause your Arcane Ward to absorb th at da mage. If this damage reduces the ward to O Hit Points, the warded creat ure takes a ny remaining damage. If that creature has a ny Resis ta nces or Vulnerabilities, apply them before reducing the ward's Hit Points.	KEY:Abjurer ~ Projected Ward																												SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e1c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Spell Breaker	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Abjurer.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You alw ays have the Counterspell and Dispel Magic spells prepared. In addition, you can cast Dispel Magic as a Bonus Action, and you can add your Proficiency Bonus to its ability check. When you cast either spell with a spell slot, that slot isn't expended if the spell fails to stop a spell.	KEY:Abjurer ~ Spell Breaker										SPELLS:Spell Breaker|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WizardLVL|Counterspell|Dispel Magic																		SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e1d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Spell Resistance	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Abjurer.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have Advantage on saving throws against spells, and you have Resistance to the damage of spells.	KEY:Abjurer ~ Spell Resistance																												SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e1e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	

Divination Savant	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Diviner.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Choose two Wizard spells from the Divination school, each of which must be no higher than level 2, and add them to your spellbook for free. In addition, whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Divination school to your spellbook for free . The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots.	KEY:Diviner ~ Divination Savant	DEFINE:DivinationSavant|0					BONUS:VAR|DivinationSavant|(WizardLVL-2)	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Wizard Known|DivinationSavant																				SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e2a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Portent	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Diviner.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Glimpses of the future begin to press on your awareness. Whenever you finish a Long Rest, roll two d20s and record the numbers rolled. You can replace any D20 Test made by you or a creature that you can see with one of these foretelling rolls. You must choose to do so before the roll, and you can replace a roll in this way only once per turn. Each foretelling r oll can be used only once. When you finish a Long Rest, you lose any unused foretelling rolls.	KEY:Diviner ~ Portent																												SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e2b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Expert Divination	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Diviner.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Casting Divinat ion spells comes so easily to you that it expends only a fraction of your spellcasting efforts. When you cast a Divination spell using a level 2+ spell slot, you rega in one expended spell slot. The slot you rega in must be of a level lower than the slot you expended and can't be higher than level 5.	KEY:Diviner ~ Expert Divination																												SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e2c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
The Third Eye	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Diviner.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can increase your powers of perception. As a Bous Action, choose one of the following benefits, which lasts until you start a Short or Long Rest. You can't use this feature again until you finish a Short or Long Rest. &nl; Darkvision. You gain Darkvision with a range of 120 feet. &nl; Greater Comprehension. You can read any language. &nl; See Invisibility. You can cast See Invisibility without expending a spell slot.	KEY:Diviner ~ The Third Eye						BONUS:VAR|POOL_The_Third_Eye|1																						SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e2d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Greater Portent	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Diviner.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:The visions in your dreams intensify and paint a more accurate picture in your mind of what is to come. Roll three d20s for your Portent feature rather than two.	KEY:Diviner ~ Greater Portent																												SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e2e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

Darkvision	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:The Third Eye.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Darkvision 120-ft.	KEY:The Third Eye ~ Darkvision						BONUS:VAR|DarkvisionRange|120|TYPE=Base																						SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e2d1	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Greater Comprehension	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:The Third Eye.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can read any language.	KEY:The Third Eye ~ Greater Comprehension																												SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e2d2	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
See Invisibility	CATEGORY:Internal	TYPE:The Third Eye.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast See Invisibility without expending a spell slot.	KEY:The Third Eye ~ See Invisibility													SPELLS:The Third Eye|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WizardLVL|See Invisibility															SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e2d3	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

Evocation Savant	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Evoker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Choose two Wizard spells from the Evocation school, each of which must be no higher than level 2, and add them to your spellbook for free. In addition , whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Evocation school to your spellbook for free . The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots.	KEY:Evoker ~ Evocation Savant	DEFINE:EvocationSavant|0					BONUS:VAR|EvocationSavant|(WizardLVL-2)	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Wizard Known|EvocationSavant																				SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e3a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Potent Cantrip	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Evoker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Your damaging cantrips affect even creatures that avoid the brunt of the effect. When you cast a cantrip at a creature and you miss with the attack roll or the target succeeds on a saving throw against the cantrip, the target takes half the cantrip's damage (if any) but suffers no additional effect from the cantrip.	KEY:Evoker ~ Potent Cantrip																											SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e3b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Sculpt Spell	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Evoker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can create pockets of relative safety within the effects of your evocations. When you cast an Evocation spell that affects other creatures that you can see, you can choose a number of them equal to 1 plus the spell's level. The chosen creatures automatically succeed on their saving throws against the spell, and they take no damage if they would normally take half damage on a successful save.	KEY:Evoker ~ Sculpt Spell																											SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e3c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Empowered Evocation	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Evoker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Whenever you cast a Wizard spell from the Evocation school, you can add your Intelligence modifier to one damage roll of that spell.	KEY:Evoker ~ Empowered Evocation																											SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e3d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Overchannel	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Evoker.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can increase the power of your spells. When you cast a Wizard spell with a spell slot of levels 1- 5 that deals damage, you can deal max imum damage with that spell on the turn you cast it. The first time you do so, you su ffer no adverse effect. If you use this feature again before you finish a Long Rest, you take 2d12 Necro tic da mage for each level of the spell slot immediately after you cast it. This damage ignores Resistance and Immunity. Each time you use this featu re agai.n before finishing a Long Rest, the Necrotic damage per spell level increases by 1d12.	KEY:Evoker ~ Overchannel																											SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e3e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB

Illusion Savant	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Illusionist.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:Choose two Wizard spells from the Illusion school, each of which must be no higher than level 2, and add them to your spellbook for free. In addition , whenever you gain access to a new level of spell slots in this class, you can add one Wizard spell from the Illusion school to your spellbook for free . The chosen spell must be of a level for which you have spell slots.	KEY:Illusionist ~ Illusion Savant	DEFINE:IllusionSavant|0					BONUS:VAR|IllusionSavant|(WizardLVL-2)	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Wizard Known|IllusionSavant																				SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e4a	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Improved Illusion	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Illusionist.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You can cast Illusion spells without providing Verbal components, and if an Illusion spell you cast has a range of 10+ feet, the range increases by 60 feet. You also know the Minor Illusion cantrip. If you already know it, you learn a different Wizard cantrip of your choice. The can trip doesn't count against your number of cantrips known. You can create both a sound and an image with a single casting of Minor Illusion, and you can cast it as a Bonus Action.	KEY:Illusionist ~ Improved Illusion						BONUS:VAR|POOL_Wizard_Cantrip|1																						SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e4b	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Phantasmal Creatures	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Illusionist.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You always have the Summon Beast and Summon Fey spells prepared. Whenever you cast either spell, you can change its school to Illusion, which causes the summoned creature to appear spectral. You can cast the Illusion version of each spell without expending a spell slot, but casting it without a slot halves the creature's Hit Points. Once you cast either spell without a spell slot, you must finish a Long Rest before you can cast the spell in that way again.	KEY:Illusionist ~ Phantasmal Creatures										SPELLS:Phantasmal Creatures|TIMES=ATWILL|CASTERLEVEL=WizardLVL|Summon Beast|Summon Fey															SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e4c	SOURCEPAGE:PHB
Illusory Self	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Illusionist.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:When a creature hits you with an attack roll, you can take a Reaction to interpose an illusory duplicate of yourself between the attacker and yourself. The attack automatically misses you, then the illu- sion dissipates. Once you use this feature, you can't use it again until you finish a Short or Long Rest. You can also restore your use of it by expending a level 2+ spell slot (no action required).	KEY:Illusionist ~ Illusory Self																												SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e4d	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	
Illusory Reality	CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Wizard Class Feature.Class Feature.Illusionist.SpecialQuality	VISIBLE:YES	DESC:You have learned to weave shadow magic into your illusions to give them a semi-reality. When you cast an Illusion spell with a spell slot, you can choose one inanimate, non magical object that is part of the illusion and make that object real. You can do this on your turn as a Bonus Action while the spell is on-going. The object remains real for 1 minute, during which it can't deal damage or give any conditions. For example, you can create an illusion of a bridge over a chasm, and then make it real and cross it.	KEY:Illusionist ~ Illusory Reality																												SORTKEY:Class_Wizard_01e4e	SOURCEPAGE:PHB	
